column3: ShortDesc
column4: LongDesc

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18071_ShortDesc", "Powerful liquor of a mystically green hue")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18071_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was quick to laugh, quick and terrible in his wrath. He was a valiant trencherman, and strong drink was a passion and a weakness with him.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nA powerful drink, often said to taste like a mixture of dessert and a death god\'s tears, absinthe is often mixed with water and sugar. Poets, artists, and mad revelers of the most decadent disposition swear by this green drink\'s reputed powers to cause visions and reveling bedlam. The Mad King of Ophir, Moranthes II, is said drink the stuff with every meal. Absinthe heavily heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_ShortDesc", "Arrows made with an Abysmal Fang")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53652_LongDesc", "The fangs of the Abysmal Remnant are made of a hardened substance that can withstand strong acid. They are also razor sharp.\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53653_ShortDesc", "Bolts made with an Abysmal Fang")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53653_LongDesc", "The fangs of the Abysmal Remnant are made of a hardened substance that can withstand strong acid. They are also razor sharp. \nBolts can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers crafted from the eye of the Abysmal Remnant")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

As far as trophies go, these dagger are amongst the most bizarre. Made with the hypnotic eye of the Abysmal Remnant embedded in the blade, it has a fearsome aspect but does not seem to have any specific powers beyond that. 

Perhaps in time, certain powers will reveal themselves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14185_ShortDesc", "An eye from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14185_LongDesc", "This eye seems to glow with an inhuman intelligence. The creature from which it was taken was of supernatural origin and this large, almost hypnotic eye explains how it could lure prey close enough to feast.\nWhile the properties of the eye seem to have passed with the death of the creature, it will still make for an impressive trophy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14186_ShortDesc", "A fang from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14186_LongDesc", "This fang, harvested from the corpse of the Abysmal Remnant, is made of an extremely hard substance. Due to the acidic environment in which the creature lived the material has developed several properties beyond regular ivory or bone which mean that it is durable")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14187_ShortDesc", "Flesh harvested from the Abysmal Remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14187_LongDesc", "This foul-smelling, acidic meat does not look or smell appetizing.\nConsidering the creature that it came from, and the environment where it was found, consuming this would be a foolhardy endeavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted from the eye of Abysmal Remnant")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

Staring long enough into the eye of the Abysmal Remnant, embedded in this sword, fills the mind with bizarre images.

Once, the Priestking made a pact with a demon from the outer void to inhabit some formed flesh that he was crafting. This was to be a weapon, used in the war against the human city in the north.

The experiment failed, the creature was born limbless and the experiment was abandoned. An acolyte of the Priestking tossed it into the sewer system, to drown in The Dregs.

But the creature did not die, and the demon was not freed. It found a pool where it could excrete the acid that it needed to survive. And then it reached out with its mind, looking for food.

Over time, it grew and the rats and other vermin in the sewers were no long enough to sustain it...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80963_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80963_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He understood now the mystery of the strangers who had disappeared from the house of Aram Baksh; the riddle of the black drum thrumming out there beyond the palm groves, and of that pit of charred bones - that pit where strange meat might be roasted under the stars, while black beasts squatted about to glut a hideous hunger.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17113_ShortDesc", "A flask of abyssal violet dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17113_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_ShortDesc", "A vicious sword made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51978_ShortDesc", "A pickaxe made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51978_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I know him not,' he answered. 'He is mad to say I hired him. Let him take his just desserts. He has a strong back and the toil in the mines will be well for him.'</> - The God in the Bowl

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.
Created in the fires at the burning heart of the forge and wrought in ornate patterns as it cooled, this pick is strong and durable. It almost seems a shame to waste it on rocks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.\n\nThis shield is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51970_ShortDesc", "A sickle made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51970_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula\n\nSickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51982_ShortDesc", "A vicious spear made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51982_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51599_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Acheronian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51599_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51985_ShortDesc", "A vicious war-axe made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51985_LongDesc", "This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41022_ShortDesc", "A patch kit for repairing damaged armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41022_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan's dark scarred face was darker yet with passion; his black armor was hacked to tatters and splashed with blood; his great sword red to the cross-piece.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

A warrior needs to be able to rely on their armor in the heat of battle. When the broadswords swing, a layer of leather or steel can mean the difference between life and death.

This patch kit, containing scraps of metals, leather and hide, can be used to repair the most egregious insults to a piece of armor, though it will never be able to repair them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41074_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for improving the poise of a set of armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41074_LongDesc", "In Poitain, the shining southern province of Aquilonia, it is common for men to engage in contests of arms wearing full plate armor. And among those people it is commonly understood that a once a warrior falls in full plate, they will be battling to return to their feet.

This kit, developed by the smiths of that fair land, is designed to resettle the weight of the armor set such that it matches the wearers center of balance. This means less chance of falling in battle and more time spent on the feet.

This simple kit will increase the poise value of armor considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41061_ShortDesc", "A blunted fitting that can be applied to a weapon to increase concussive damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41061_LongDesc", "Sometimes the best course in combat is not to defeat an enemy, but to see them humiliated and begging for mercy. Or dragged back to spend some time whimpering on the Wheel of Pain.

This fitting can be attached to almost any weapon and increases the chance of knocking an enemy out before they bleed to death.

Applying this advanced fitting will increase the concussion damage of a weapon considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41066_ShortDesc", "A reinforcement that can be used to make weapons and armor more durable")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41066_LongDesc", "A warrior relies on their strength, their skill and their weapon to carry them in battle. If any of these are broken in the clash of swords, it puts life and limb at risk.

This reinforcement can be used to find the flaws in a weapon or piece of armor and buttress them against the storm of battle.

This simple reinforcement will increase the durability of a weapon or a piece of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41058_ShortDesc", "An assortment of upgrades to make tools more efficient")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41058_LongDesc", "There is wisdom among the simple peoples of the world; those who spend their time tilling, hunting, growing and harvesting.

The time-tested techniques for improving the harvesting capacity of tools have been distilled into the upgrades found in this kit.

Applying this advanced upgrade to a tool will increase its harvesting capacity considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41054_ShortDesc", "A bag of unpleasant things that can be attached to weapons to increase their damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41054_LongDesc", "Some warriors adorn their weapons to intimidate their foes and make them a memorable presence on the battlefield.

But the collection of spikes and studs contained in this bag have a single purpose - to wreck foes. Whether hammer, sword, or spear - there is something here to bring ruination, laceration, and devastation to the bodies and minds of enemies everywhere.

Applying this advanced kit to a weapon will increase its damage considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41026_ShortDesc", "A toolkit for repairing damaged weapons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41026_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He rushed in, hacking madly, but Conan, recognizing him, shattered his sword with a short terrific chop and with a powerful push of his open hand sent him reeling to the floor.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the fury of battle has subsided and the lightning clash of weapons has stilled, the victors are left to count the cost. And sometimes the price of battle is the very weapons that are used to wage it.

This kit, containing a whetstone, a hone and a small portion of blade oil, will allow even unskilled crafters to repair the worst damage to their blades, though it will never be able to renew them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41077_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for making armor more pliant and flexible")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41077_LongDesc", "Uri the Mastersmith once stated that creating an armor set was a balance of three forces - flexibility, strength and coverage. He claimed that in developing a suit of armor, you could have two of these things, but never three. He demonstrated this principle by crafting the King of Nemedia a suit of armor that made him completely impervious to assassins; but also left the King completely unable to move once encased within.
Uri was executed not long afterward.

This small kit contains tools for stretching leather and working metal joints to make them more pliable. 

Using this simple kit on an armor set will make it considerably more flexible when climbing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51828_ShortDesc", "A tool for woodworking")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51828_LongDesc", "A tool specifically designed to enhance the user-experience of slaving away as a thrall. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51548_ShortDesc", "A club that imparts terrible strength on its wielder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51548_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan rose, still smiling, as if to reach into a near-by cooking pot; then quick as a cat he struck Aja a terrible blow with the heavy bone. The Bakalah war-chief slumped over, his skull crushed in, and instantly a frightful yell rent the skies as the Bamulas went into action like blood-mad panthers.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The Bakalah who live on the border of Kush are known for their fearsome raids to take slaves and other captives. And none were more feared than Aja, their war-chief, a great brute of a man who was deadly with both club and spear.

This bony club was allegedly used to kill Aja in a moment of betrayal by a neighboring tribe. It impacts great strength on whoever uses it in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51538_ShortDesc", "Daggers of Akbitanan Steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51538_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Thrusting his dagger-point into the crack, Conan exerted leverage with a corded forearm. The blade bent, but it was of unbreakable Akbitanan steel.</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

The expertise of the smiths of Akbitana combined with a local source of ore that has special qualities, provides the hardest steel weapon on earth.

Usually only sold in the city itself, these daggers are a very rare find. They will not bend or break for a very long time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51567_ShortDesc", "A shield of Akbitanan Steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51567_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Thrusting his dagger-point into the crack, Conan exerted leverage with a corded forearm. The blade bent, but it was of unbreakable Akbitanan steel.</> - Jewels of Gwaluhr

The expertise of the smiths of Akbitana combined with a local source of ore that has special qualities, provides the hardest steel weapon on earth.

Usually only sold in the city itself, this shield is a very rare find. It will not bend or break under repeated blows, in fact the Akbitana steel is called unbreakable, though it does have a limit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11127_ShortDesc", "Black liquid that reeks of the outer dark")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11127_LongDesc", "This black ooze, harvested from the corpse of a demonic entity, steams slightly when exposed to air.
Blood is used to increase the potency of the blasphemous rituals of both priests and sorcerers. And this is particularly potent blood.
The nature of demons is hotly disputed by scholars. Some suggest that they are simply remnants of elder races that stalked the earth before mankind, while others insist that they are formless creatures from the outer void given form by the incantation of vile sorceries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11070_ShortDesc", "A standard mixture used to enhance and vivify potions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11070_LongDesc", "Every alchemist has their own signature base, a set of ingredients that, when combined, are said to up the efficacy of their potions and tinctures.\n\nThis base, created by combining various ingredients scattered across the Exiled Lands, will serve to enhance the process of creating new compounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18072_ShortDesc", "A most refreshing beverage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18072_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And more than looking the part, he felt the part. The awakening of old memories, the resurge of the wild, mad, glorious days of old before his feet were set on the imperial path when he was a wandering mercenary, roistering, brawling, guzzling, adventuring, with no thought for the morrow, and no desire save sparkling ale, red lips, and a keen sword to swing on all the battlefields of the world.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nOne of the oldest forms of alcoholic drink devised by man. With just enough alcohol to preserve it, ale can save lives when water is tainted or in short supply. It cools and refreshes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80673_ShortDesc", "A keg for storing ale")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80673_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He remembered great horns of foaming ale, jacks of sparkling wine gulped carelessly or spilled on the tavern floor.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

Ale is the choice drink of fighting men, especially in taverns where the wine is sour. Served in foaming tankards from large oaken kegs, ale is usually served at room temperature and has a rich fruit flavor.

This keg bears no specific maker's mark, but that won't stop anybody from drinking it")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53001_ShortDesc", "Extract of the aloe plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53001_LongDesc", "Stygian traditions of healing hold that the aloe plant contains many desirable properties. In Luxur, the aloe is harvested for use in the temples of Derkheto to cleanse blemishes from the skin of the priestesses. It is often used to sooth oozing wounds and those who ingest it claim that they feel a burst of wellbeing. Whether these effects are of the body or the mind is irrelevant - ingesting aloe extract seems to give the imbiber a regenerative health effect.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14001_ShortDesc", "This spiky plant has well known medicinal properties")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14001_LongDesc", "A favorite of herbalists the world over, the leaves of this plant are highly sought after for their medicinal properties.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11113_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11113_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18236_ShortDesc", "A green soup with no meat at all")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18236_LongDesc", "Many a survivor knows to apply the juice of the aloe to a burn or to seek the plant\'s moisture when trekking out in the hot wastes, but certain crones and culinary masters know the healing properties of cooking aloe in a soup. Such a meal offers seemingly instant and moderate relief to the injured.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18525_ShortDesc", "A large chest for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18525_LongDesc", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this chest is made from sturdy materials. It can be locked against strangers, and all but the most determined thief will be deterred. No system is perfect, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80952_ShortDesc", "An altar to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80952_LongDesc", "Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine altar will not remain so for long. \nThe hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.\nAltars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_ShortDesc", "A place of sacrifice to Ymir, the Frost Giant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80974_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The clangor of the swords had died away, the shouting of the slaughter was hushed; silence lay on the red-stained snow. The bleak pale sun that glittered so blindingly from the ice-fields and the snow-covered plains struck sheens of silver from rent corselet and broken blade, where the dead lay as they had fallen. The nerveless hand yet gripped the broken hilt; helmeted heads back-drawn in the death-throes, tilted red beards and golden beards grimly upward, as if in last invocation to Ymir the frost-giant, god of a warrior-race...</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said that the battlefield is truly Ymir\'s altar. The war god does not want murdered sacrifices so much as beautiful deaths during the din of glorious combat. Yet those most devoted to the Lord of Storm and War still find themselves constructing places where they can directly commune with their god through the medium of spilt blood. On the cold winds of deadly winter, one might hear the grinding whisper of the Father of Giants saying, \'You get what you give.\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53502_ShortDesc", "A dish purported to be blessed by the gods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53502_LongDesc", "Worshippers of Mitra often bring sacrifices of fruit or grain to lay upon his altar, in return for his blessing. And occasionally his blessing is very formidable indeed, taking the form of Ambrosia. This bizarre substance, considered a food of the gods, has healing properties that the Priests of Mitra use to bring strength and vitality to the poor. How it is made is pure conjecture, as it seems to congeal within empty vessels left out on the altar with no physical intervention from priest or penitent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_ShortDesc", "An arrow of evil and ancient design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53616_LongDesc", "Who knows what sorcery is etched upon the head of this ancient arrow? All that is know is that every shot with it weakens an enemy, corrupting their soul and leaving them gasping for relief.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51212_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed steel axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51212_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with ancient markings, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_ShortDesc", "A bow forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Springing to his feet, he bent his bow powerfully and drove his last shaft point blank at a great hairy shape that soared up at his throat. The arrow was a flying beam of moonlight that flashed onward with but a blur in its course, but the were-beast plunged convulsively in midair and crashed headlong, shot through and through.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Created based on an ancient design found in the Exiled Lands, this bow seems to confuse the eye with its odd, alien curves.

In the thrum of the bowstring, it whispers of gibbering terrors screeching beneath a blood-red moon and the terrified screams of those who flee the merciless hunt.

One who holds this bow too long risks being drawn into its miasma of madness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80218_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Acheronian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80218_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80219_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Acheronian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80219_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?'</> - The God in the Bowl

These daggers are designed in imitation of a style long since faded into the mists of time.

Capable of cutting and dicing, slashing and slaying, daggers are for those who like to get in close and wreak havoc, then move to a safe distance while their foes bleed out.

Some warriors speak of the bloodlust that sweeps over them while using such weapons, an alien force that drives them to acts of great cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51084_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear of ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51084_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it's ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.

When equipped, this javelin seems to whisper to its bearer in the long forgotten language of the Giant-Kings. This constant distraction drains the willpower of the user, but those who master it may uncover hidden strengths.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15503_ShortDesc", "An ancient key")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15503_LongDesc", "This key is of Lemurian origins. It looks like it would fit some of the doors in the Black keep.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_ShortDesc", "An ancient khopesh marked in strange runes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> You shall go down the dark road to Acheron, which is the road of silence and the night. The dark empire, unreborn, shall remain a legend and a black memory.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This khopesh, made from an ancient design, seems to suck away the warmth and daylight. A relic of the past, the shape of it calls up shadow-haunted memories of ape-gods squatting on shattered altars.

It whispers ceaselessly to its bearer and slowly, inevitably, tears their sanity apart.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51087_ShortDesc", "A mace forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51087_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

This mace is designed in imitation of a style long since faded into the mists of time.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Some warriors speak of the bloodlust that sweeps over them while using such weapons, an alien force that drives them to acts of great cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51090_ShortDesc", "A pike forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51090_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The ancient aura that clings to this pike fills any nearby with a distinct sense of dread. What unholy purpose were such weapons put to in the dim past? 

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15502_ShortDesc", "The horn of an ancient rhinoceros")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15502_LongDesc", "There is a certain energy in the fall of an ancient beast. This horn, taken from an ancient rhinocerous, is an occult focal point. Who knows to what use such an artefact could be put?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51623_ShortDesc", "A whispering shield forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51623_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> I am cursed. A fiend from the abysses has set his mark upon me. Night after night he lurks in the shadows, whispering awful secrets to me.</> - Black Colossus

This shield was created from designs looted in the unnamed city ruins within the Exiled Lands. The design of the shield is intricate, with a serpentlike design that is both repellent and fascinating when examined.
This shield is heavy but the solid construction offers additional protection against repeated blows. 

When equipped, this shield seems to whisper to its bearer in the long forgotten language of the Giant-Kings. This constant distraction drains the willpower of the user, but those who master it may uncover hidden strengths.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51215_ShortDesc", "An ancient axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51215_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51941_ShortDesc", "An ancient greatsword marked in strange runes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51941_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">You shall go down the dark road to Acheron, which is the road of silence and the night. The dark empire, unreborn, shall remain a legend and a black memory.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This greatsword, made from an ancient design, seems to suck away the warmth and daylight. A relic of the past, the shape of it calls up shadow-haunted memories of ape-gods squatting on shattered altars.
It whispers ceaselessly to its bearer and slowly, inevitably, tears their sanity apart.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51155_ShortDesc", "A warhammer forged from an ancient design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51155_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> 'This is a grisly thing,' shuddered the clerk. 'It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

Among the relics excavated from the ruins of the Exiled Lands are patterns for weapons that are familiar to blacksmiths. This Warhammer is one such weapon.

Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

This hammer whispers to its bearer of the glory of strength. The sweetness of blood. The nobility of dying in battle. The succulence of marrow slurped raw from shattered bones. The flavor of eyeballs...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11105_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting anklets from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11105_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make anklets from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82007_ShortDesc", "Antelope Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82007_LongDesc", "The head of an Antelope")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81007_ShortDesc", "Antelope Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81007_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52632_ShortDesc", "A set of gauntlets favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52632_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52631_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52630_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52630_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52634_ShortDesc", "A pair of sandals favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52634_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52633_ShortDesc", "A leather riveted skirt favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52633_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

Aquilonian guardsmen are often forced to chase down criminals or leap across rooftops in pursuit of fleeing foes. This short skirt is designed to allow them this freedom of movement, while still protecting their upper thighs.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80152_ShortDesc", "A target for refining ranged techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80152_LongDesc", "Bows require a lifetime of discipline to master and those who do not practise regularly will find themselves losing the edge.\nThis target provides a perfect opportunity to practise with bows, crossbows and thrown weapons without the inevitable conflict that comes from shooting somebody full of arrows.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13601_ShortDesc", "An offering to the bloody spectacle of battle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13601_LongDesc", "Thousands of years past, when the Giant-kings ruled the land and the arena was active, there was a human gladiator named Tyros.\nTyros was a fighter such as the world had never seen - legend had it that he was a descendant of the legendary Kull of Atlantis.\nOne of the many names that were ascribed to Tyros during his gladiatorial career was that of Dragonslayer. It was said that the appearance of Tyros in the arena was enough to drive the beasts wild with rage. This offering, however, was the more likely cause. Before every battle it was burned on the sacrifice altar and the smoke from the offering was said to drive any within the arena into a mighty frenzy - perhaps even reaching across the boundary between life and death.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41076_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for making armor more pliant and flexible")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41076_LongDesc", "Uri the Mastersmith once stated that creating an armor set was a balance of three forces - flexibility, strength and coverage. He claimed that in developing a suit of armor, you could have two of these things, but never three. He demonstrated this principle by crafting the King of Nemedia a suit of armor that made him completely impervious to assassins; but also left the King completely unable to move once encased within.
Uri was executed not long afterward.

This small kit contains tools for stretching leather and working metal joints to make them more pliable. 

Using this simple kit on an armor set will make it more flexible when climbing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41021_ShortDesc", "A patch kit for repairing damaged armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41021_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan's dark scarred face was darker yet with passion; his black armor was hacked to tatters and splashed with blood; his great sword red to the cross-piece.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

A warrior needs to be able to rely on their armor in the heat of battle. When the broadswords swing, a layer of leather or steel can mean the difference between life and death.

This patch kit, containing scraps of metals, leather and hide, can be used to repair the most egregious insults to a piece of armor, though it will never be able to repair them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41070_ShortDesc", "A set of reinforcing plates that can attached to increase the strength of armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41070_LongDesc", "Designed to protect in battle, it can be disastrous if armor shatters beneath a powerful blow. Wise warriors seek to shore up their weaknesses, often by reinforcing the weaker joints of their armor.\n\nAttaching these plates to any set of clothing will increase its armor value.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41073_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for improving the poise of a set of armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41073_LongDesc", "In Poitain, the shining southern province of Aquilonia, it is common for men to engage in contests of arms wearing full plate armor. And among those people it is commonly understood that a once a warrior falls in full plate, they will be battling to return to their feet.

This kit, developed by the smiths of that fair land, is designed to resettle the weight of the armor set such that it matches the wearers center of balance. This means less chance of falling in battle and more time spent on the feet.

This simple kit will increase the poise value of armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41068_ShortDesc", "A kit used to identify and remove superfluous weight from armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41068_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, armor can range from the bone and feathers of the Darfari to the heavy plate worn by members the Silent Legion.
Due to cultural stylings, many of these armors include elements that are not necessary to the primary purpose of armor - protection.

This kit contains various tools for identifying and removing additional weight from a set of armor, while still maintaining its protective properties.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for crafting armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89201_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With the firelight glinting from his blue steel armor, he seemed like an image of steel - dynamic power for the moment quiescent; not resting, but motionless for the instant, awaiting the signal to plunge again into terrific action.</> - Black Colossus\n\nCreating armor, particularly metal armor, requires a large number of exotic tools. This armormaking bench can be used to create anything from the lightest leather armor to hardened steel armor. Provided that the raw materials are available, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18512_ShortDesc", "A table with all the tools required for miscellaneous creations")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18512_LongDesc", "Sometimes a saw and a hammer are simply not enough. This worktable contains a variety of small tools that are uniquely suited to various tasks that involve the creation of dozens of miscellaneous objects.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17099_ShortDesc", "A flask of ash dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17099_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14199_ShortDesc", "Flower of a magenta hue")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14199_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Send my soul clean to Asura!\'</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nThis tall flower originated in Vendhya, but through trade and happenstance, this hardy bloom can now be found growing in many places the world over. Its magenta hue is much sought after for dyes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11098_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11098_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15506_ShortDesc", "A staff topped with a serpentine skull that has glowing eyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15506_LongDesc", "This staff, awakened during a ritual on top of the Tower of the Bat, seems to be possessed by the spirit of a demon. \n\nWhen called upon, the demon can offer advice to the wielder, but whether it can be trusted is a completely different story.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80571_ShortDesc", "A small awning of orange cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80571_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80772_ShortDesc", "A small awning of blue cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80772_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80774_ShortDesc", "A small awning of green cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80774_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80773_ShortDesc", "A small awning of red cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80773_LongDesc", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51577_ShortDesc", "A legendary axe from the Black Kingdoms")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51577_LongDesc", "For centuries, traders in Kush would hear tales of a holy relic known simply as the Axe of the Lion. It was kept in the palace of El Shebbeh for a century, displayed only to the most honored guests of the kingdom.

Then, the axe went missing. All of Shumballah was put on alert and the Chagas and Gallahs were at each other's throats over the theft.

Which was exactly as Shevatas the thief had planned it. He took ship for Zingara while the locals were squabbling and offered it for auction on the docks of Kordava. It was purchased by a local noble and it passed out of sight and mind for many years.

Whoever equips this axe will find themselves as strong as a lion.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51554_ShortDesc", "A hammer that weighs nothing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51554_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Even as he struck, the apparition vanished, and his blade clashed deafeningly on the adamantine surface. Instantly he sensed something abnormal. The blade stuck to the table! He wrenched at it savagely. It did not give. This was no mesmeristic trick. The table was a giant magnet.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

In Zamboula, at the shrine of Hanuman, there is a table that attracts metal objects. The faithful consider it a divine object, and they claim that anything that touches it inherits a part of the divinity temporarily. 

This hammer is made of the same material as that table and, though it is hard to explain, this blade weighs nothing. It seems to repel the very ground itself and push upwards, against the hands of the bearer.

In the hands of the right user, this force can be harnessed into greater momentum and therefore, greater strength.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51541_ShortDesc", "A blade that weighs nothing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51541_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Even as he struck, the apparition vanished, and his blade clashed deafeningly on the adamantine surface. Instantly he sensed something abnormal. The blade stuck to the table! He wrenched at it savagely. It did not give. This was no mesmeristic trick. The table was a giant magnet.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

In Zamboula, at the shrine of Hanuman, there is a table that attracts metal objects. The faithful consider it a divine object, and they claim that anything that touches it inherits a part of the divinity temporarily. 

This blade is made of the same material as that table and, though it is hard to explain, this blade weighs nothing. It seems to repel the very ground itself and push upwards, against the hands of the bearer.

In doing so, it lightens the load of any who carry it, freeing them to focus on their other possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51192_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51192_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41051_ShortDesc", "A fitting that can be applied to almost any weapon to reduce stamina cost")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41051_LongDesc", "Most weapons, when crafted, are designed to a generic standard. Rarely do they account for the variation among individuals - height, strength, reach and balance.\n\nThis fitting, which can easily be altered to match almost any weapon, can change the center of balance to fit the idiosyncrasies of the wielder. This leads to more efficient, less strenuous swings that in turn leads to less strain on the stamina of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10005_ShortDesc", "Strip of bark torn from a tree")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10005_LongDesc", "Strip of bark torn from a tree. Use for tanning leather and as a meagre fuel source. A byproduct of using bark in the tanning process is Tar.
The leatherworkers of Kordava are renowned for their supple and pliant leather. Their process for tanning, and the bark that they use, is a well-guarded secret.
Teas brewed from the bark of certain trees are rumoured to cure many different kinds of ailment.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80671_ShortDesc", "A common wooden barrel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80671_LongDesc", "Used for long term storage or long haul transportation of goods, the sturdy barrel can be found in wagons, storehouses and taprooms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82010_ShortDesc", "The head of a Bat Demon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82010_LongDesc", "The head of a Bat Demon")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81011_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Bat Demon head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81011_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18306_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a bat demon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18306_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to bat demons, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11063_ShortDesc", "The membranous skin of a bat")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11063_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There were grisly feasts beneath the moon, across whose red disk a bat-like shadow incessantly swept.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Though bat-skins are sought after by warlocks and witches, they find little traffic among the common merchants of Hyboria. 

In the Exiled Lands, the bat demons - once used by the Giant-kings as messengers and transport - have turned feral, nesting in the rooves and high places of the land. Their skins might be large enough to use for some purpose.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51579_ShortDesc", "The signature axe of a team of heroes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51579_LongDesc", "Berserkers have long been known in the northern kingdoms for their absolute, unflinching ferocity. Some have suggested that their berserk rages are the result of chewing a particularly potent form of mushroom.\n\nThis axe seems to provide some of the same effect, though whether that is simply in the mind of the bearer, or the result of mushroom spores soaked into the haft of the weapon, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11061_ShortDesc", "The hairy pelt of a bear")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11061_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, such as this one taken from a bear, communicate strength, prowess and primal nature of the beast.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51553_ShortDesc", "A Warhammer which combines hammer and pick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51553_LongDesc", "There is no love lost between the Knights of Poitain and the Zingarans who live just to their south across the border. The Zingarans raid the rich lands of Poitain and the knights take revenge by crossing the border and burning ever crop and field that they see.

The Bec-de-Corbin was developed by a wily Zingaran fighter who wished to be able to more easily penetrate the armor of his Poitanian foes. Copies of the weapon quickly spread southward, along with word of its effectiveness.

Using this weapon in battle provides the wielder with greater armor penetration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80101_ShortDesc", "A comfortable wooden bed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80101_LongDesc", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. They consider it an important part of civilization and sneer at those who sleep on the ground as uncouth savages.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80102_ShortDesc", "A folding bed that takes up little space")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80102_LongDesc", "This bed made of leather stretched over a folding frame, take up less space than a conventional bed.\nCommonly used in barracks, cheap inns and mercenary headquarters, this bed is valued mostly for its ability to be stacked and stored whenever it isn\'t being used.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80103_ShortDesc", "A low divan made in the Stygian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80103_LongDesc", "Both couch and bed, the divan probably originated in Vendhya or Turan, but it rapidly became popular in the kingdom of Stygia. The most elaborate of divans are made of silk and gold inlaid ebony, but they can also be made from simple materials.\nStygian nobles are often portrayed as indolent and decadent and imagery of them lounging on divans, eating and drinking, has contributed to this portrayal. In practicality, during the hottest hours of the day all Stygians retire to their houses for leisure time and these rumors are probably spread by foreign merchants frustrated with a culture that doesn\'t follow their schedule.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80756_ShortDesc", "A low divan made in the Stygian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80756_LongDesc", "Both couch and bed, the divan probably originated in Vendhya or Turan, but it rapidly became popular in the kingdom of Stygia. The most elaborate of divans are made of silk and gold inlaid ebony, but they can also be made from simple materials.\nStygian nobles are often portrayed as indolent and decadent and imagery of them lounging on divans, eating and drinking, has contributed to this portrayal. In practicality, during the hottest hours of the day all Stygians retire to their houses for leisure time and these rumors are probably spread by foreign merchants frustrated with a culture that doesn\'t follow their schedule.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18500_ShortDesc", "Buzzing hive of honey-producing bees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18500_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They ran full into a cloud of stinging death.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nEven the most devolved of savages rarely fails to note the wiliness of beasts to endure countless stings in order to acquire that coveted, golden jelly of the bees. Humankind first learns to remember where wild hives grow and devise clever ways to acquire the treasure inside. As hunters become gatherers and gatherers turn to agriculture, humankind learns to propagate their own hives close to home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18221_ShortDesc", "Sweet drink made from berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18221_LongDesc", "This drink, made from squeezed berries, is sweet to the taste and lightly cools the parched tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51557_ShortDesc", "A bow which confers a bonus to stamina")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51557_LongDesc", "In Ophir lives a pretty lass,
With hair of shining gold,
her rounded breasts and supple ass,
would make a weak man bold.

Her suitors came from all the world,
expectin' to be shunned,
But Bessie was a gen'rous girl,
She did them, every one!

All day and night they heard the cries,
Of Bessie in her bed,
And men were dropping off like flies,
She'd ridden 'em to dead.
Now came the Priest of Mitra,
And the girl he did beseech,
Stop with all this wickedness,
Just listen to me preach

But Bessie was a peacemaker,
She didn't want to fight,
She acted as a horse breaker,
And rode that priest all night.

The priest would not be beaten back,
His heart would not give way,
Though Bessie sought to drain his sack,
He'd shoot throughout the day.

And then together they each found,
The one that they had sought,
In marriage were they solemn bound,
Together they were caught.

The priest and girl they took their vow,
And shaved their hair away,
Let this be used to string a bow,
And may it shoot all day!")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51965_ShortDesc", "A rope made from the tresses of dead women")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51965_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">"...We must climb this cord - little need to ask a Cimmerian if he can."
"If it will bear my weight," grunted Conan, cleansing his sword on the grass.
"It will bear thrice my own," answered Taurus. "It was woven from the tresses of dead women, which I took from their tombs at midnight, and steeped in the deadly wine of the upas tree, to give it strength. I will go first - then follow me closely."</> - The Tower of the Elephant
 Created by soaking the tresses of dead women in the wine of the upas tree, this rope is almost unbreakable.
Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.
Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. This rope, however, will last for a very long time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82020_ShortDesc", "The head of a Black Bear")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82020_LongDesc", "The head of a Black Bear")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82019_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Black Bear head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82019_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'So being hungry and weary, I ate a meal in the tap-room, aware of those questioning eyes fixed upon me, and then lay down in a corner on a bear skin the host fetched for me, and slept.'</> - Wolves Beyond the Border

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved bear's head tells the frightful tale of a battle with this hulking predator.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51566_ShortDesc", "A legendary shield with an interesting strap mechanism")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51566_LongDesc", "Black Bruargh was not always a bandit. In his life before the Border Kingdoms, he was an armorer and blacksmith. He was inventive and liked to try out new designs for shields and weapons.

More often than not, his designs failed, leading to the deaths of those who bought his goods. This led to a drop in custom, so he was forced to close his doors.

Ironically, the last thing he had worked on was a specialized shield with straps that gave the wielder more freedom of movement during battle. His theory was that it would allow for more flexibility in combat.

Black Bruargh left the shield, along with all his other inventions, close his shop, and went on to become one of the most feared bandits in the history of the Border Kingdom.

His debtors sold all off all of his inventions.

Equipping this shield will provide a boost to agility, due to the deft strapping mechanism.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80523_ShortDesc", "A black, beeswax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80523_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nBlack candles are sought after by sorcerers for use in their rituals. The vilest of men purportedly create candles from the blood of demons for communicating with presences that circle in the Outer Void.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80524_ShortDesc", "A black wax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80524_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nBlack candles are sought after by sorcerers for use in their rituals. The vilest of men purportedly create candles from the blood of demons for communicating with presences that circle in the Outer Void.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51573_ShortDesc", "A pike from the legendary Black Dragons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51573_LongDesc", "The Black Dragons are the elite troops of Aquilonia, charged with guarding the Royal family of Aquilonia until death. They are well respected throughout Tarantia and the realm, and the king sends them to serve his justice to bandits and other outlaws.

With such a towering reputation, only the best of recruits and the most valuable equipment are ever used to outfit the troops.

This pike was forged by a master smith in Aquilonia itself - and simply holding it instils a sense of pride and ownership that increases the stamina.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17116_ShortDesc", "A flask of black dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17116_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80738_ShortDesc", "A patterened banner in the fashion of the Black Hand")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80738_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with the signature motif of the Black Hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_ShortDesc", "A heavily stitched pair of boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

These boots are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_ShortDesc", "A pair of earrings worn by buccaneers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nThese earrings are crude, cobbled together from base metals. But among pirates, keeping up a certain appearance is all the matters. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30016_ShortDesc", "A drinking song of questionable quality")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30016_LongDesc", "Sing, sing to the broken road,
Paved in the oaths of forgotten men,
And blood and bones that churned the sand,
The bitter heart of a traitors den.

Behold the swollen corpses song,
Croaked from the throats of hanging fools,
Pattering feet in a rictus jig,
Come to the rope our eager ghouls!

Listen now to the wind swung souls,
Diving down to the rocks and sand,
Holding their tongues in bloat and decay,
Never again to cross The Black Hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80769_ShortDesc", "A sailcloth tent made in the Black Hand style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80769_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80768_ShortDesc", "A sailcloth tent made in the Black Hand style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80768_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80767_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")
