column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80766_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand may be aggressive, disgusting, pirates, but like all good sailors they know their way around a needle and thread.\n\nDuring their time in the Exiled Lands, they have devised several different designs for their tents using little more than sailcloth, sturdy branches and a few lengths of stout rope.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52534_ShortDesc", "A heavily stitched pair of leather pants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52534_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\nThese trousers are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_ShortDesc", "A patchwork vest of leather, rope and cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_LongDesc", "One of the skills that sailors carry with them from port to port is the ability to mend almost any piece of cloth with a needle. Sailors repair their own sails and their clothes turning them overtime into a patchwork of sailcloth, rope a bit of scrap leather. This garment, favored bt eh sailors of the Black Hand looks as though it has been mended so many times that none of the original material is left. Still due to the age of the garment and the many layers it exhibits more durability than it\'s frail appearance would indicate. \nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18041_ShortDesc", "A cold shard from the Outer Dark")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18041_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">First there was the blackness of an utter void, with the cold winds of cosmic space blowing through it. Then shapes, vague, monstrous and evanescent, rolled in dim panorama through the expanse of nothingness, as if the darkness were taking material form.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThere exist whole galaxies of dimensions between the spaces of human perception. Substances in the Outer Dark have a material, but not of any composition that follows earthly laws. One of sorcerous intent can, with the proper skills, reach sidewise into the nighted gulfs and pull forth some of these weird substances, such as black ice. This material is cold, the cold from between the stars, a cold that burns. It can be used in the smelting process of star metal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51976_ShortDesc", "A broadsword fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51976_LongDesc", "The blade of this weapon is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51598_ShortDesc", "A javelin of Black Ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51598_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_ShortDesc", "A sword fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_LongDesc", "The blade of this weapon is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51977_ShortDesc", "A pickaxe fashioned out of pure black ice")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51977_LongDesc", "This pickaxe is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51943_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51943_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90058_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90058_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90076_ShortDesc", "Black Ice-Reinforced roof supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90076_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90077_ShortDesc", "Black Ice-Reinforced roof supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90077_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90283_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90293_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90293_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90288_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of black ice-reinforced wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90288_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90314_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of black ice-reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90314_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90315_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of black ice-reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90315_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90320_ShortDesc", "A wall made of Black Ice Reinforced Stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90320_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.\nA barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90265_ShortDesc", "A ceiling made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90265_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmned in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90270_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90270_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90266_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90266_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90272_ShortDesc", "A low fence made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90272_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90280_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90280_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90263_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90263_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90269_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90269_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90282_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90282_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90281_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90281_LongDesc", "The best battle, they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90271_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90271_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90081_ShortDesc", "A staircase made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90081_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90267_ShortDesc", "A staircase made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90267_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")
