column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90073_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90264_ShortDesc", "A wall made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90264_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90268_ShortDesc", "A wedge made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90268_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90273_ShortDesc", "A wedge foundation made of Black Ice-Reinforced Wood ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90273_LongDesc", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11086_ShortDesc", "Plucked from deadly black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11086_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. Few know the secrets of the alchemy involved and there are few who dare to experiment with such a deadly substance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18291_ShortDesc", "Brewed from the deadly petals of the black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18291_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. 

This potion, steeped in dark mystery, is death to the unprepared. But for those who know when and how to drink it, it can provide an instant surge of sorcerous power.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11087_ShortDesc", "A small bag of black lotus powder ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11087_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then Taurus brought the mouth of the tube to his lips and blew powerfully. A long jet of yellowish powder shot from the other end of the tube and billowed out instantly in a thick green-yellow cloud that settled over the shrubbery, blotting out the glaring eyes.</> - Tower of the Elephant

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover

This powder is known to be deadly to animals when blown into their faces, though with the wrong wind, such an attack can prove deadlier to the attacker.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11088_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the black lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11088_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The next instant, with appalling suddenness, the jungle waved and dimmed out before his eyes; he did not hear the screams that burst out awfully not far away, as his knees collapsed, letting him pitch limply to the earth. Above his prostrate form the great black blossoms nodded in the windless air.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The black lotus is a much feared, oft-discussed, plant. It is said that the scent of the flowers brings mad, blighted dreams that trouble all but the blackest of souls. The juice of the black lotus is death, an instant plunge into darkness from which one can never recover.

It is rumored that the sorcerers of the Black Ring use the Black lotus to recover their necromantic powers. Few know the secrets of the alchemy involved and there are few who dare to experiment with such a deadly substance.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82002_ShortDesc", "Black Rhino Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82002_LongDesc", "The head of a Black Rhino")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81002_ShortDesc", "Black Rhino Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81002_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for shaping metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89301_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

Smithing is a well-known and oft-used profession in the Hyborian kingdoms. In the larger cities and towns, smiths are forced to join guilds that offer them a certain amount of political protection, while enforcing a rigorous set of standards of work and tools.

This bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51542_ShortDesc", "A sword borne by the Adventurers of Nemedia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51542_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I was riding for Belverus on Amalric's business, said the Adventurer, advancing warily. The starlight was a long sheen on the great two-handed sword he bore naked in his hand.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Considered the most dangerous foes in all of Nemedia, the Adventurers are a class of warrior peculiar to that country. They have not attained the wealth and position of knighthood or have fallen from that estate; they are hard-bitten fighters, dedicating their lives to war and adventure. The hold themselves accountable to no man but the King.

The grip of this sword is worn smooth by participation in thousands of battles and the blade is oiled and razor sharp. In the hands of a competent wielder, this two-handed sword does additional damage with every strike.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51462_ShortDesc", "A tool for extracting unfulfilled desires")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51462_LongDesc", "Derketo teaches that when a person dies their unfulfilled desires manifest within their bodies. The worshippers of Derketo have created this tool for extracting that...remnant from those who die while under their ministrations.\n\nJust don\'t look too closely at what it pulls out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51460_ShortDesc", "A hatchet dangerously cold to the touch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51460_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I have seen the hoar-frost glittering in the sun,\' she answered. \'I have heard the wind whispering across the everlasting snows.\'</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said Ymir sends these sacred tools out into the world for champions to find. With such a hatchet, one can harvest the ice of winter itself and use such material to craft garments and weapons holy to the frost giant god.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51457_ShortDesc", "An Ankh used in the ritual purification of the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51457_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Mitra would have folks stand upright before him - not crawling on their bellies like worms, or spilling blood of animals all over his altars.'</> - Black Colossus

The purification of the dead is considered an important part of the death rites of Mitra. When one dies, the vessel that was the body is usually consigned to the flames in a rite that was borne from the legend of the phoenix. It is said that in cleasning the body with fire, a new soul can be reborn from the ashes.

However, before a body is burned, it is ritually purified using an Ankh of Mitra. The body is struck with the Ankh to push out any trace of spirit left trapped within the body, preventing the corpse from rising again and sealing it against necromancy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51459_ShortDesc", "A formal dagger used for ritualistic killings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51459_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> She has instituted human sacrifice, and since her mating with Constantius, no less then five hundred men, women and children have been immolated. Some of these have died on the altar she has set up in the temple, herself wielding the sacrificial dagger, but most have met a more horrible doom. </> - A Witch Shall be Born

The devotees of Set are spread far and wide in the lands of Stygia and the Old Serpent demands human sacrifice as a part of his worship.

These daggers are crafted in the thousands at the forges of Luxur and then spread to the priesthood of the Serpent god.

While the rituals of Set are many and depraved, the fastest is bending a victim over an altar and cutting their heart from their chest.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51458_ShortDesc", "A rudimentary axe created from a jawbone bound to a stout branch")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51458_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> On the heels of the shout came a clamor of blood-freezing screams, the shattering impact of axes on the gate.</> - The Black Stranger

Bladed weapons are generally frowned upon by the worshippers of Yog, but this jawbone is dull enough that it acts more like a club than a sword.
Yoggites believe that the consumption of human flesh gives them the Blessing of Yog for a period of time, which grants them invulnerability to normal weapons.

While Yog is considered a deity in Darfar, scholars in Hyboria classify him as a demon of the Elder night, referencing ancient documents that survived the drowning of Atlantis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11079_ShortDesc", "The crimson hued fluid of life")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11079_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan set his teeth and drove the sword deep. Blood streamed over the blade and his hand, and the monster started convulsively, then lay back quite still.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Blood is an inevitable part of life in the Exiled Lands - splattered on the weapons and clothing of friend and foe, running from the victorious blade, soaked in the bandages of the wounded.

There is a power in blood, not just in the foul sorceries of black mages, but in the blood of ordinary men and women.

Blood can be mixed into compost to increase the potency of the mixture and bring additional life from this side effect of death.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18276_ShortDesc", "Links of meat held together by innards. Tasty.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18276_LongDesc", "Loved by some, hated by most - blood sausages are a staple food amongst the tribes of the frozen north. Every part of the animal is used, even the blood that courses through their veins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80977_ShortDesc", "A place of sacrifice to Ymir, the Frost Giant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80977_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The clangor of the swords had died away, the shouting of the slaughter was hushed; silence lay on the red-stained snow. The bleak pale sun that glittered so blindingly from the ice-fields and the snow-covered plains struck sheens of silver from rent corselet and broken blade, where the dead lay as they had fallen. The nerveless hand yet gripped the broken hilt; helmeted heads back-drawn in the death-throes, tilted red beards and golden beards grimly upward, as if in last invocation to Ymir the frost-giant, god of a warrior-race...</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said that the battlefield is truly Ymir\'s altar. The war god does not want murdered sacrifices so much as beautiful deaths during the din of glorious combat. Yet those most devoted to the Lord of Storm and War still find themselves constructing places where they can directly commune with their god through the medium of spilt blood. On the cold winds of deadly winter, one might hear the grinding whisper of the Father of Giants saying, \'You get what you give.\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17050_ShortDesc", "A flask of blue dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17050_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80623_ShortDesc", "A patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80623_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51103_ShortDesc", "A blunted arrow for taking down enemies at range")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51103_LongDesc", "Originally designed for knocking birds from the air without damaging their meat and feathers, blunted arrows quickly became a staple of thieves and thugs who preferred to take their victims down from a distance.\n\nThe problem with using blunted arrows in combat is that they do very little damage, so the archer has to be accurate or risk the rage of a bruised, charging foe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51104_ShortDesc", "A blunted bolt for taking down enemies at range")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51104_LongDesc", "Originally designed for knocking birds from the air without damaging their meat and feathers, blunted bolts quickly became a staple of thieves and thugs who preferred to take their victims down from a distance.\n\nThe problem with using blunted bolts in combat is that they do very little damage, so the crossbowman has to be accurate or risk the rage of a bruised, charging foe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51102_ShortDesc", "A blunted javelin for knocking out foes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51102_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I watched my opportunity and captured a Shemitish jailer - knocked him senseless as he left the courtyard late one night - dragged him into a cellar near by and questioned him.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

Sometimes an enemy will fight to the death. Sometimes an enemy will flee like a coward.

With this blunted javelin, a single well-placed throw can put down a fleeing enemy for interrogation and humiliation at a later point. 

It can be used in regular melee, of course, but it is somewhat less effective at stabbing than a regular pointed weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41060_ShortDesc", "A blunted fitting that can be applied to a weapon to increase concussive damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41060_LongDesc", "Sometimes the best course in combat is not to defeat an enemy, but to see them humiliated and begging for mercy. Or dragged back to spend some time whimpering on the Wheel of Pain.

This fitting can be attached to almost any weapon and increases the chance of knocking an enemy out before they bleed to death.

Applying this fitting will increase the concussion damage of a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10021_ShortDesc", "Bones and bone fragments from animals and humans")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10021_LongDesc", "Used by shamans and witch doctors for rituals and ceremonial gear, bone is a staple of crafting primitive equipment. 
The people of Darfar are known for ritual cannibalism as a part of their worship of Yog. They use the remains of their victims to craft horrifying weapons and armours.
Bone is not particularly durable and will shatter easily upon iron or steel.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51184_ShortDesc", "Primitive arrows made from bone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51184_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51185_ShortDesc", "Primitive bolts made from bone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51185_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18252_ShortDesc", "Under the delicious broth is something that was recently...human")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18252_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Yet what creature but man breaks bones for their marrow? Perhaps those remnants were mute evidence of a horrible, cannibalistic feast...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nA delicacy out of Darfar. The proper way to serve this delicious, hot broth is with a hull human skull in the bowl, slowly revealed with every slurping spoonful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88884_ShortDesc", "A pile of bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88884_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about these bones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88885_ShortDesc", "A pile of bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88885_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about these bones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51601_ShortDesc", "A shield lashed together from the bones of the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51601_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Wildly driven spears and knives glanced from his helmet or the shield on his left arm, while his broadsword cleft flesh and bone, split skulls, scattered brains and spilled entrails into the bloody dust.</> - The Snout in the Dark

Bones lashed to a wooden frame make for an intimidating defensive wall. Unfortunately, the brittle nature of bone means that intimidation is the strongest element of this shield. A few blows and it will shatter and leave the wielder vulnerable.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Darfari cannibals often craft this type of shield from the leftover bones in their sacrifice pits. The smell of charred flesh still clings to the bones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11078_ShortDesc", "A mixture of fine and coarse bone grindings")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11078_LongDesc", "Kill everything, waste nothing is an adage of vital meaning to the tribes of Hyrkanian nomads who roam the steppes east of Turan. Out on the grasslands, every resource is vital, including the bones and claws of their kills which are ground down into bone meal.\n\nBone meal can be added to compost to improve its composition and, unappetizing as it sounds, it can also be used in some food recipes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_ShortDesc", "A large bonfire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89010_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They camped that night on the northern slopes of those hills, and hook-nosed, fiery-eyed men of the hill tribes came in scores to squat about the fires and repeat news that had come up out of the mysterious desert. </>- Black Colossus\n\nBuilt of large pieces of wood, the bonfire is a blazing beacon in the night. Bonfires give off more light and heat than their lesser relative, the campfire, which can be an advantage if the priority is to remain warm, or a disadvantage if the priority is to remain hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11104_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting bracelets from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11104_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make bracelets from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80511_ShortDesc", "An iron bracketed torch that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80511_LongDesc", "Defending a fortification during a night assault is made infinitely simpler by the ability to see where the enemy is coming from.\nAttaching torches to the walls of a building can free hands to grip a blade or pike and cast a light upon the activities of enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10012_ShortDesc", "A sturdy branch fallen from a tree")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10012_LongDesc", "Branches can be used to create rudimentary weapons and tools, which can then be used to shape wood for more beneficial purposes")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18206_ShortDesc", "A loaf of bread")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18206_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">She gave into his hands a wooden dish heaped with dried  fruits, cheese and barley bread, and a great pot of the heady upland beer, brewed from barley grown in the high valleys.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBread takes on many forms, baked from various mixtures of dough and water. On the climb from savagery, bread tends to come at the dawn of agriculture.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53102_ShortDesc", "A glowing potion that improves underwater breathing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53102_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">She waded out until the low waves were lapping about her waist; then she struck out strongly, swimming with a vigor that promised unusual enurance.</> - The Devil in Iron

The Dregs have always been a dangerous place. When the Giant-kings would send slaves to clean out the sewers, they would often lose valuable servants to the creatures which dwelt in the sewers, not to mention those that drowned when a chamber suddenly flooded.

For the latter, at least, they could craft a solution. Using a combination of the strange glowing plants and heat, they created a potion that would allow those caught in water to be able to buy a few more minutes of precious breathing time.

Slaves still disappeared from time to time, but the scrutiny of the Giant-kings seemed to cause a great reduction in these incidents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16011_ShortDesc", "Shaped stones for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16011_LongDesc", "Loose fitting stones are a poor defense against the elements and the creatures of the Exiled Lands. Bricks, cut from sections of sandstone, provide more strength to structures and can be butressed with iron and steel to create sturdy walls and strong defenses.\n\nThese bricks are shaped to fit, but have not undergone any more specific treatment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14171_ShortDesc", "Foul smelling yellow crystals used in dark rituals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14171_LongDesc", "Brimstone is one of the most sought after alchemical components due its application in a wide variety of concoctions.
Searing fumes make collecting it a difficult task and the bleached bones of those who did not adequately prepare serve as a grisly warning to others.
Combined with sticky tar, brimstone creates steelfire, which is a catalyst that hardens iron into steel.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15516_ShortDesc", "A broken piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15516_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82038_ShortDesc", "The head of a Brown Bear")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82038_LongDesc", "The head of a Brown Bear")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82037_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Brown Bear head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82037_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17010_ShortDesc", "A flask of brown dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17010_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52498_ShortDesc", "A wooden prosthetic leg")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52498_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nSomehow, this peg leg allows the temporary removal of your own - where it is stored is anyones guess.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_ShortDesc", "A wooden prosthetic leg")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nSomehow, this peg leg allows the temporary removal of your own - where it is stored is anyones guess.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18254_ShortDesc", "Roasted bugs on a skewer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18254_LongDesc", "A trick learned from the people of Kush is to skewer assortments of large insects and grubs, with bits of vegetable or fruit for flavor, and roast it all on a fire. It makes for a surprisingly tasty treat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18214_ShortDesc", "Strips of feral meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18214_LongDesc", "Meat can be preserved for a time by salting and drying. The process also improves the flavor, or perhaps covers it up, of stringy and gamy meat. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18074_ShortDesc", "An unlikely drink, sweeter than expected")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18074_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Give me a clean sword and a clean foe to flesh it in. Damnation! What would I not give for a flagon of wine!</> - The Scarlet Citadel\n\nHumankind will find a way to have its drink, and there are those who learned to make an alcoholic beverage where grapes fear to grow. Made from the fermented juice of the cactus, this wine cools the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80213_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80213_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_ShortDesc", "A small campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89001_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Lie here.' He indicated a clean-swept space close to a small flickering fire. He saw no incongruity in a princess lying down on the naked ground beside a campfire, wrapped in a warrior's cloak.</> - Black Colossus

The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around. Made from simple branches and twigs, the campfire is an excellent source of light and heat.

Campfires can be used to cook meat which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.

With the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility. Wary travelers would do well to hide their fires, lest they be ambushed in the night by men with unsavory intentions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80521_ShortDesc", "The melted, half-used stub of a candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80521_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nMade from beeswax shaped around a treated wick, this candle has been used extensively in the past.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80525_ShortDesc", "A metal candleholder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80525_LongDesc", "Mostly used for decoration and to prevent the ever-present danger of candlewax burns, this candleholder is nondescript and could be found in any Hyborian Kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51497_ShortDesc", "A shield of hardened carapace")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51497_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is crafted from the hardened carapace of one of the insectoid creatures that roams the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable - but not as effective as a shield made of metal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for carpentry")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89401_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Our merciful sovereign offers you one more chance, Countess,\" said the tallest of the three, and he spoke Aquilonian without an accent. \"He bids me say that if you soften your proud, rebellious spirit, he will still open his arms to you. If not-\' he gestured toward a grim wooden block in the center of the cell. It was blackly stained, and showed many deep nicks as if a keen edge, cutting through some yielding substance, had sunk into the wood.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe ability to work wood is a useful skill for anybody interested in creating buildings and furniture. This bench is covered with all of the implements that one needs to create anything from houses to chairs.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51829_ShortDesc", "A tool for carpentry")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51829_LongDesc", "A tool specifically designed to enhance the user-experience of slaving away as a thrall. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80601_ShortDesc", "A red, patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80601_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80745_ShortDesc", "A heavy iron cauldron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80745_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldorn means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

This cauldron, however, has seen better days and now only serves a purpose as an ornamental piece.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18210_ShortDesc", "Dark green egg smelling of ammonia")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18210_LongDesc", "There is a method of preserving eggs, developed in faraway Khitai. The details vary among the people, but this method often involves clay or ash or salt or quicklime. The egg, so preserved, turns to a dark green. Those foreign to the practice often only eat such an egg out of desperation or a drunken dare. There is the chance that the one who preserved it did not use the ancient method precisely. An imperfectly preserved egg might bring terrible sickness to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80644_ShortDesc", "A small jar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80644_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80643_ShortDesc", "A ceramic jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80643_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51964_ShortDesc", "Bindings strong enough to constrain a captive for a very long time")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51964_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">In one of these chariots lay Conan, king of Aquilonia, weighted with chains, the tang of defeat in his mouth, the blind fury of a trapped tiger in his soul.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Created of intricate links of iron and steel, this chain is strong enough to drag many times the weight of a man.

Chains have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with chain and they are dragged into captivity.

Chains are vulnerable in their links which chip on stones and break occasionally. The stronger the chain links, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80261_ShortDesc", "A wooden chair")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80261_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth binding that protects the upper body")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that has been wound around the upper body to keep everything in its place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18250_ShortDesc", "Meaty and eye-wateringly spiced")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18250_LongDesc", "A specialty of desert caravans. Whatever meat is available is mixed and stewed and livened with copious amounts of spice. This dish will heavily heat the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11062_ShortDesc", "Pieces of exoskeleton ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11062_LongDesc", "Scorpions and insects are covered in a hardened outer shell that provides them with some protection against the elements. Due to the extremely large size of these creatures in the Exiled Lands, their chitin can be harvested and used to all manner of purposes.\n\nThe harvesting is, of course, the difficult part. A man-sized scorpion is no laughing matter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51851_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed steel axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51851_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17102_ShortDesc", "A flask of Cimmerian blue dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17102_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80509_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80509_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52570_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52570_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These reinforced boots of leather and fur keep one's feet both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52568_ShortDesc", "Furred gauntlets")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52568_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These gauntlets of fur and mail furs keeps one's hands and forearms both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52567_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined chestpiece ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52567_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

This chest armor of mail and furs keeps one's vitals both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52566_ShortDesc", "A riveted fur cap")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52566_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

A medium cap of fur and rivets to keep one safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52569_ShortDesc", "Furred leg armor ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52569_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

This leg armor of mail and furs keeps one's vitals both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18242_ShortDesc", "It\'s hot, and its filling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18242_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They have no hope here or hereafter,\' answered Conan. \'Their gods are Crom and his dark race, who rule over a sunless place of everlasting mist, which is the world of the dead. Mitra! The ways of the Aesir were more to my liking.\'</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThe Cimmerians are a hearty people, and they make their meals equally hearty when they can afford to. But Cimmerians are also a grim people, and things such as spice and flavor rarely touch their tongues.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52565_ShortDesc", "Plated boots of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52565_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The firelight gleamed redly on his steel mail, on his baleful eyes. They burned in the firelight like the eyes of a wolf.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These plated boots are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52563_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52563_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">But Conan's thews were iron too, and his mail saved him from the gnashing fangs and ripping claws long enough for him to drive home his dagger, again and again and again.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These heavy gauntlets are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_ShortDesc", "A helmet of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This heavy helmet is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52562_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52562_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A gray sky arched overhead, and a moaning wind was chill with a promise of winter. Brown leaves fluttered slowly down from the bare branches, sifting upon his mailed shoulders.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This pauldron is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52564_ShortDesc", "Heavy leg armor of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52564_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The great frame under the mail mesh was too hard and supple for a civilized man; the elemental fire of the primitive burned in those smoldering eyes.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This leg armor is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11106_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting circlets from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11106_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make circlets from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11072_ShortDesc", "The claws of some unfortunate beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11072_LongDesc", "These claws were harvested from the limbs of some poor creature. Hopefully it was dead, otherwise, somewhere out there in the wilderness there is a panther struggling frantically to maintain its grip on a tree, a bear casually slapping a deer on the rump or a very confused pack of wolves sliding across an icy lake.\n\nClaws can be ground into bone meal or affixed to arrows.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18226_ShortDesc", "Smells sharp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18226_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It is not against men I must shield you. There are dark worlds barely guessed by man, wherein formless monsters stalk - fiends which may be drawn from the Outer Voids to take material shape and rend and devour at the bidding of evil magicians.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nIt is said that the long-dead sage Epemitreus devised a modest brew, by steeping a very particular mix of herbs and ingredients in boiling water, that could cleanse a small amount of the corrupting influence of the Outer Dark from one\'s mind and body.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52295_ShortDesc", "Studded boots for climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52295_LongDesc", "As civilization sweeps across the barbaric nations of the world it brings comfort, security and occasionally, peace. But in such times, men forget the skills that they once had.

The ability to climb, for example, to find purchase on the steepest slopes and cling by the fingernails to the smallest of outcrops. To traverse the world using no more than the power of muscle and grit.

The barbaric Cimmerians and tribes of Afghul are known among the civilized nations for their near miraculous climbing ability. As any inhabitant of the Exiled Lands will tell you, there is no miracle here. Just the iron will to survive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_ShortDesc", "Rough gloves suited for climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His groping hands and feet found niches and knobs, precarious holds at best, and sometimes he virtually hung by his finger nails. Yet upward he went, clawing, squirming, fighting for every foot.</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

As civilization sweeps across the barbaric nations of the world it brings comfort, security and occasionally, peace. But in such times, men forget the skills that they once had.

The ability to climb, for example, to find purchase on the steepest slopes and cling by the fingernails to the smallest of outcrops. To traverse the world using no more than the power of muscle and grit.

The barbaric Cimmerians and tribes of Afghul are known among the civilized nations for their near miraculous climbing ability. As any inhabitant of the Exiled Lands will tell you, there is no miracle here. Just the iron will to survive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11011_ShortDesc", "The glowing heart of the forge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11011_LongDesc", "Coal is a versatile, long lasting fuel. Serious smithing requires a supply of coal to reach the high temperatures for smelting workable metals.
Coal is required for the process of transforming iron into the steel.
Harlots and nobles often use charcoal to whiten their teeth and healers often keep a small supply handy as a simple remedy for stomach ailments.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_ShortDesc", "Footwraps woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_LongDesc", "The soles of these footwraps offer very poor protection from the sharp-edged stones that litter the ground of the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_ShortDesc", "Handwraps woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_LongDesc", "Digging in the gritty soil of the Exiled Lands and tearing up plants by their roots without protection is dirty, infection-prone work. \nThese handwraps provide some protection from the elements and physical attacks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_ShortDesc", "Leggings woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_LongDesc", "In the Hyborian age, nudity is a part of life. In warm climates, men and women go bare chested and wear flimsy clothing, slaves are clothed in whatever tatters they can find and children run naked in the streets.\nClothing, however, is a practical bulwark against the elements. And these leggings, coarse as they may be, can protect some very sensitive areas from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_ShortDesc", "A tunic woven from fibrous plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_LongDesc", "When the sand whips and swirls in the wind, abrading everything in its path, even the smallest amount of protection is appreciated.\nThis tunic provides little protection from sword or fang, but it does provide slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14193_ShortDesc", "A small insect with brightly colored innards")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14193_LongDesc", "These small insects live and feed on cacti. They can be prepared into a bright red dye for use in coloring textiles. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11075_ShortDesc", "A mold for minting perfectly rounded coins ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11075_LongDesc", "Minting a currency is a crime punishable by death in almost all of the kingdoms of the Hyborian age. Kings are loathe to give up the power to regulate the currency of the kingdoms.\n\nThere was one attempt, years past, to make an independent currency built around the principles of free exchange and free markets. Unfortunately, the necromancer who invented the idea was executed before it could take root and his crypt-o-currency was forgotten.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80263_ShortDesc", "Wooden chair with backrest and armrests")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80263_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11076_ShortDesc", "A handful of decomposed organic matter")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11076_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?

Carrying around piles of stinking decomposing matter, however, is probably not the most exciting part of farming. 

This compost can be used in planters to encourage planted seeds to grow strong and healthy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18519_ShortDesc", "A smelly pile of rotting matter")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18519_LongDesc", "Ask not a man what goes into his compost heap. That is his business alone. It is what a man removes from his compost heap that matters.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13600_ShortDesc", "The cooked flesh of the abysmal remnant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13600_LongDesc", "This foul-smelling, acidic meat does not look or smell appetizing even after being cooked. Considering the creature that it came from, and the environment where it was found, consuming this would be a foolhardy endeavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18257_ShortDesc", "Eggs sizzling hot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18257_LongDesc", "Eggs make for a fine, storable food, given by nature in their own containers. Cracked open, eggs cook quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18202_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18202_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18205_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18205_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18285_ShortDesc", "A cooked haunch of exquisite meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18285_LongDesc", "A cooked haunch of the best meat these lands have to offer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18200_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18200_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13053_ShortDesc", "Flesh torn from other humans")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13053_LongDesc", "Consuming the flesh of men is a mark of savagery and desperation. Various demonic religious practices encourage ritual consumption while some tribes in the Black Kingdoms devour pieces of their fallen enemies in order to absorb their prowess and courage.\nThe desert men of Darfar are well known for their cannibalism. With their teeth filed to points and bizarre hairstyles of mud and twigs they are an intimidating sight - more so with the blood of a fresh kill drying on their chins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18220_ShortDesc", "Oysters served hot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18220_LongDesc", "The fruit of the shell, the bounty of the sea, cooked and safe for consumption. Oysters have a way of becoming a delicacy to most any culture that rests on the water\'s edge.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18280_ShortDesc", "A calorie-filled dinner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18280_LongDesc", "Only the heartiest meals can prepare one for the savage world.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18277_ShortDesc", "Delicious!")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18277_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18278_ShortDesc", "Scraps of wild boar flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18278_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18201_ShortDesc", "Steaming bowl of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18201_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It takes an Argossean merchant to wring wealth out of a little waterfront shop that stank of rotten fish and cheap wine.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe bounty of the rivers and seas are a major food source for many peoples in Hyboria. Such fare may be prepared by roasting, boiling, and many other methods besides.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18204_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18204_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18203_ShortDesc", "An assortment of shellfish, hot and prepared")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18203_LongDesc", "Shellfish comprise a large category of varied and tasty fare. Such meaty bounty can be plucked right from the waters, but cooking reduces the risk of sickness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11500_ShortDesc", "A chunk of stone pulsing with corruption")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11500_LongDesc", "Thousands of years of sorcerous rituals have left their essence embedded deeply in this stone. It seethes with dark intent - but perhaps that can be useful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18215_ShortDesc", "A foreboding liquid of acrid yet sweet aroma")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18215_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Even the arts you call sorcery are governed by cosmic laws.</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nFoul ingredients are brewed together to make this forbidden drink which corrupts body and soul. Sorcerers covet this libation, for they know that it nourishes a certain, long atrophied organ of the human soul, stimulating it to open like a nocturnal flower and become sensitive to the vibrations and blasphemies of the Outer Dark.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11124_ShortDesc", "A blossom plucked from the crimson lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11124_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nWhat special properties does it have? It will take an avid (or foolhardy) alchemist to find out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11125_ShortDesc", "A small bag of crimson lotus powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11125_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nWhat effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11126_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the crimson lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11126_LongDesc", "There are many varieties of lotus in the world, but the Exiled Lands seems to bring forth a few unique varieties. The Crimson Lotus grows on the site of ancient battlefields - it seems to thrive in soil that has been soaked in blood.\n\nThese seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82011_ShortDesc", "The head of a Crocodile")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82011_LongDesc", "The head of a Crocodile")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81012_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Crocodile head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81012_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18308_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a crocodile")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18308_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to crocodiles, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51451_ShortDesc", "A mechanical bow with a slow rate of fire")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51451_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

Until the invention of the crossbow, those kingdoms who had no cultural relationship with archery were at a disadvantage in battle. However, the creation of this mechanically loaded bow erased that advantage.

Using a bolt locking mechanism, this crossbow can be used by even the most unskilled peasants to make a decisive difference in battle. When loaded with the correct type of bolts, it has a long and accurate range. However, a skilled archer will always be able to fire arrows faster with a longbow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80763_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying crossed weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80763_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90289_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90289_LongDesc", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18520_ShortDesc", "A crude planter for slowly growing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18520_LongDesc", "When man discovered the secrets of agriculture, the world changed. No longer roving bands of battling tribes, the first villages and cities formed around the idea that going out hunting food was a lot harder than just growing it safely behind walls.\n\nThis planter is very crude, and seeds sown in it will grow slowly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80645_ShortDesc", "A roughly shaped wooden bowl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80645_LongDesc", "This crude bowl could have been made in any land, by any maker. It bears no distinguishing markers beyond its ability to hold liquid.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11051_ShortDesc", "Transparent, shimmering stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11051_LongDesc", "Brittle, impossible to work with conventional tools, crystal is mostly used for focusing light and creating rudimentary lenses.\nThe Black Seers of Mount Yimsha craft great lenses to aid in their astrological divinations. Black sorceries gain potency when the heavens are in certain configurations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80743_ShortDesc", "A shelved piece of furniture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80743_LongDesc", "Often made of wood and featuring shelves and doors, cupboards are places to stow dishware or even display certain ornaments or property.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17114_ShortDesc", "A flask of cursed green dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17114_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_ShortDesc", "A slashing weapon favoured by pirates")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> At this kind of fighting the freebooters of the sea were at their stoutest; their arrows and bolts tore holes in the charging horde, their cutlasses hewed the wild men from the palisades they strove to scale.</> - The Black Stranger

Favoured by sailors from the Western ocean to the Vilayet, the cutlass is a short, curved sword capable of hacking through ropes, canvas, wood, and flesh.

Forged of cheap iron, cutlasses are usually splotched with rust due to their time spent near salt water.  This cutlass does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17030_ShortDesc", "A flask of cyan dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17030_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11118_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11118_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51539_ShortDesc", "A pair of inscribed stone daggers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51539_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">What is time to us? We stand outside. All things have happened. All things are happening.</> - Unknown

These daggers appear to have been created by a madman and inscribed a language unknown to men. Only an oracle, high on the fumes of yellow lotus, claims to have been able to read the text inscribed on them. It reads In the cradle of the Nameless Days, the leopard of the smoking mirror shall eat the moon and sun. There is no beginning. There is no end. Invisible mouths devoured them, from either side, as a prelude to a hideous kiss. You will see them in time.

Light attacks with these daggers seem to take no effort, but heavy attacks seem to weary the wielder even more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51954_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51954_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">What is time to us? We stand outside. All things have happened. All things are happening.</> - Unknown\n\nThese daggers appear to have been created by a madman, and inscribed with words that make no sense in a language unknown to men. Only an oracle, high on the fumes of yellow lotus, claims to have been able to read the text inscribed on the dagger. It reads \"In the cradle of the Nameless Days, the leopard of the smoking mirror shall eat the moon and sun. There is no beginning. There is no end. Invisible mouths devoured them, from either side, as a prelude to a hideous kiss. You will see them in time.\"")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_ShortDesc", "A primitive axe, shaped by crude materials and bone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nBone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80734_ShortDesc", "A primitive banner in the style of the Darfari")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80734_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common Darfari patterns.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80735_ShortDesc", "A primitive banner in the style of the Darfari")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80735_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common Darfari patterns.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80736_ShortDesc", "A primitive banner in the style of the Darfari")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80736_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common Darfari patterns.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80740_ShortDesc", "A primitive banner in the style of the Darfari")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80740_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common Darfari patterns.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18234_ShortDesc", "Full of things with no legs or too many legs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18234_LongDesc", "The tribes of Darfar know how to find hidden sustenance. Certain grubs and meaty insects, combined with certain herbs, make for a surprisingly refreshing soup. Served cold, this dish moderately cools the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80215_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80215_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_ShortDesc", "A cudgel of Darfari make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52073_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52073_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91017_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91017_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52072_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52072_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52075_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:

These greaves are simple and adorned with small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52076_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52076_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the speaker mask is said to allow the wearer to communicate with the dead.\nDarfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.\nBut in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can command the dead and communicate with Yog directly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_ShortDesc", "A tooth-edged sword of bone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nA mark of the Darfari wish to emulate more advanced cultures, this \"sword\" is more like a flat plank embedded with the teeth of various animals. It swings like a plank as well, so while it may not have the lethality of a well whetted blade, it will still leave a nasty mark on anything it managed to hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52071_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52071_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91015_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91015_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80753_ShortDesc", "Wind chimes crafted of human bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80753_LongDesc", "The cannibal tribes of Darfar have developed a unique mechanism to warn them against the sandstorms that occasionally sweep through their lands. These wind chimes, made from the bones of humans, begin to chime when the wind picks up. If a sandstorm is coming, the noise of the chimes becomes impossible to ignore.\nWhen the wind moves sluggishly through the Darfari camps, however, the chimes create an eerie, ghostly music. Perhaps this unsettling tune contributes to the unsettling reputation of the Darfari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17101_ShortDesc", "A flask of dark ash dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17101_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17001_ShortDesc", "A darkening agent for dyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17001_LongDesc", "When this dark substance is added to a dye, it darkens it to produce a shade that is darker than the original dye, without changing the color.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17062_ShortDesc", "A flask of dark green dye ")
