column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14175_ShortDesc", "Taken from the tresses of dead women")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14175_LongDesc", "In Zamoria, there was a city ruled by a sorcerer named Yara in his fabulous dwelling known only as the Tower of the Elephant. Yara had a dark reputation, but he was also rumored to be the keeper of a wonderful treasure known only as the Heart of the Elephant.\nNobody knows precisely what happened to Yara, but his tower collapsed into rubble and among the rubble was found a coil of rope woven from hair. Though none knew its purpose, many speculated that the hair for the rope was taken from dead women, in accordance with a ritual found in the dread Book of Skelos, which would make it incredibly strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51072_ShortDesc", "An unholy relic, forged using with the black heart of the Kinscourge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51072_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This ancient axe pulses with blasphemous power.

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80312_ShortDesc", "A finely woven bowl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80312_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'A shell-shaped bowl of gold on a black altar in a deep cavern,\' Conan muttered, frowning as he sought to capture the illusive image.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBowls are no rare thing among the tools of man - made from clay and metal and carved wood. Some bowls are given a more decorative touch, made from finer materials with artistic flourishes - a show of an artisan\'s skill, the indulgence of the wealthy, or the reverence of a sorcerer or priest who puts the receptacle to mystical purpose.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80332_LongDesc", "This planter is merely for decoration and can be used to ornament the home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82022_ShortDesc", "The head of a Deer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82022_LongDesc", "The head of a Deer")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82021_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Deer head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82021_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I've hunted deer all my life on the Tauran.'</> - Beyond the Black River

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved deer's head bespeaks of one swift enough to catch food from the land.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14182_ShortDesc", "Black liquid that reeks of the outer dark")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14182_LongDesc", "This black ooze, harvested from the corpse of a demonic entity, steams slightly when exposed to air.
Blood is used to increase the potency of the blasphemous rituals of both priests and sorcerers. And this is particularly potent blood.
The nature of demons is hotly disputed by scholars. Some suggest that they are simply remnants of elder races that stalked the earth before mankind, while others insist that they are formless creatures from the outer void given form by the incantation of vile sorceries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18245_ShortDesc", "Links of blackened meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18245_LongDesc", "The blood and flesh of demons are not only components to the profane rituals of sorcerers... but also the culinary arts of the adventurous. These links of cooked meat seem to pulse with eldritch life and eating such fare bestows strong recuperative powers, over time, to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82054_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Demonic Spider head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82054_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_ShortDesc", "Ammunition for the trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They pushed on grimly, over soil charred and blackened, where the naked rock had in places been turned to lava by the explosion of those diabolical bombs.</> - People of the Black Circle

Using similar ingredients to those found in Kothic Demon-fire, this explosive barrage is designed to melt the very stones that it explodes upon, slowly burning all caught in its wrath.

It is expensive to create, however, and those who use it in battle earn a reputation for ruthlessness and unusual cruelty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51971_ShortDesc", "A glass orb that shimmers with fire")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51971_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'His hand dipped into his robe and came out with something shining-a glistening sphere. This he threw suddenly at Conan. The Cimmerian contemptuously struck it aside with his sword-at the instant of contact there was a sharp explosion, a flare of white, blinding flame, and Conan pitched senseless to the ground.'</> - The Hour of the Dragon

While there are always rumors of sorcerers who summon fire from the skies and cause the earth to revolt against their foes, this orb is simply a concoction created from mixing fluids together.

To the credulous and superstitious, it appears to be sorcery. But to the educated it is simply an alchemical curiosity, able to set a burning fire on whatever surface it impacts.

It can also be used in combination with grease to create a larger fire effect.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82015_LongDesc", "The head of a Demonic Shaleback")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51998_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Acolytes of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51998_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That's what the black people of Kush call the Apples of Derketa. Derketa is the Queen of the Dead. Drink a little of that juice, or spill it on your flesh, and you'd be dead before you could tumble to the foot of this crag.</> - Red Nails

Derketo was originally worshipped in Shem, but was quickly adopted in Stygia and the Black Kingdoms further south.

The dual nature of Derketo is death and fertility, and as such she is often paired with the most powerful deity of the kingdom she is associated with. Derketo is the consort of Set in Stygia, but the companion of Dagon in Zembabwei. In Kush she is Derketa, Queen of the Dead, and there, she walks alone.

This ceremonial armor is designed to awe and seduce in equal measure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52115_ShortDesc", "Anklets worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52115_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

These anklets jingle with every movement of the wearer - every provocative hip-thrust and sinuous flick of the ankle produces a golden note.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_ShortDesc", "A blouse worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This loose-fitting blouse is designed to accentuate rather than conceal, to titillate rather than reveal. Dancers of Derketo are aware that lust, like fear, is one of the most powerful motivators of human kind.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_ShortDesc", "Bracelets worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

These bracelets jingle with every movement of the wearer - every provocative chest shake and sinuous coil of the wrist produces a golden note.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_ShortDesc", "A headdress worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This headdress signifies the status of the wearer as a dancer in the service of Derketo.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_ShortDesc", "A skirt worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

Half-transparent, this skirt presents those who watch the dancers of Derketo with shadowy outlines of the flesh that lies beneath. A stirring in the blood that sets the heart to racing - and matches the step of the dancers in full flight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51456_ShortDesc", "A tool for extracting unfulfilled desires")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51456_LongDesc", "Derketo teaches that when a person dies their unfulfilled desires manifest within their bodies. The worshippers of Derketo have created this tool for extracting that...remnant from those who die while under their ministrations.\n\nJust don\'t look too closely at what it pulls out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18006_ShortDesc", "Small, blue berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18006_LongDesc", "Growing in the dry wastes of the desert, these blue berries are used in the making of juice and wine. They can be eaten, though they do not offer much nourishment. Still, any sustenance is precious out in the desolate lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18033_ShortDesc", "Blue berry pulp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18033_LongDesc", "This blue-colored pulp, squeezed from desert berries, can be used to make wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11094_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11094_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18080_ShortDesc", "A particularly thirst-quenching wine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18080_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Wine!\' gasped the king from the couch where they had laid him. They put a goblet to his bloody lips and he drank like a man half dead of thirst.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nA light-colored wine, popular in Turan, known to ease a throat that has taken in the dust of the desert roads. It cools the tongue more than the average vintage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13550_ShortDesc", "The crushed bones and marrow of an otherworldly creature.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13550_LongDesc", "Taken from a dark creature summoned from the outer void, this ground up hunk of disgusting matter glows with an otherworldy energy.\nIt\'s probably useful for something, but eating it should be a last resort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15507_ShortDesc", "An ornate diadem worn by the Giant-kings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15507_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Kallian Publico believed that it contained the diadem of the giant-kings, of the people who dwelt in that dark land before the ancestors of the Stygians came there. He showed me a design carved on the lid, which he swore was the shape of the diadem which legend tells us the monster-kings wore.</> - Rogues in the House

Long- Too large to be worn by a human, this diadem hums with contained power. Taken from the Priestking of the Giant-kings - known today as the Barrow King - the story of the diadem is one of betrayal and hatred.

It seems that the Priestking was the father of Tyros the Deathbringer. Tyros turned against his father at some point during the war between the Lemurians and the Giant-kings and his father cursed him, and all of his loyal warriors.

Such is the strength of the diadem, that Tyros and his men were cursed to live forever, a Silent Legion brooding in the ruins of the north.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90305_ShortDesc", "A diagonal wooden support beam")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90305_LongDesc", "Support beams offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82033_ShortDesc", "The head of a Dire Wolf")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82033_LongDesc", "The head of a Dire Wolf")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82032_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Dire Wolf head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82032_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80737_ShortDesc", "A patterened banner in the fashion of the Dogs of the Desert")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80737_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with the signature motif of the Dogs of the Desert.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80104_ShortDesc", "A comfortable, double sized bed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80104_LongDesc", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. They consider it an important part of civilization and sneer at those who sleep on the ground as uncouth savages.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18309_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a dragon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18309_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to dragons, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10022_ShortDesc", "Bones taken from a dragon raised to life through terrible ritual")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10022_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

Through their arts, the Giant-kings resurrected dragons from the bones that they could find. They kept them as pets and bred them for battle in their gladiatorial games. 

Their bones are particularly strong and can be worked into powerful weapons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54004_ShortDesc", "Arrows crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54004_LongDesc", "Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

These arrows are strong, durable and sharp. Being crafted from the bones of a dragon also gives them a certain prestige - like beating a rich merchant to death with a sack of gold coins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54003_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54003_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51991_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51991_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10023_ShortDesc", "Horn taken from a dragon raised to life through terrible ritual")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10023_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.

Through their arts, the Giant-kings resurrected dragons from the bones that they could find. They kept them as pets and bred them for battle in their gladiatorial games. 

Their horns are particularly strong and can be worked into powerful weapons.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14183_ShortDesc", "A volatile powder created by mashing various alchemical components")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14183_LongDesc", "Alchemists in the west first discovered this wondrous powder through a crumbling manuscript that came with a caravan from Khitai. \nThrough much experimentation and loss of limb and life, they eventually stablized the formula with localized ingredients. Combined with other ingredients, Dragonpowder becomes a potent explosive - though many see it as a form of sorcery and refuse to use it in battle.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows or denies access to a gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90224_LongDesc", "Connected to a gate, the drawbridge is designed as a defensive measure, denying approaching enemies easy access to the gate. The drawbridge is operated by a lever.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18258_ShortDesc", "A handful of dried berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18258_LongDesc", "These berries have been dried to preserve them. They do not offer much nourishment, but will resist decay for a time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18013_ShortDesc", "Preserved fish flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18013_LongDesc", "Salting and drying are among man\'s earliest means of preserving food. This fish flesh will resist decay for a while.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18014_ShortDesc", "Preserved animal flesh")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18014_LongDesc", "Salting and drying are among man\'s earliest means of preserving food. This animal flesh will resist decay for a while.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80760_ShortDesc", "A decorative drinking horn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80760_LongDesc", "Usually drinking horns are hollowed out and filled with liquid, but the crafter of this particular horn was lazy, so it is just for show. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51830_ShortDesc", "A drum stretched with animal skin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51830_LongDesc", "A tool specifically designed to enhance the user-experience of slaving away as a thrall. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80754_ShortDesc", "A drum crafted in Darfari style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80754_LongDesc", "When the throbbing of the drums begins in the darkness that covers the Exiled Lands, men and women hide in terror. Around their firepits, the devotees of Yog are preparing for a hunt.\nThe cannibalistic rituals of the Darfari are always accompanied by the beating of these skin-covered drums. A wise man does not look too closely at the pale leather that covers the drums, nor question where it was obtained. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51832_ShortDesc", "A razor sharp tool for scraping hides")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51832_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">But a bat has flown over the Mountains of the Dead and drawn your image in blood on the white tiger\'s hide that hangs before the long hut where sleep the Four Brothers of the Night.</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nBefore preparation, hides must be scraped to remove excess fibres and clots of skin. The best hide scrapers are sharp, easy to weild and leave a smooth line of transition so that it is easy to see which part of the hide still requires treatment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18025_ShortDesc", "Baked wood ready to burn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18025_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the forest-covered hills of the northwest exist wandering bands of ape-men, without human speech, or the knowledge of fire or the use of implements.</> - The Hyborian Age\n\nFire protected mankind from feral predators and took them one more rung up the ladder of savagery and civilization. Humanity ever looks for ways to build a better fire. These kiln-baked pieces of wood are better fuel for a superior fire.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18506_ShortDesc", "Special rack for drying")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18506_LongDesc", "With some ingenuity, a specialized rack, oven or kiln might be used to dry certain materials. Drying meat can help to preserve it. Dried wood makes for a much better fire.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51534_ShortDesc", "A long, pointed blade suited for dueling")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51534_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Framed in his steel morion his face was dark, saturnine and hawk-like, wherefore men called him the Hawk. His armor and garments were rich and ornate, after the fashion of a Zingaran grandee. His hand was never far from his sword-hilt.</> - Pool of the Black One

Zaporavo, known as the Hawk, was a nobleman in Zingara known for his dueling prowess, defeating all of the champions of Kordava to become to premiere swordsman in the kingdom.

However, due to his pride, Zaporavo was unable to allow himself to lose. During a bout with the King of Zingara, where tradition demands that the king be allowed to win, Zaporavo drew first blood. 

The king was furious and Zaporavo was exiled. He cast his dueling blade from the docks of Kordava, and then left the city forever, becoming the Captain of the Wastrel and a terror to those who sailed the Zingaran coastline.

It is not known how the sword came to the Exiled Lands, but the wielder is blessed with great agility, as if the Hawk himself were watching them with dark, brooding eyes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11107_ShortDesc", "A mold for casting earrings from precious metals ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11107_LongDesc", "Jewelry is considered a sign of status and wealth. This holds true from the most primitive tribes to the most civilized. One need only glance at a Shemite merchant, arms and legs covered in golden trinkets, to understand the power that jewelry conveys.\n\nThis simple mold can be used to make earrings from precious metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80651_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80651_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13011_ShortDesc", "A large nutritious meal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13011_LongDesc", "Many eggs, amongst others the Shaleback eggs, are considered a rare delicacy in the civilized lands. Anybody who has seen an enraged adult Shaleback up close can understand why they remain so.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18256_ShortDesc", "A delicious looking egg...")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18256_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">From the deep gash flowed a strange ichor, and Khosatral cried out like the dirging of a great bell.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nThese innocent-looking eggs hide a gleeful treachery. Within the obfuscation of the shell there resides a blasphemous gush of ichor. Some sadistic nobles relish springing such a surprise on their guests, savoring the looks on their masticating faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11059_ShortDesc", "Where?")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11059_LongDesc", "Where elephant hide? Me not see elephant hiding here? You silly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18310_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw an elephant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18310_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling organic material bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to elephants, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows horizontal travel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90226_LongDesc", "The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.\n\nThe practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a horde of barbarians following a rope hand over hand can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_ShortDesc", "A mechanism that allows vertical travel without climbing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90225_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Then, looping the loose end of his silk rope about Natala's hips, and cautioning her to hold on with both hands, he lifted her through the window and lowered her the thirty-odd feet to the earth.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The mechanics of creating such a machine - involving counter-weights, pulleys and other fine details - are considered sorcery by the ignorant and wisdom by the enlightened.

The practical benefits of such a machine cannot be denied, but civilized peoples who grow too reliant upon them will find that a climbing horde of barbarians can be just as effective, and infinitely more deadly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18295_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases grit")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18295_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir fills the imbiber with unflinching optimism. This means that they become absolutely certain that they can succeed in their endeavor and they will endure anything to get their task done. Which is useful - right up until they pass out from exhaustion.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18304_ShortDesc", "A concoction that frees the imbiber ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18304_LongDesc", "The priests and priestesses of Derketo have often had to deal with penitents who were too reserved or too unwilling to participate in the orgiastic ceremonies of the goddess.\n\nThis potion adds a spring to their step while freeing their mind of any... moral impediments. The practical effect is that any who drink this cannot be stopped, by physical or mental means.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18290_ShortDesc", "A concoction that temporarily increases agility")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18290_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThe imbiber of this elixir becomes more graceful, seemingly able to dance among the attacks of their enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18298_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases survivability")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18298_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.

This elixir seems to have a digestive effect on the drinker, allowing them to quickly process foods and other concoctions taken through the mouth.

Ironically, perhaps, this elixir is most often taken by apothecaries (or their servants) when they are about to test a new concoction.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18297_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18297_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir allows an imbiber to push their muscles beyond their normal limits. For a limited period of time, they can perform feats of immense strength proportionate to their original strength, of course. It is said that Zamorian street performers drink this potion to increase their strength during performances.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18292_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases encumbrance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18292_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir is often given to slaves to numb their senses to the heavy loads that their masters pile upon them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18289_ShortDesc", "A concoction that temporarily increases accuracy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18289_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir seems to give a boost to eyesight, useful for archers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18299_ShortDesc", "A concoction that increases survivability")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18299_LongDesc", "Brewing elixirs is a dangerous, often fatal pursuit. The wrong combination of ingredients is poisonous, or worse. The larger problem, however, is that apothecaries are loathe to share their secrets with one another, for fear of losing their business advantage. Which means that each and every practitioner has their own specific set of recipes for creating a desired effect.\n\nThis elixir provides the drinker with a feeling of robust health. Wounds seem to matter less under the influence of this potion, which is either a blessing or a curse depending on the scenario.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82035_ShortDesc", "The head of an Elk")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82035_LongDesc", "The head of an Elk")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82018_ShortDesc", "The head of an Elk King")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82018_LongDesc", "The head of an Elk King")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82036_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Elk King head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82036_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'On they fled, the hunted and the hunter, and not a foot could the black stallion gain, though he strained each nerve and thew.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This massive, preserved head marks the hunter who brought down the Elk King.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82034_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Elk head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82034_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'On they fled, the hunted and the hunter, and not a foot could the black stallion gain, though he strained each nerve and thew.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved elk's head bespeaks an ability to bring down quarry both powerful and fleet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51532_ShortDesc", "A sword of blackest ebony")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51532_LongDesc", "The origins of this blade are mysteriously absent from any record. Those who have possessed it over the years claim that it fills them with a nameless hunger for blood.

Once the sword was taken to oracle who named it a dark spirit that crosses between worlds and time endlessly, in search of shattered men in shattered lands who will let it drink.

This sword seems to drain additional life from the enemy with every hit, soaking it into the very surface of the sword.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18225_ShortDesc", "It is gruel, but it actually smells good")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18225_LongDesc", "Sometimes one is able to find a few extra things to throw into the gruel, to make it a more satisfying meal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15513_ShortDesc", "A black essence left by the Servant of the Ring")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15513_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Set, mine enemy knew not the hour when he might awake at midnight to feel the taloned fingers of a nameless horror at his throat! I did dark and terrible magic with the Serpent Ring of Set, which I found in a nighted tomb a league beneath the earth, forgotten before the first man crawled out of the slimy sea.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

Thoth Amon of the Black Ring is the man who created the Exiled Lands.

During one of his journeys seeking sorcerous knowledge, he stumbled upon the Unnamed City and, befriending the lone survivor, Warmaker Klael, he soon learned of the powerful artefacts contained beneath the city.

Exploring the ruins, he found the Serpent Ring of Set, and the slave bracelets of the Giant-kings. In his twisted mind, a plan began to form.
A deal was struck with King Cstephon of Stygia. Thoth Amon would provide the bracelets and a place where the political and ideological enemies of the king could be exiled forever (but kept alive as a contingency for the future) and in return, King Cstephon would provide troops to occasionally ride through the Exiled Lands and collect any artefacts that the poor unfortunates had obtained.

This then was the founding of the Exiled Lands and the Purge, though over the years the deal has altered and Thoth Amon has extended his offer to other rulers across the world (without the knowledge of King Cstephon, naturally).

Thoth Amon has moved further and further from the concerns of the  worldly - he no longer deals personally with the affairs of the Exiled Lands. Instead, he sends his enforcer, the Servant of the Ring to deal with any major problems.

This essence, taken from the Servant of the Ring, hopefully contains enough of the dark sorcery to complete the ritual to create the keystone, that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30014_ShortDesc", "A note etched into a block of wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30014_LongDesc", "By the gods, they're going to eat me! The drums are beating in frenzied rhythm and the Darfari savages 
are dancing around a pit of swirling flames.
I've seen what happens to those who are cast into the pit - the screams as the searing heat consumes 
them.
If you are, like me, a captive of these devils then I can offer no comfort. But if you are a free man and 
can read these words then I would ask a boon of you: Salaceo of the Black Hand pretended to be my 
friend and then traded me to these savages for animal hides.
He needed my skills as a scribe to write down directions to the place where he keeps his treasures, lest 
he forget the path. But then because of my knowledge of his hiding place, he sold me to the Darfari.
But I prepared for this eventuality. I wrote his instructions down incorrectly. If you find him, kill him. Do 
not offer quarter or mercy. Take his instructions, by way of thanks.
But remember that for every step I wrote, I took two.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80978_ShortDesc", "A place of sacrifice to Ymir, the Frost Giant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80978_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The clangor of the swords had died away, the shouting of the slaughter was hushed; silence lay on the red-stained snow. The bleak pale sun that glittered so blindingly from the ice-fields and the snow-covered plains struck sheens of silver from rent corselet and broken blade, where the dead lay as they had fallen. The nerveless hand yet gripped the broken hilt; helmeted heads back-drawn in the death-throes, tilted red beards and golden beards grimly upward, as if in last invocation to Ymir the frost-giant, god of a warrior-race...</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said that the battlefield is truly Ymir\'s altar. The war god does not want murdered sacrifices so much as beautiful deaths during the din of glorious combat. Yet those most devoted to the Lord of Storm and War still find themselves constructing places where they can directly commune with their god through the medium of spilt blood. On the cold winds of deadly winter, one might hear the grinding whisper of the Father of Giants saying, \'You get what you give.\'")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51980_ShortDesc", "A vicious sword made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51980_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52637_ShortDesc", "A set of gauntlets favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52637_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51193_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51193_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51498_ShortDesc", "A shield of hardened carapace")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51498_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is crafted from the hardened carapace of one of the insectoid creatures that roams the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable - but not as effective as a shield made of metal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51178_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed steel axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51178_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52585_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52585_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These reinforced boots of leather and fur keep one's feet both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52580_ShortDesc", "Plated boots of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52580_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The firelight gleamed redly on his steel mail, on his baleful eyes. They burned in the firelight like the eyes of a wolf.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These plated boots are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52578_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52578_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">But Conan's thews were iron too, and his mail saved him from the gnashing fangs and ripping claws long enough for him to drive home his dagger, again and again and again.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These heavy gauntlets are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52576_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51452_ShortDesc", "A mechanical bow with a slow rate of fire")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51452_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

Until the invention of the crossbow, those kingdoms who had no cultural relationship with archery were at a disadvantage in battle. However, the creation of this mechanically loaded bow erased that advantage.

Using a bolt locking mechanism, this crossbow can be used by even the most unskilled peasants to make a decisive difference in battle. When loaded with the correct type of bolts, it has a long and accurate range. However, a skilled archer will always be able to fire arrows faster with a longbow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51823_ShortDesc", "A slashing weapon favoured by pirates")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51823_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> At this kind of fighting the freebooters of the sea were at their stoutest; their arrows and bolts tore holes in the charging horde, their cutlasses hewed the wild men from the palisades they strove to scale.</> - The Black Stranger

Favoured by sailors from the Western ocean to the Vilayet, the cutlass is a short, curved sword capable of hacking through ropes, canvas, wood, and flesh.

Forged of cheap iron, cutlasses are usually splotched with rust due to their time spent near salt water. This cutlass does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52097_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52097_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52095_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52095_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91110_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91110_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51176_ShortDesc", "A curved sword with a single sharp edge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51176_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A man on a giant horse whirled, slashed and smote apparently at thin air, and from another direction swept a wild horde of riders, their curved swords flashing in the moonlight.</> - Drums in Tombalku

Straddling the line between the traditional khopesh of Stygia and broadsword favoured in the northern kingdoms, the falcata is forward curved blade with a single edge on the concave side.

The distinctive hooked hilt helps to prevent the weapon from jarring free of the hands during battle. There is much dispute about the origin of the weapon, considering its similarity to the Argossean kopis and the Stygian khopesh.  This falcata bears no marking which would betray its origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51187_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51187_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51590_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Hardened Steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51590_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51960_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51960_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51061_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel, two-handed sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51061_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this massive sword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51157_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from hardened steel of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51157_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Limp and broken he sagged across the altar, his brains oozing from his crushed skull.</> - The Servants of Bit-Yakin

This fine hammer, shining with the blue of hardened steel, bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51596_ShortDesc", "A javelin of hardened steel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51596_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51079_ShortDesc", "A mace of hardened  steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51079_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At their saddle-bows hung battle-axes or steel maces, and each man wore at his hip a long broadsword.</> - Black Collossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its purpose in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Cimmerian clans often forge weapons such as this for trade - theirs raids against the Vanir and Aesir of the north rarely require them to take down foes in heavy armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51629_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel shield of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51629_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Through a whistling cloud of arrows they plowed to break like a thundering wave on the bristling wall of spears and shields.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This hardened steel shield bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for armor of unusually strong aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51727_ShortDesc", "A spear with a hardened steel head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51727_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The defile was blocked by a wild and terrible band of men who stood silent as images - ragged, shock-headed men with spears in their hands - hundreds of them. And up on the cliffs appeared other faces - thousands of faces - wild, gaunt, ferocious faces, marked by fire and steel and starvation.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this large spear baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

The Cimmerians make large, two-handed spears for maximum reach to hunt the most dangerous game animals. Such weapons are fine to have against more human opponents as well.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51842_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51842_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51933_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51933_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51845_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51845_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51170_ShortDesc", "A steel reinforced crossbow")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51170_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

Until the invention of the crossbow, those kingdoms who had no cultural relationship with archery were at a disadvantage in battle. However, the creation of this mechanically loaded bow erased that advantage.

Using a bolt locking mechanism, this crossbow can be used by even the most unskilled peasants to make a decisive difference in battle. When loaded with the correct type of bolts, it has a long and accurate range. However, a skilled archer will always be able to fire arrows faster with a longbow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52038_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated gauntlets")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52038_LongDesc", "These gauntlets are adorned with overlapping plates of steel, which keeps the main hand protected while allowing full flexibility and mobility in the off-hand. 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91107_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91107_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52036_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52036_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91105_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91105_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52037_ShortDesc", "A heavy vest that offers significant protection")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52037_LongDesc", "Designed with defence in mind, this heavy pauldron is reinforced with overlapping steel plates on the main hand. This offers optimal protection and stability mid-swing, while allowing the wearer room to breathe and remain cool.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91106_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91106_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52040_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52040_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91109_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91109_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52039_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52039_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91108_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91108_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51168_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from a single piece of wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51168_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</> - Song of the Bossonian Archers.

Carved from a single piece of wood, the hunting bow is used across the world and in hundreds of variants.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52546_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52546_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52961_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52961_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91169_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91169_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52953_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52960_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52960_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91165_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52959_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52952_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51403_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted of horn, wood and sinew")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51403_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Kerim Shah had unslung the powerful Turanian bow that killed at five hundred paces, and the Irakzai looked to their own lighter and less lethal bows.</> - The People of the Black Circle

This bow is made in the Hyrkanian style, using different materials to strengthen different areas of the bow and allowing it to be shorter than a longbow. For Hyrkanians, who spend most of their lives shooting from horseback, this is a necessity.

Hyrkanians are widely considered the best archers in the world, raised to the hunt and the art of shooting from horseback. Their bows, however, are not as well made as those of the Shemites, who have spent centuries perfecting the art.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52415_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52415_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These boots are designed to protect the feet from blows during combat from the back of a horse.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52412_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.
