column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91134_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91134_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather boots are practical onboard a ship - for preventing splinters and broken toes, but also for kicking unfortunate prisoners over the side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91132_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91132_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather gloves are practical onboard a ship - for preventing blisters, rope-burn and the occasional knife wound as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91130_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91130_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91133_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91133_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather pants offer the freedom to scamper along lines, while still being stiff enough to turn the sharp edge of a dagger. They also never need to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91131_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91131_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18207_ShortDesc", "A decadent display of choice meats")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18207_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">His life was a series of feasts and wild debauches. He filled his palace with the fairest girls of the kingdom, willing or unwilling. He blasphemed the gods and sprawled drunken on the floor of the banquet hall wearing the golden crown, and staining his royal purple robes with the wine he spilled.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nSome eat merely to survive another savage day. Others, of a sensual bent, create magnificent feasts of the most exotic meats, feasts that would make the gods salivate unto a deluge. Decadence to the point of madness? Perhaps. But there is something to be said for the great boon of health this grants the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18012_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18012_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is taken from one of the exotic species of fish swimming in the waters of the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling catch is a matter for sages to discuss.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13003_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13003_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh is taken from one of the exotic creatures that roam the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling hunt is a matter for sages to discuss.
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18022_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from exotic shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18022_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is taken from one of the exotic species of crustaceans or molluscs dwelling in the waters of the Exiled Lands. The effect of this meat is particularly potent, but whether this boost is due to the rare flavour or is an aftereffect of the thrilling catch is a matter for sages to discuss.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80915_ShortDesc", "An exploding jar that can be buried")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80915_LongDesc", "Originally created in Khitai for use in fireworks, enterprising warriors and merchants soon saw the value of using this explosive powder in warfare.\nOne enterprising Nemedian merchant thought that surrounding his mansion with a ring of explosive jars buried in the earth, their lids rigged with a special trigger, would deter would-be thieves from stealing over his walls. When his favorite hunting hound triggered the trap and knocked down half of the wall around his mansion, the merchant sold the details of the trigger mechanism to a blacksmith and left the estate behind.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_ShortDesc", "An arrow that explodes on impact")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53617_LongDesc", "Only a madman would willingly carry arrows like this into battle. The chance of hitting friends when trying to damage foes, the chance of accidentally ricocheting an arrow back into oneself, and the chance that the arrows will explode in the quiver...
A madman or a berserker, perhaps.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80901_ShortDesc", "A ceramic vase of explosive powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80901_LongDesc", "Originally created in Khitai for use in fireworks, enterprising warriors and merchants soon saw the value of using this explosive powder in warfare.\nThe jars are prepared, filled with the powder and carefully sealed against the air. The very touch of air is enough to ignite the powder yet each jar comes with a fuse that can be lit for a delayed detonation.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18286_ShortDesc", "A choice cut")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18286_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18249_ShortDesc", "Chunks of exotic meat floating in a fine stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18249_LongDesc", "Only the choicest cuts of meat go into this superior stew.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51556_ShortDesc", "A Hyrkanian bow with remarkable accuracy")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51556_LongDesc", "Across the Vilayet, where the blue sea gives way to the steppes, the Hyrkanians live in the saddle from the day that they are born - learning to shoot, fight and eat.

This bow was crafted for the son of a great khan, but the boy was trampled by bulls before he was ten years old and the old khan was left with nothing but the bow in memory of his favored son.

The old khan claimed that the bow would whisper to him with the voice of his son, telling him where to find water and how to avoid enemies. The Khan's other sons saw this as a sign of their father being unfit to rule, and promptly knifed him in the back.

The bow was given away, or lost, or sold. And the son of the khan was forgotten.

This bow, when wielded, conveys increased accuracy. Some have described the sensation as being guided by a pair of steady, gentle hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_ShortDesc", "A crudely-fashioned eye patch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_60001_ShortDesc", "Imp Idol Eye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_60001_LongDesc", "Imp Idol Eye")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13052_ShortDesc", "Eyes taken from a being of pure innocence")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13052_LongDesc", "It is said that all beings are born with light eyes, that darken when the world begins to stain them. These eyes, taken from a creature too young to know the evils of the world, contain a certain amount of power that can be called upon in occult rituals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_ShortDesc", "A curved sword with a single sharp edge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A man on a giant horse whirled, slashed and smote apparently at thin air, and from another direction swept a wild horde of riders, their curved swords flashing in the moonlight.</> - Drums in Tombalku

Straddling the line between the traditional khopesh of Stygia and broadsword favoured in the northern kingdoms, the falcata is forward curved blade with a single edge on the concave side.

The distinctive hooked hilt helps to prevent the weapon from jarring free of the hands during battle. There is much dispute about the origin of the weapon, considering its similarity to the Argossean kopis and the Stygian khopesh.  This falcata bears no marking which would betray its origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14194_ShortDesc", "A bush with small berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14194_LongDesc", "The berries of true mandrake must be taken from the resting place of a dead man by the light of the moon. False mandrake berries are much simpler to harvest and can be used to create a purple dye. \nSome have suggested that the intense blooming of False Mandrake along the banks of the Vilayet during spring is a simple explanation for the fabled purple sails of the Turanian fleet. However, alchemists argue that the purple comes from the properties of the pitch found in the region.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11110_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11110_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18050_ShortDesc", "Large, sharp tooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18050_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The muscles coiling under that gray corpse-like skin were stringy and hard as steel wires, exceeding the strength of a man. But Conan\'s thews were iron too, and his mail saved him from the gnashing fangs and ripping claws long enough for him to drive home his dagger, again and again and again.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThe incisors and large teeth of beasts are often used as adornments by man. Perhaps it is a defiant challenge to the savage world, a reminder that humankind has crawled out of the primordial depths, above the food chain, and their flesh is not for feasting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13012_ShortDesc", "Disgusting, yet filling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13012_LongDesc", "For the strong of stomach, these grubs offer a both food and moisture in the midst of the desert")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18303_ShortDesc", "A holy food served at the orgies of Derketo")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18303_LongDesc", "The rituals of Derketo are often mocked by outsiders who do not understand the pleasures and lusts of the goddess. This feast, however, typifies the food served at the revels and orgies of the goddess. No rich or fatty foods here, no. This meal is designed to titillate and preserve the participants, awakening the tingling warmth of the goddess inside them and giving them the stamina to proceed through the night. \n\nOnly untutored fools think that the men and women who laze around the gauzy temples of Derketo are recovering from a night of strong wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18302_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Jhebbal Sag")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18302_LongDesc", "In honor of the god who hunts, lord of beasts and claws and fangs, this meal is prepared to sate even the most hungry predator.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18222_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Mitra")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18222_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Mitra grant that I do not fail of this mighty trust!</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Mitra. Mitra, chief god of Hyboria! Mitra, the righteous, the father of justice, the enemy of Set! May this meal open a holy and eternal spring in the belly.  May man\'s heart know mercy. Mitra, guard us against the powers of darkness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18218_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18218_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Their ghastly feasts were considered a sacrifice to the scaly god.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Set. Set, the Old Serpent! Set. archenemy Iblis! Set, who is known as Damballah in the Southern kingdoms, whose holy scales blind all with their bright darkness! Set is a jealous god and requires constant sacrifices from his chosen. This meal is devoured as an offering to the Lord of Snakes. May it grow a nest of serpents in the belly of the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18260_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18260_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Tall and fair and blue-eyed. Their god is Ymir, the frost-giant, and each tribe has its own king. They are wayward and fierce. They fight all day and drink ale and roar their wild songs all night.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Ymir. Ymir, the Frost Giant and father of all lesser giants! Ymir, Lord of Storm and War! May he grant the strength to fight all of the day and drink all of the night. May this meal grant a warrior the bravery to die in battle, earning a place in Ymir\'s hall in Valhalla to feast and revel until the end of days.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18212_ShortDesc", "A ritualistic meal in honor of Yog")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18212_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">There were grisly feasts beneath the moon, across whose red disk a bat-like shadow incessantly swept.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThis feast is consumed in the name of Yog. Yog, the Lorde of Empty Abodes! Yog, cousin of them that slither in the immaculate slime of the Elder Night! All good and fearing worshipers of Yog must dedicate themselves to the consumption of only meat. All the faithful of Yog must taste human flesh once a month, lest they become unclean until they again perform this communion of body and blood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11056_ShortDesc", "A soft feather, used in fletching and cushioning")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11056_LongDesc", "Used primarily in the creation of arrows and for stuffing cushions, feathers come in all sizes and colors. Soft, downy feathers plucked from the breast of an animal are the best for cushioning, while stiffer feather taken from the tail of a bird are more useful for keeping arrows true in the air.\n\nThese feathers are taken from the wild birds that roam the Exiled Lands - so ferocious, but oh so delicious as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11060_ShortDesc", "The sleek pelt of a large cat")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11060_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, such as this one taken from a panther, speak to the skill and strength of the hunter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18213_ShortDesc", "Mounds of cooked, feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18213_LongDesc", "A feast of various gamey meats. What such a meal lacks in quality, it makes up for quantity. Gorging on such fare can satisfy the belly and offer a little relief to the injured.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13001_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from small beasts and fowl")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13001_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh is harvested from small animals. It is not particularly filling or flavorful. 
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18504_ShortDesc", "A wooden cask used in fermentation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18504_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The dead are dead, and what has passed is done! I have a ship and a fighting crew and a girl with lips like wine, and that\'s all I ever asked. Lick your wounds, bullies, and break out a cask of ale.</> - The Pool of the Black One\n\nWhat better way to prove to a savage that civilization is good than to wet their fierce tongues with liquor, wine, or ale? The arts of fermentation give humankind the gift of drink and libation. These wooden barrels are the heart of that blessed task.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80112_ShortDesc", "A mattress of leaves, twigs and grass.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80112_LongDesc", "A hastily gathered bundle of fibers stripped from the plants and vegetation that dot the Exiled Lands, this bedroll offers very little in the way warmth or protection.\nIt\'s probably better than lying on the hard ground though. Slightly.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bedroll will set it as your spawn point temporarily, until you have died once.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51961_ShortDesc", "A twisted rope strong enough to drag a captive a short distance")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51961_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. The stronger the material of the rope, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53614_ShortDesc", "Arrows with flammable tips")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53614_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53514_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with flammable tips ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53514_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_ShortDesc", "A cauldron for mixing concoctions")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89103_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldorn means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

Smelting catalysts such as Steelfire, can only be created by an alchemist who knows the particular combination of ingredients.

This particular type of cauldron was first used commonly in Vendhya.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80742_ShortDesc", "A crackling place of warmth and welcoming")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80742_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.\'</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nFew things warm the body and the soul, as a proper fireplace and the welcoming spirit of the hearth. How civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18075_ShortDesc", "Tastes like death, but packs a kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18075_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They\'ll be Lying around too drunk to move by this time. If I had a hundred men I could wipe out the whole horde.</> - The Black Stranger\n\nThe term is used for too wide an array of strong drinks, of various qualities, often made from whatever is on hand. With any luck, the drinker will spend the night drunk and not wake up blind. It certainly heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30015_ShortDesc", "A brief report about desertions from the Black Hand")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30015_LongDesc", "As ordered, we tracked the deserters into the southern desert. We found Old Colby here hidden in the 
shelter of a rocky outcrop, muttering to himself. Of the others, there was no sign.
I asked Colby to tell me what happened, and I got this wild tale which I have written down in full.

"We weren't desertin', we was off huntin' for treasure! Jacoby had it in 'is mind that them broodin' 
ruins, the ones that the bracelet calls The Observatory was full of treasures. 
Jacoby got me and the boys to follow along, an' he took us to the cliff with a length o' stout rope an' a 
plan to go climbin'.
Well, the ascent was steep an' dangerous, on account of us doin' it during the nighttime to avoid them 
cannibals as haunts the area, but we picked a nice clear night with a full moon and got ourselves to the 
very top.
I gotta say, I didna like them ruins from the moment we got there. Just a pile o black brooding stone in 
the moonlight and no treasure in sight.
Jacoby starts poking around, lookin for the treasure an all and he uncovers one of them glowing tablets. 
That voice - you know the one - starts talkin' about constellations and star signs and the crew starts 
swearin' and cursin Jacoby for dragging us up for nothin and then it came...
I ain't ever seen anything like it, mate. It had skin like a plague corpse and black bristlin' fur. It's red eyes 
were glowin' like the coals of hell and when it reared up, the wings blotted out the moonlight.
It took Jacoby first, just snappin forward and tearing 'is head clean off.
Me and the boys were screamin' and scramblin', trying to reach the rope and get down afore this beasty 
could take us.
I got to the rope and started slidin' down, burnin' my hands as I went. Above, I could hear the screamin' 
and snapping and warm blood was a rainin' from the sky. The rope was swayin' and slappin' me into the 
cliffface and I was scramblin' and then... it let go.
I fell and I fell, but I crashed into the top of a tree and I passed out.
When I awoke, I was alone out here in the desert, with a sandstorm sweepin' in. I got meself to some 
shelter and then you found me here."

I'm bringing Colby back to the ship for judgement. Personally, I think we can hang him from the edge. 
He's obviously lying to protect the others.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18301_ShortDesc", "A potion that increases underwater breathing time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18301_LongDesc", "This potion, made from gently glowing plants, allows the imbiber to spend more time underwater. None are truly sure of how the mechanism works, but it is well known to bandits in Kush, who chew a paste made of the same plants before lying in ambush beneath the waters of rivers that run beside major trade routes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18199_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18199_LongDesc", "Both the savage and the civilized mouth water when strips of meat sizzle and hiss on the skewer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18502_ShortDesc", "A woven trap for fishing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18502_LongDesc", "Much of humanity\'s earliest exercises in cunning and ingenuity came from staring at the water and devising an easier way to catch fish. Traps and nets are woven from various, tough fibers, and aid in man\'s pursuit of tasty fish.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82060_ShortDesc", "A dried and stuffed fish mounted on a wooden plack")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82060_LongDesc", "Fishermen often keep their most memorable catch as a trophy. Some are kept for the memories, others to impress, and yet others are kept for the sole reason of having something on the wall. Looking at this piece, you cannot help but wonder what reason could possibly be behind this one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80647_ShortDesc", "A vessel for holding questionable liquids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80647_LongDesc", "Hammered wood, banded with iron, this flagon is indistiguishable from thousands of the same found in dives and watering holes across Hyboria. A friend to cling to in dark times, a lover to kiss when lonely and a weapon to swing when the action starts, the humble flagon has seen and been everywhere.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51186_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51186_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18216_ShortDesc", "Gruel with a dash of flavor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18216_LongDesc", "Spices, ingredients, and oddities often get thrown into gruel to mask the fact that all one has to eat is gruel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51981_ShortDesc", "A vicious sword made in the Acheronian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51981_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51990_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51990_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.\n\nThis shield is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51984_ShortDesc", "A vicious spear made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51984_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51987_ShortDesc", "A vicious war-axe made in the Acheronian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51987_LongDesc", "This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian stlye bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that one ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52642_ShortDesc", "A set of gauntlets favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52642_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91252_ShortDesc", "A set of gauntlets favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91252_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52641_ShortDesc", "A leather vest and pauldron in Aquilonian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52641_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot.

The large pauldron on the right shoulder is designed to protect the main arm during combat, while keeping the armor flexible and relatively light.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52640_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52640_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. The clearly recognizable plume of the helmet also serves to identify guardsmen on sight - a boon for which the pickpockets of Tarantia are eternally grateful.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52644_ShortDesc", "A pair of sandals favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52644_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The distinctive sound of these sandals slapping against the paving stones is a hallmark of Aquilonian cities. 

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52643_ShortDesc", "A leather riveted skirt favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52643_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

Aquilonian guardsmen are often forced to chase down criminals or leap across rooftops in pursuit of fleeing foes. This short skirt is designed to allow them this freedom of movement, while still protecting their upper thighs.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51194_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51194_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51499_ShortDesc", "A shield of hardened carapace")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51499_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is crafted from the hardened carapace of one of the insectoid creatures that roams the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable - but not as effective as a shield made of metal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51179_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed steel axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51179_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52600_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52600_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These reinforced boots of leather and fur keep one's feet both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52595_ShortDesc", "Plated boots of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52595_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The firelight gleamed redly on his steel mail, on his baleful eyes. They burned in the firelight like the eyes of a wolf.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These plated boots are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52593_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets of hardened steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52593_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">But Conan's thews were iron too, and his mail saved him from the gnashing fangs and ripping claws long enough for him to drive home his dagger, again and again and again.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These heavy gauntlets are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52591_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

column4:

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52594_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The great frame under the mail mesh was too hard and supple for a civilized man; the elemental fire of the primitive burned in those smoldering eyes.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51453_ShortDesc", "A mechanical bow with a slow rate of fire")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51453_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

Until the invention of the crossbow, those kingdoms who had no cultural relationship with archery were at a disadvantage in battle. However, the creation of this mechanically loaded bow erased that advantage.

Using a bolt locking mechanism, this crossbow can be used by even the most unskilled peasants to make a decisive difference in battle. When loaded with the correct type of bolts, it has a long and accurate range. However, a skilled archer will always be able to fire arrows faster with a longbow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52048_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52048_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52046_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52046_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91205_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91205_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51177_ShortDesc", "A curved sword with a single sharp edge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51177_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A man on a giant horse whirled, slashed and smote apparently at thin air, and from another direction swept a wild horde of riders, their curved swords flashing in the moonlight.</> - Drums in Tombalku

Straddling the line between the traditional khopesh of Stygia and broadsword favoured in the northern kingdoms, the falcata is forward curved blade with a single edge on the concave side.

The distinctive hooked hilt helps to prevent the weapon from jarring free of the hands during battle. There is much dispute about the origin of the weapon, considering its similarity to the Argossean kopis and the Stygian khopesh.  This falcata bears no marking which would betray its origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51188_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51188_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51591_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Hardened Steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51591_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51966_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51966_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51062_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel, two-handed sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51062_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this massive sword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51158_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from hardened steel of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51158_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Limp and broken he sagged across the altar, his brains oozing from his crushed skull.</> - The Servants of Bit-Yakin

This fine hammer, shining with the blue of hardened steel, bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51597_ShortDesc", "A javelin of hardened steel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51597_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51080_ShortDesc", "A mace of hardened  steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51080_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At their saddle-bows hung battle-axes or steel maces, and each man wore at his hip a long broadsword.</> - Black Collossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its purpose in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Cimmerian clans often forge weapons such as this for trade - theirs raids against the Vanir and Aesir of the north rarely require them to take down foes in heavy armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51630_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel shield of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51630_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Through a whistling cloud of arrows they plowed to break like a thundering wave on the bristling wall of spears and shields.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This hardened steel shield bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for armor of unusually strong aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51728_ShortDesc", "A spear with a hardened steel head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51728_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The defile was blocked by a wild and terrible band of men who stood silent as images - ragged, shock-headed men with spears in their hands - hundreds of them. And up on the cliffs appeared other faces - thousands of faces - wild, gaunt, ferocious faces, marked by fire and steel and starvation.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this large spear baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

The Cimmerians make large, two-handed spears for maximum reach to hunt the most dangerous game animals. Such weapons are fine to have against more human opponents as well.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51843_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51843_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51934_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51934_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51846_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51846_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51171_ShortDesc", "A steel reinforced crossbow")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51171_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52068_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated gauntlets")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52068_LongDesc", "These gauntlets are adorned with overlapping plates of steel, which keeps the main hand protected while allowing full flexibility and mobility in the off-hand. 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91202_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91202_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52066_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52066_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91200_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91200_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52067_ShortDesc", "A heavy vest that offers significant protection")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52067_LongDesc", "Designed with defence in mind, this heavy pauldron is reinforced with overlapping steel plates on the main hand. This offers optimal protection and stability mid-swing, while allowing the wearer room to breathe and remain cool.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91201_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91201_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52070_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52070_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91204_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91204_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52069_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52069_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91203_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91203_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51169_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from a single piece of wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51169_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</> - Song of the Bossonian Archers.

Carved from a single piece of wood, the hunting bow is used across the world and in hundreds of variants.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52964_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52964_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51404_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted of horn, wood and sinew")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51404_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Kerim Shah had unslung the powerful Turanian bow that killed at five hundred paces, and the Irakzai looked to their own lighter and less lethal bows.</> - The People of the Black Circle

This bow is made in the Hyrkanian style, using different materials to strengthen different areas of the bow and allowing it to be shorter than a longbow. For Hyrkanians, who spend most of their lives shooting from horseback, this is a necessity.

Hyrkanians are widely considered the best archers in the world, raised to the hunt and the art of shooting from horseback. Their bows, however, are not as well made as those of the Shemites, who have spent centuries perfecting the art.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52420_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52420_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These boots are designed to protect the feet from blows during combat from the back of a horse.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52416_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_ShortDesc", "A flawless broadsword of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans.

This weapon is truly flawless and will do a lot more damage and take longer to break than other weapons of this type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51191_ShortDesc", "A broad-headed iron pike")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51191_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51167_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51167_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51173_ShortDesc", "A broad-headed iron pike")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51173_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">- Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51956_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51956_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

Crafted of iron, these poniards taper quickly to a sharp point that can be used to puncture holes in armor and flesh.

A thin groove in the center of the poniard can be filled with venom harvested from various creatures of the Exiled Lands. Venoms cause excruciating pain before death but are particularly effective for incapacitating large animals.

This poniard does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51197_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed iron axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51197_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51163_ShortDesc", "A solid-iron Warhammer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51163_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The wild Kushites rushed into the shambles, spearing the wounded, bursting the helmets of the knights with stones and iron hammers.</> - Black Colossus

Forged of iron, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Iron weapons last longer than stone weapons, but the iron found in the Exiled Lands is brittle and poor quality.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52450_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52450_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.\n\nThis armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52446_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52446_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52478_ShortDesc", "Ornate bracers designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52478_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.\n\nThe royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52477_ShortDesc", "An ornate gown designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52477_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.

The royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.

It is clear that the designers of the royal Lemurian clothing were also responsible for the design of the bracelet that imprisons people in the Exiled Lands. Another mystery.")
