column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52465_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52465_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese boots protect the lower part of the leg and foot, while offering a simple mechanism for quick release in the event that the warrior needs to be barefoot in a hurry.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52462_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52462_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe chestpiece is designed to protect the vitals of the warrior\'s head and neck, while allowing freedom of movement for swimming. It\'s not as light as some other armors, but it is not going to drag a warrior down into the depths. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52463_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52463_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese gauntlets are designed to protect the hands and lower arms, but the hands are freed to take up the work of the sailor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52461_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52461_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe mask can be used to hide the face of the wearer, as they plunder an enemy in the open ocean.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52464_ShortDesc", "A tasset worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52464_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.

This tasset is designed to be quickly kicked off if a warrior falls into water, freeing the warrior from its protection and weight before they are sucked into the depths.

The metal discs sewn on to this garment depict Dagon, the god of the Lemurians.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52405_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52405_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91194_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91194_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52402_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52402_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91191_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52403_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52403_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91192_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91192_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52401_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52401_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52404_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52404_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51837_ShortDesc", "A common, thin bladed, double-edged sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51837_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

The only description of a longsword that seems to be agreed upon is that they are double-bladed and straight. Beyond that they vary wildly from grooved blades to smooth blades, long hilts to short hilts, one-handed and two-handed variations.

This example is plain, straight and intended to be wielded in a single hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52060_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52060_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52058_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52057_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52057_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52059_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52059_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51484_ShortDesc", "Short, sharp blades of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51484_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these daggers are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nDaggers are a weapon used with passion by the untrained and with a cold dispassion by the trained. Unseasoned warriors consider swords the superior weapon - until they come across a master, twin blades flashing as they dash and dart within the reach of their enemies and disembowel them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51481_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51481_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun. 'By Crom, man, if you don't get under way, I'll drench this galley in the blood of its crew!'</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this hammer is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51478_ShortDesc", "A massive hammer of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51478_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nMauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51487_ShortDesc", "A mace of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51487_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this mace is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51490_ShortDesc", "A shield of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51490_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this shield is made of obsidian. Nobody knows what the purpose of a glass shield is, but perhaps the black glass is strengthened when formed into such a lattice.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51493_ShortDesc", "A pike of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51493_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this spear is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51496_ShortDesc", "A sword of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51496_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nSwords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91294_ShortDesc", "Boots made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91294_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51513_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers in a blasphemous ancient style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51513_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

These daggers are forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51502_ShortDesc", "A shield made from shaleback shell")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51502_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

The shell of the shaleback provides them with excellent protection against the elements and predators of the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable, though it tends to chip and flake in the midst of battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52974_ShortDesc", "A pair of Shemitish gloves")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52974_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51588_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Star Metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51588_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51969_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51969_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">When I was a fighting-man, the kettle-drums they beat; The people scattered gold-dust before my horse's feet; But now I am a great king, the people hound my track; With poison in my wine-cup, and daggers at my back.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These impossibly sharp daggers are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51065_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51065_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Something came writhing up the steps, something that slithered and rustled and brought a chill in the air with it. Conan lashed down with his great sword and felt the blade shear through something that might have been flesh and bone, and cut deep into the stair beneath.</> - Red Nails

This impossibly sharp great sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51161_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51161_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This devastating hammer is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51083_ShortDesc", "A mace forged from mysterious Star Metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51083_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This mace is forged of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

This mace is exquisitely balanced, the metal forged with the perfect ratio of weight to power in mind. It gives off a satisfying whoosh as it passes through the air, as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51633_ShortDesc", "A shield forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51633_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

This impossibly durable shield is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51725_ShortDesc", "A spear with a head forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51725_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They met like a thunderclap. The Nemedian's lance, striking his foe's helmet, snapped bolts and rivets and tore off the casque, revealing the features of Pallantides. But the Aquilonian's lance-head crashed through shield and breast-plate to transfix the baron's heart.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This impossibly sharp spear has a head made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Spears are two-handed weapons with an ungainly tall wooden haft, but their reach is second to none.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51071_ShortDesc", "A sword forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51071_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'This day you become knights!' he laughed fiercely, pointing with his dripping sword towards the hillmen horses, herded nearby. 'Mount and follow me to hell!'</> - Black Colossus

This impossibly sharp sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51940_ShortDesc", "An axe forged from star metal and balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51940_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a queen by fire and steel and slaughter...</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly sharp throwing axe is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51627_ShortDesc", "A heater shield of beaten steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51627_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Usable by both infantry and cavalry, the heater shield is known for its unique shape and large area of protection.

As a defensive material, there is very little than can match the quality of steel. The additional weight is worth the extra protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51208_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51208_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51183_ShortDesc", "A pair of sharp-bladed off-hand daggers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51183_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan did not reply; he merely stood and glared at her with his burning eyes, testing the edge of his poniard with a callused thumb.</> - Rogues in the House

While all poniards are capable of fast stabbing attacks with their venom coated blades, the extra strength of a steel poniard means that it can also be used to parry the attacks of enemies.

Using a poniard to parry requires more skill than a shield, but if successful such a parry will leave the enemy open for counter attack. Poniards are the weapon of choice in Zingaran duels for exactly this reason.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51211_ShortDesc", "A spear with a steel head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51211_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">- Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51203_ShortDesc", "A steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51203_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51175_ShortDesc", "A heavy, three pronged spear")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51175_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Spears! he muttered. What a blasted fool I am not to have thought of that before! That shows what a pretty woman does to a man's mind.</> - Red Nails

Originally used for fishing along the Argossean coastline, the flamboyant gladiator Aros of Koth decided to adopt the trident as his signature weapon.

The extremely broad head of the weapon makes it top heavy and too thick to be used in a shield wall while the barbed prongs are prone to getting caught on armor and flesh. 

The trident is best used against large creatures where stopping power is more important than precision. Aros of Koth discovered this the hard way, earning renown and fortune for taking down the Beast Lizard of Messantia, but then being killed in a later encounter with a swarm of Darfari Cannibals.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51165_ShortDesc", "A steel Warhammer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51165_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The sheer weight of his shackles would have slain a lesser man with exhaustion. The locks that held band and chain were massive affairs that a sledge-hammer could hardly have dinted.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Forged of steel, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Steel weapons are the standard in the civilized kingdoms of Hyboria and savages find themselves at a distinct disadvantage when they find themselves pitting weapons of stone or wood against hardened steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51200_ShortDesc", "A studded mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51200_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52433_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52433_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52318_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52318_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52316_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52316_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52317_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52317_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52320_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51181_ShortDesc", "An ornate pike made in the Stygian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51181_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus

The Stygian armies are famed for using chariots into battle. This frees their hands to use either the bow or the spear to great effect.

The Stygian spear is heavy, two handed, and bronze tipped. Wielded with the momentum of a charging chariot it is devastating to infantry and cavalry alike.

Stygian hunters use the broad bladed spears to hunt lions and rhinoceros on the rocky plains around the Styx river.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51046_ShortDesc", "A two-handed Iron sword")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51046_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I pay my way with steel!\' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nGreat swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51049_ShortDesc", "A two-handed Steel sword")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51049_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I pay my way with steel!\' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nGreat swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52629_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined boots of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52629_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These reinforced boots of leather and fur keep one's feet both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52590_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52590_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They gave tongue like wolves and surged about the lone figure in the gray mail, and the clamor and din of steel drowned the cries of the circling raven.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard plated boots are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52989_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52989_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These boots keep the feet warm while stumbling through banks and drifts of snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52988_ShortDesc", "A furry breechclout worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52988_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

This breechclout  keeps the settler warm, but has an unfortunate tendency to attract fleas and lice. Vanir women are well known for their habit of bathing in freezing streams in the midst of winter, Vanir men are known for being lice-infested bastards.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52949_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52949_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52948_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52948_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52946_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52946_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91229_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91229_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather boots are practical onboard a ship - for preventing splinters and broken toes, but also for kicking unfortunate prisoners over the side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91227_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91227_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather gloves are practical onboard a ship - for preventing blisters, rope-burn and the occasional knife wound as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91225_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91225_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91228_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91228_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather pants offer the freedom to scamper along lines, while still being stiff enough to turn the sharp edge of a dagger. They also never need to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91226_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91226_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_ShortDesc", "Arrows with flint heads")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53611_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53511_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with flint heads")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53511_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18505_ShortDesc", "A manual pressing machine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18505_LongDesc", "This useful device presses and separates liquid from materials - such as oil from raw fish or seeds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51463_ShortDesc", "A powerful axe blessed by Ymir")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51463_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The giants answered with roars like the grinding of icebergs on a frozen shore and heaved up their shining axes as the maddened Cimmerian hurled himself upon them.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

This two-handed axe is rimed in frost and decorated with the angular runes of the Nordheimers. The haft thrums with power and the presence of Ymir emanates from the weapon itself.

This is a sacred weapon, imbued with the blessing of a deity. Use it well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_ShortDesc", "A placeable divider for the easily embarrased")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88899_LongDesc", "While noone would claim Stygians are easily embarrased, some  visitors to the brothels in Khem may wish for some privacy. While the folding screens do not muffle the screams of what goes on behind them, they do obscure the line of sight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51551_ShortDesc", "A warhammer that glows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51551_LongDesc", "When this weapon was forged, it was left too long in the coals, becoming super-heated until it glowed a fierce, white-gold.\n\nOnce it was cooled and fitted, the new owner noticed that it still glimmered in the darkness, even when there were no other lights around. Unfortunately for the owner, who was a footpad by trade, the light interfered with business that is mostly done in dark alleys. The weapon was quickly sold on, and has changed hands dozens of times, yet it still maintains its glow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11103_ShortDesc", "A stone inscribed with a bizarre symbol")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11103_LongDesc", "This small piece of stone is inscribed with a symbol that seems to slide away from the eye that beholds it. There is something dark and wonderful about the lines and swirls that make up the shape.\n\nBut it is incomplete. There must be more stones like this scattered around the Exiled Lands. Who knows what putting them together might do.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11080_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11080_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18300_ShortDesc", "A potion brewed from the frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18300_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\nDrinking this potion will definitely have some effect. It\'s just that nobody is sure what it is.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11121_ShortDesc", "A small bag of frost lotus powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11121_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\n\nWhat effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11081_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the frost lotus")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11081_LongDesc", "Unlike the other flowers of this family, the frost lotus has no towering reputation for strange mystical effects. It is possible that alchemists have simply not discovered the best possible use of this blossom - further experimentation is the only way to find out.\n\nThese seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51558_ShortDesc", "A bow that seems to penetrate even the thickest armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51558_LongDesc", "There was a legend among the Nordheimers that one of the skalds was captured by a Hyperborean Witch-man. 

The skald was imprisoned in the top of a Hyperborean keep, where thick icicles hung from the ceiling and the cold northern winds would cut him directly to the bone. He was going to die, so he prayed to Ymir for help.

The Skald had just given up hope, when a flash of lightning outside the tower illuminated his room - and revealed the shape of a bow trapped inside one of the icicles.

Chipping slowly at the icicle, the Skald uncovered the wondrous bow, and shaped himself some arrows of ice from the shards.
The next time his captor came to feed him, he shot an ice arrow at the Hyperborean, expecting it to shatter on his chest. Instead, it passed through the armor and directly into the creature's heart.

The Skald escaped, and the bow went with him.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18052_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18052_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nPelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength. Furs are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89101_ShortDesc", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89101_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51974_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with green gas")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51974_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'With sudden suspicion he thrust his head over the threshold, into the bluish mist that filled the inner cavern. And he screamed, chokingly: 'There is death in the smoke!'</> - The Black Stranger

This orb, filled with the spores of the pufferball mushroom, explodes into a cloud of green mist when thrown.

While the spores of the mushroom are not as potent as the pollen of the lotus or dust from Stygian tombs, they still cause significant damage to those unlucky enough to inhale them.

When combined with water, the spores also form a thick viscous substance that acts like grease. When a cloud of spores is met with fire, the resulting explosion rocks the very heavens.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51572_ShortDesc", "A pike pitted with rust ravaged by age")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51572_LongDesc", "Gavain was a member of the Free Companies, a red-handed mercenary who fought and plundered wherever he was commanded. He earned considerable fame during a border skirmish between two Shemitish city-states when he defended a corridor against a surging rush of men.

Shortly afterwards, however, he was struck down by the one ailment for which there is no cure - love. He followed a golden-haired Aesir warrioress into the north, abandoning his gear which, according to mercenary legend, rusted overnight.

Nothing is known of the fate of Gavain of his gear, though it is still said of any mercenary who abandons the companies for a woman that they have been touched by Gavain's pike.

This rusty pike will do additional penetration damage to armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51722_ShortDesc", "A pike pitted with rust ravaged by age")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51722_LongDesc", "Gavain was a member of the Free Companies, a red-handed mercenary who fought and plundered wherever he was commanded. He earned considerable fame during a border skirmish between two Shemitish city-states when he defended a corridor against a surging rush of men.
Shortly afterwards, however, he was struck down by the one ailment for which there is no cure - love. He followed a golden-haired Aesir warrioress into the north, abandoning his gear which, according to mercenary legend, rusted over night.

Nothing is known of the fate of Gavain, though it is still said of any mercenary who abandons the companies for a woman that they have been "touched by Gavain's pike".

This rusty pike will do additional penetration damage to armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82005_ShortDesc", "Gazelle Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82005_LongDesc", "The head of a Gazelle")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81005_ShortDesc", "Gazelle Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81005_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51068_ShortDesc", "A great axe humming with frigid power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51068_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice. Snow sprinkled their locks; in their beards were spikes of icicles; their eyes were cold as the lights that streamed above them.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThe skalds of Nordheim sing storied songs of Ymir forging weapons out of ice and lightning. This axe, gelid as a tundra, gives proof to that legend with every thunder-crack blow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11551_ShortDesc", "Brittle and breakable, glass is best used for ornamentation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11551_LongDesc", "Only the wealthy can afford to ornament their houses in glass, even though creating glass is a simple process. Glass offers protection from the elements and a view of what is occurring outside, at the risk of being easily shattered.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14200_ShortDesc", "A flask for storing liquids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14200_LongDesc", "Glass is a fragile substance most often used by nobles and rich merchants for mirrors and windows. Alchemists also prize it for its ability to store volatile concoctions and their ability to observe reactions within the glass as they experiment. Experienced alchemists have hundreds of such flasks, filled with exotic materials from across the world. Less experienced alchemists are probably dead because they stored their concoctions in a less adequate container.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14601_ShortDesc", "A mold used for creating flasks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14601_LongDesc", "Due to their need for somewhere to store volatile concoctions alchemists are usually proficient in the art of glass creation.\nIt also ensures that if somebody dies due to a flaw in their glasswork releasing a noxious poison into their workshop, they only have themselves to blame.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51578_ShortDesc", "A glowing axe with a wicked edge")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51578_LongDesc", "For years, Glimmermoon was the favored weapon of the Royal Executioner of Nemedia. The executioner himself was a Hyperborean, a gaunt, raw-boned fellow who brought the axe with him from his native land. The axe earned its name due to its glowing metal and half-moon shape. Nobody recalls the name of the executioner.

His executions were quite the show, his glowing axe whirling in a great arc to lop the head from the guilty. But he fell afoul of a plot to overthrow the throne, and his axe went missing in the ensuing turmoil.

This axe glimmers with an unearthly light, and blood seems to cling to the blade. It does additional damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14197_ShortDesc", "A glowing gum-like substance")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14197_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The tunnel debouched into a wide room before the moonlight played out, an empty cavern of no great dimensions, but with a lofty, vaulted roof, glowing with a phosphorescent encrustation, which, as Conan knew, was a common phenomenon in that part of the world.</> 
Jewels of Gwahlur

Some shipwrecked Zingaran mercenaries stumbled into Khemi, wild-eyed with a tale of beautiful mermaids who lured half of their company to their death on the shallow reefs off the coast.

Though the sailors were adamant that the naked, beautiful women were fish from the waist down, their reports of "shining smiles" led scholars to suspect that they were native Kushite women chewing a glowing paste that allowed them to prolong their time underwater.

The existence of this paste is well known among the shamans of the Black Kingdoms, though it is rare in the north where the plants that are used in its production do not commonly grow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14195_ShortDesc", "A pile of...something that glows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14195_LongDesc", "What this is, where it comes from and how it got here are a mystery. What matters is that it can be used in the creation of a cyan dye.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80539_ShortDesc", "A standing torch made from glowing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80539_LongDesc", "Scholars and adventurers have long known of the properties of certain glowing plants that can be found in subterranean caves and hollows. Though some barbaric tribes swear that such places are demon-tainted and ghost-haunted and avoid them at all costs, others swear that they provide healing or other medicinal properties.\n\nThis smokeless torch, created from the bones of some unfortunate creature and a bundle of glowing plants can be used underwater without losing any of its efficiency. However, the glowing properties of the plant are drawn from the soil in which it is rooted. Once uprooted it loses its glow over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41035_ShortDesc", "A makeshift torch made from glowing goo and bone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41035_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The tunnel debouched into a wide room before the moonlight played out, an empty cavern of no great dimensions, but with a lofty, vaulted roof, glowing with a phosphorescent encrustation, which, as Conan knew, was a common phenomenon in that part of the world.</>  - Jewels of Gwahlur

Scholars and adventurers have long known of the properties of certain glowing plants that can be found in subterranean caves and hollows. Though some barbaric tribes swear that such places are demon-tainted and ghost-haunted and avoid them at all costs, others swear that they provide healing or other medicinal properties.

This smokeless torch, created from the bones of some unfortunate creature and a bundle of glowing plants can be used underwater without losing any of its efficiency. However, the glowing properties of the plant are drawn from the soil in which it is rooted. Once uprooted it loses its glow over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80540_ShortDesc", "A wall torch made from glowing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80540_LongDesc", "Scholars and adventurers have long known of the properties of certain glowing plants that can be found in subterranean caves and hollows. Though some barbaric tribes swear that such places are demon-tainted and ghost-haunted and avoid them at all costs, others swear that they provide healing or other medicinal properties.\n\nThis smokeless torch, created from the bones of some unfortunate creature and a bundle of glowing plants can be used underwater without losing any of its efficiency. However, the glowing properties of the plant are drawn from the soil in which it is rooted. Once uprooted it loses its glow over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90997_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90997_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11054_ShortDesc", "An ingot of mostly pure gold")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11054_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the brink, under his very hand as he crouched, he found it, a thin vein of sparkling gold running from an outcropping of ore to the edge and down across the silvery floor.</> - People of the Black Circle

Merchants and Kings alike will tell you that gold is more powerful than any sorcery. It is gold that keeps bellies full, armies equipped, and the commoners entertained. A pauper may be free, but gold offers an entirely different type of freedom.

Gold is too soft to be used in the forging of weapons, but it is a highly sought after alchemical ingredient. It can be ground into a fine dust and ingested or melted down and used to create jewelry and other trinkets.

Some sages argue that gold has properties that ward against creatures of the Outer Dark, but other, wiser sages have pointed out that wearing gold to ward off such creatures will attract the attention of a complete different class of unsavory being.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90999_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90999_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90998_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90998_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11066_ShortDesc", "A gold coin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11066_LongDesc", "This coin is made of gold.\nThese coins are of dubious mercantile value but can probably be melted down to obtain base metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11068_ShortDesc", "A pouch of gold dust")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11068_LongDesc", "Gold has many properties considered desirable by alchemists, so it is always a hard decision for them to decide whether they should grind their gold into dust or use it to purchase more mundane ingredients.\n\nOver the years there have been plenty of alchemists who tried to have it both ways - and found themselves on the execution block for debasing the currency, a crime which kings and taxmen take very seriously.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90996_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90996_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11089_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving golden lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11089_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

Known for its healing properties, golden lotus has been rumored to be able to mend broken bones, heal scars and even unnaturally extend the life of those who drink it.

Perhaps for this reason, golden lotus is extremely rare.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18293_ShortDesc", "Brewed from golden lotus petals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18293_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

Known for its healing properties, golden lotus has been rumored to be able to mend broken bones, heal scars and even unnaturally extend the life of those who drink it.

This potion will provide a significant healing boost to any who drink it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11123_ShortDesc", "A small bag of golden lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11123_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was no dagger in her fingers; they grasped a stalk of golden lotus, the crushed blossoms drooping on the bruised stem.</> - People of the Black Circle

column4:
