column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11053_ShortDesc", "A chunk of ore flecked with golden fragments")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11053_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the brink, under his very hand as he crouched, he found it, a thin vein of sparkling gold running from an outcropping of ore to the edge and down across the silvery floor.</> - People of the Black Circle

Merchants and Kings alike will tell you that gold is more powerful than any sorcery. It is gold that keeps bellies full, armies equipped, and the commoners entertained. A pauper may be free, but gold offers an entirely different type of freedom.

Gold is too soft to be used in the forging of weapons, but it is a highly sought after alchemical ingredient. It can be ground into a fine dust and ingested or melted down and used to create jewelry and other trinkets.

Some sages argue that gold has properties that ward against creatures of the Outer Dark, but other, wiser sages have pointed out that wearing gold to ward off such creatures will attract the attention of a complete different class of unsavory being.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80751_ShortDesc", "A bronze gong mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80751_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Startingly, shockingly in the slumberous stillness, there had boomed the deep strident clangor of a great gong!</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

The clamor of gongs ringing from the temples of a hundred different deities rouses the common folk of Hyboria from sleep each morning. 
Gongs are used mainly for ceremony in temples while noblemen use gongs to summon servants to obey their whims.

It is rumored that in far Khitai, gongs are used to summon the spirits of the ancestors, or drive them forth into the night.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12003_ShortDesc", "Spider silk - soft, strong and lightweight")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12003_LongDesc", "Harvested from the webs of spiders, gossamer can be spun into a durable, strong thread.
Gathering gossamer would require weeks were it not for the presence of extremely large spiders in the Exiled Lands. Their webs are large enough that gossamer gathering can be a profitable enterprise.
It is not known what causes the spider in the region to grow to such an extreme size, but enterprising Stygians have been harvesting gossamer here for centuries.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82052_ShortDesc", "The head of a Gray Ape")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82052_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82058_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Gray Ape head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82058_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18294_ShortDesc", "Brewed from the gray lotus plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18294_LongDesc", "The gray lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.\n\nThis potion offers a slightly less potent version of the powder - imbibing it will fill a person with battle rage that lends them power and aggression, but they will tire quickly in the midst of battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51972_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with a greasy substance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51972_LongDesc", "An orb filled with treated tar that leaves the tar slick and greasey. Upon application to a surface, this reduces friction and sudden changes of direction become impossible.\n\nThe grease can also be set alight by fire, or used to enhance the heat of a fire already burning.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89913_ShortDesc", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89913_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \n\nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82044_ShortDesc", "The head of a green dragon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82044_LongDesc", "The head of a green dragon")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82046_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Green Dragon head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82046_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17060_ShortDesc", "A flask of green dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17060_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80624_ShortDesc", "A patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80624_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17020_ShortDesc", "A flask of gray dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17020_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11091_ShortDesc", "Plucked from the gray lotus plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11091_LongDesc", "The gray lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.\n\nAny who use it do so at the risk of not only their lives, but the lives of their friends and family.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11092_ShortDesc", "A small pouch of gray lotus powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11092_LongDesc", "The gray lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.\n\nAny who use it do so at the risk of not only their lives, but the lives of their friends and family.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11093_ShortDesc", "A small pouch of gray lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11093_LongDesc", "The gray lotus plant is rumored to grow only in the swamps of the dead, beyond the land of Khitai. A powder made from these plants is known to drive men into a berserker rage, giving them inhuman strength and brutality - and no capacity for mercy.

Any who use it do so at the risk of not only their lives, but the lives of their friends and family.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82004_ShortDesc", "Grey Rhino Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82004_LongDesc", "The head of a Grey Rhino")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81004_ShortDesc", "Grey Rhino Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81004_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14190_ShortDesc", "A gray flower used to dye clothing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14190_LongDesc", "This common flower is used by Hyrkanians to dye their felt yurts. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13502_ShortDesc", "Cooked slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13502_LongDesc", "Juicy with the blood and fat of the kill, this universally life sustaining meal could as easily be found around the campfires of hunters from Vanaheim to the southern Black Kingdoms.\nFlavorful and filling, the only downside is the relative ease with which the meat becomes spoiled.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18510_ShortDesc", "Heavy, stone tool.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18510_LongDesc", "With its circular action, this heavy, stone tool grinds greater masses of substances, more efficiently, than a simple mortar and pestle. It can be used to grind things like salt and spices down to useful granules and powders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13540_ShortDesc", "A thin, foul-smelling gruel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13540_LongDesc", "Made from plant seeds that have been ground into a paste and mixed with water, this thin and watery gruel is probably not enough to sustain an active adventurer. For slaves, however, it serves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13013_ShortDesc", "These will keep starvation at bay. Barely.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13013_LongDesc", "To the starving, a handful of insects can be enough to stave off hunger for a while. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80507_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80507_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80508_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80508_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51552_ShortDesc", "A war-club dedicated to Hanuman")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51552_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He knew the hideous habits of the priests of the East and was aware that an invader of Hanuman's shrine might expect to encounter almost any sort of nightmare horror.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The worship of Hanuman migrated to the west from Vendhya, and as it brought with it military traditions of Vendhyan origin. This particular gada is extremely large and is reputed to have been wielded by Hanuman himself once upon a time.

The oversized head makes it heavy and awkward to swing, but it does a lot of damage when it lands a blow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16012_ShortDesc", "Shaped, furnace-hardened stones for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16012_LongDesc", "Loose fitting stones are a poor defense against the elements and the creatures of the Exiled Lands. Bricks, cut from sections of sandstone, provide more strength to structures and can be butressed with iron and steel to create sturdy walls and strong defenses.\n\nThese bricks are shaped to fit and have also been treated with a consolidant and steel reinforcement, making anything constructed of them almost impregnable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12516_ShortDesc", "Tanned hide that is commonly used for lightweight armors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12516_LongDesc", "Supple material that offers enhanced protection. Leather can be stiff and difficult to work if it has not been correctly treated, but there is a fine line between softening the leather too far and having it lose its protective properties.
Leather will help to stop the claws and fangs of a beast, but a determined foe will be able to break through the material.
Used to create armors at an Armorers Bench
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_ShortDesc", "Arrows with hardened steel heads of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53654_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds. Cimmerians use this fine metal to create arrowheads that will put holes straight through the fine and pretty armor of their civilized foes.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18062_ShortDesc", "Steel ingot of adamantine strength")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18062_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Presently he withdrew the blade and showed her the blue steel stained a dull purplish crimson.</> - Red Nails\n\nThose who know the riddle of steel know how to employ both steel-fire and ice to harden steel bars to a higher quality.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53655_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with hardened steel heads of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53655_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl

Without bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.

Cimmerian bolts are made from hardened steel and penetrate deeply into armor, though one needs a supply of such finely made metal.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51589_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Hardened Steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51589_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41029_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel cleaver of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41029_LongDesc", "Hunters in the wild use whatever they have available to butcher their kills and the results are often less than perfect.

The cleaver, a tool perfected by butchers for slicing through flesh, muscle, ligaments and bone, allows the luxury of harvesting more useable flesh from every creature killed. And removing heads without damaging them.

Just don't try to use it as a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51060_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel, two-handed sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51060_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this massive sword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51156_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from hardened steel of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51156_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Limp and broken he sagged across the altar, his brains oozing from his crushed skull.</> - The Servants of Bit-Yakin

This fine hammer, shining with the blue of hardened steel, bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51014_ShortDesc", "An axe of hardened steel for chopping wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51014_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Then his manner changed again, with lightning-like abruptness; he recoiled with a startled curse, knife and hatchet flashing as they leaped to positions of defense.</> - The Black Stranger

One need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unwieldy weapons.

Constructed from superior materials, and marked with intricate designs, this hatchet is as much a display of workmanship as a tool for cutting wood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51595_ShortDesc", "A javelin of hardened steel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51595_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51078_ShortDesc", "A mace of hardened  steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51078_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At their saddle-bows hung battle-axes or steel maces, and each man wore at his hip a long broadsword.</> - Black Collossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its purpose in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Cimmerian clans often forge weapons such as this for trade - theirs raids against the Vanir and Aesir of the north rarely require them to take down foes in heavy armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51022_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel pick of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51022_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The mere fact of your being here is sufficient to send you to the mines for ten years, anyhow, whether you admit your guilt or not.</> - The God in the Bowl

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.

Forged of hardened steel, this pick shows the swriling markings of a Cimmerian clan. Its blue-steel strength is more than enough to mine the hardest ore.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51628_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel shield of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51628_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Through a whistling cloud of arrows they plowed to break like a thundering wave on the bristling wall of spears and shields.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This hardened steel shield bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for armor of unusually strong aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51041_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sickle of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51041_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula

Sickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.

Forged of hardened steel, this sickle's blade shows the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51311_ShortDesc", "A curved hardened steel skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51311_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51726_ShortDesc", "A spear with a hardened steel head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51726_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The defile was blocked by a wild and terrible band of men who stood silent as images - ragged, shock-headed men with spears in their hands - hundreds of them. And up on the cliffs appeared other faces - thousands of faces - wild, gaunt, ferocious faces, marked by fire and steel and starvation.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this large spear baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

The Cimmerians make large, two-handed spears for maximum reach to hunt the most dangerous game animals. Such weapons are fine to have against more human opponents as well.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51844_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe of Cimmerian make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51844_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.

Cimmerian clans often engage in violent local conflict and the battle-axe is a preferred weapon for breaching the wood-walled settlements and laying waste to the rival clansmen within.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90290_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90290_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_ShortDesc", "Arrows that release a healing cloud")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53615_LongDesc", "Made somewhat unwieldy by the bag of ground aloe attached to them, these arrows will release a small cloud of healing gas wherever they strike.

This doesn't seem like a practical way to deliver healing in battle, as there is just as much chance of healing foes. But... some people like exotic solutions.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18400_ShortDesc", "Cloth bandages")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18400_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'She sat on a couch with her wounded leg extended upon it, and the Tecuhltli woman had just bound it with silk bandages. Valeria\'s red-stained sword lay on the couch beside her.\'</> - Red Nails\n\nWounds require special care, to heal and to avoid infection and putrefaction. Sometimes, upon the battlefield, all one can do is bind a wound with strips of cloth.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15501_ShortDesc", "The heart of a fallen hero")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15501_LongDesc", "This heart was taken from the chest of one who called themselves hero. The definition shifts between cultures and locations so being sure that one has captured the heart of a hero is a difficult business. Most sorcerers simply content themselves with trying out hundreds of hearts, in the hope that the odds are on their side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15504_ShortDesc", "A heart ripped from the chest of the commander of The Silent Legion.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15504_LongDesc", "The heart is still beating. The dark energies contained within this heart could be used by a skilled enough craftsman.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15512_ShortDesc", "A stone containing an enslaved elemental ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15512_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He it was who shook down the cliffs at Valkia, by his spells that enthrall the elementals of the earth-he it was who sent the creature of darkness into your tent before dawn.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Long- Also known as the Scourgestone, this unassuming chunk of stone contains the elemental that plagues the Exiled Lands with continual sandstorms.

Enslaved by the Priestking in his desperation to end the war after the Shattering on the Plains, he gave it over to the Warmaker to release at the right moment.

When the time came, the Warmaker shattered the stone into fragments and scattered them across the battlefield, freeing the elemental to do its work.

It seemed to work, gathering a gigantic storm that crossed the Exiled Lands, moving towards the city of Xel-ha in the far east.
But the Giant-kings had not reckoned with the power of the human spirit. A Lemurian priest named Petruso went out to confront the sandstorm. Using the power of Dagon, he anchored the elemental controlling the sandstorm to his flesh, preventing it from moving further east and destroying the Lemurian city.

He saved his people, yes, but Petruso paid a terrible price. His sacrifice had not stopped the sandstorm, it had simply put it into a temporal loop. It passed across the Exiled Lands, time and time again, stopping when it reached Petruso... then starting again.

Eventually this drove him insane.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51537_ShortDesc", "A pair of peshkabz stained with blood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51537_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Sobbing wildly, Yasmina plucked a jeweled dagger from her girdle and plunged it to the hilt in his breast. He stiffened and then went limp, a grim smile curving his dead lips. Yasmina hurled herself face-down on the rush-covered floor, beating the reeds with her clenched hands. Outside, the gongs and conchs brayed and thundered, and the priests gashed themselves with copper knives.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The peshkabz of Vendhya are designed to pierce armor, passing through layers of steel to strike at the flesh beneath.
This matched pair is whispered to have been used to murder kings, and that the stain on the blade from the royal blood can never be removed.

Using these in battle will give increased armor penetration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18251_ShortDesc", "A meal both filling and flavorful")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18251_LongDesc", "Only the heartiest meals can prepare one for the savage world.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18244_ShortDesc", "Chunks of succulent meat floating in a stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18244_LongDesc", "Meat chopped up and cooked in a broth of vegetables makes for a simmering stew that smells both inviting and filling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52920_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52920_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52917_ShortDesc", "A basic padding for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52917_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51454_ShortDesc", "A steel reinforced crossbow")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51454_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus felt his skin crawl, and he fingered his crossbow tensely, of half a mind to drive a bolt through the stranger's body without parley, yet fearful of what might happen if he failed to inflict death at the first shot.</> - The God in the Bowl

Until the invention of the crossbow, those kingdoms who had no cultural relationship with archery were at a disadvantage in battle. However, the creation of this mechanically loaded bow erased that advantage.

Using a bolt locking mechanism, this crossbow can be used by even the most unskilled peasants to make a decisive difference in battle. When loaded with the correct type of bolts, it has a long and accurate range. However, a skilled archer will always be able to fire arrows faster with a longbow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52918_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52918_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated gauntlets")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_LongDesc", "These gauntlets are adorned with overlapping plates of steel, which keeps the main hand protected while allowing full flexibility and mobility in the off-hand. 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91012_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91012_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91010_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91010_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52916_ShortDesc", "A basic padding for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52916_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52608_ShortDesc", "A heavy leather helmet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52608_LongDesc", "This helmet is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer\'s brains on the inside of their skull.\n\nThis heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52919_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52919_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_ShortDesc", "A heavy vest that offers significant protection")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_LongDesc", "Designed with defence in mind, this heavy pauldron is reinforced with overlapping steel plates on the main hand. This offers optimal protection and stability mid-swing, while allowing the wearer room to breathe and remain cool.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91011_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91011_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52601_ShortDesc", "A steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52601_LongDesc", "This helmet is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_ShortDesc", "A heavy door, reinforced with metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90208_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91014_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91014_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91013_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91013_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18228_ShortDesc", "A medicinal brew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18228_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis brew, a recipe from far away Khitai, revitalizes one\'s stamina in small measures, and moderately heals the wary and injured over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12011_ShortDesc", "The untreated skin of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12011_LongDesc", "Taken from any number of wild beasts, hide can be processed into leather using a tannery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80621_ShortDesc", "A rug made from rawhide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80621_LongDesc", "In the gloomy hills of Cimmeria and the snow capped ranges of Vanaheim and Asgard, animal hides and furs are considered a necessity. Hide rugs are a common floor ornament considered doubly practical if the fur is left attached.\nThey also have a distinctive fragrance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18005_ShortDesc", "Small, red berries")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18005_LongDesc", "Growing in the cold of the highlands, these blue berries are used in the making of juice and wine. They can be eaten, though they do not offer much nourishment. Still, any sustenance is good sustenance when waiting for meatier prey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18032_ShortDesc", "Red berry pulp")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18032_LongDesc", "This red-colored pulp, squeezed from highland berries, can be used to make wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18073_ShortDesc", "Wine with a spiced kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18073_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He remembered great horns of foaming ale, jacks of sparkling wine gulped carelessly or spilled on the tavern floor.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nIn Vanaheim and in Asgard, it is popular to flavor wine with mulled spices and serve it hot when a fire is available. Such mulled wine heats the body and soul.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11095_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11095_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51067_ShortDesc", "A hatchet dangerously cold to the touch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51067_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I have seen the hoar-frost glittering in the sun,\' she answered. \'I have heard the wind whispering across the everlasting snows.\'</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nIt is said Ymir sends these sacred tools out into the world for champions to find. With such a hatchet, one can harvest the ice of winter itself and use such material to craft garments and weapons holy to the frost giant god.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18002_ShortDesc", "The viscous, sweet bounty of bees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18002_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'But your skin is white as milk, your eyes are clear as dawn, and there is about you a freshness and daintiness alluring as honey.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nEven at the lowest point in the cycle of savagery and civilization, mankind never fails to value honey. The sweet, viscous food substance miraculously defies contagion and rot. It is used in cooking. The very first fermented beverages came from honey. Medicine men and women know to apply honey to rashes, wounds, and burns - to administer it to ease coughs and soar throats. Honey is even employed in certain Stygian embalming techniques.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18272_ShortDesc", "Strips of exotic meat dried, salted and drenched in honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18272_LongDesc", "There are those who say drying and salting such fare is a waste of superior meat, but there are also those who want a finer sort of dry ration to reach into their bag for on faraway and lonely trails.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18273_ShortDesc", "A loaf of bread that smells of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18273_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">She gave into his hands a wooden dish heaped with dried  fruits, cheese and barley bread, and a great pot of the heady upland beer, brewed from barley grown in the high valleys.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nBread takes on many forms, baked from various mixtures of dough and water. On the climb from savagery, bread tends to come at the dawn of agriculture.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18269_ShortDesc", "Eggs sizzling hot with a light covering of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18269_LongDesc", "Eggs make for a fine, storable food, given by nature in their own containers. Cracked open, eggs cook quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18271_ShortDesc", "It is gruel, but it actually smells good")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18271_LongDesc", "Sometimes one is able to find a few extra things to throw into the gruel, to make it a more satisfying meal.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18079_ShortDesc", "A very sweet wine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18079_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">In front of him stood Tsotha, and on divans lounged Strabonus and Amalrus in their silks and gold, gleaming with jewels, naked slave-boys beside them pouring wine into cups carved of a single sapphire.</> - The Scarlet Citadel\n\nA technique out of Arogs uses honey in the processes of fermenting the pulped grapes, producing a wine that is both sweet and medicinal. This is indeed a drink that blesses one\'s health.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18268_ShortDesc", "Zesty scraps of feral meat, drenched in honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18268_LongDesc", "One of the best uses for strong spice is to improve the flavor of gamey meat, shredded to make up for this chewy toughness. Tavern owners share a proverb: \'A dead rat and a jar of spice will get you a lot further in life than just a dead rat.\' This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52497_ShortDesc", "A replacement prosthetic for a hand")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52497_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nWho needs dual-wielding anyway?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_ShortDesc", "A replacement prosthetic for a hand")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nWho needs dual-wielding anyway?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18000_ShortDesc", "Seed cones of the hop plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18000_LongDesc", "As the monks of a particular order are fond of saying, \'Beer is proof that Mitra desires us to be happy.\' Hops is the flavoring agent and heart of many of man\'s most loved libations.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11096_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11096_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18051_ShortDesc", "The horns of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18051_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'That helmet held the other\'s gaze; it was without a crest, but adorned by short bull\'s horns. No civilized hand ever forged that head-piece.\'</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nThe horns taken from the head of a beast. Horns are used in making jewelry, tools, drinking receptacles, and even instruments of sound.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80752_ShortDesc", "A huge warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80752_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.
This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defence in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52602_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52602_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13051_ShortDesc", "Flesh torn from other humans")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13051_LongDesc", "Consuming the flesh of men is a mark of savagery and desperation. Various demonic religious practices encourage ritual consumption while some tribes in the Black Kingdoms devour pieces of their fallen enemies in order to absorb their prowess and courage.\nThe desert men of Darfar are well known for their cannibalism. With their teeth filed to points and bizarre hairstyles of mud and twigs they are an intimidating sight - more so with the blood of a fresh kill drying on their chins.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15001_ShortDesc", "Stolen from a chest somewhere")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15001_LongDesc", "One of the most important facets of the worship of Set is ritual sacrifice. With consecrated blades, the worshippers of Set will cut the hearts from their enemies and offer them as sacrifice on the altar of their demonic god.\nFor the snakes who gather at the dark altars of the serpent god, human hearts provide a rare delicacy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51401_ShortDesc", "A bow crafted from a single piece of wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51401_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</> - Song of the Bossonian Archers.

Carved from a single piece of wood, the hunting bow is used across the world and in hundreds of variants.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82012_ShortDesc", "The head of a Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82012_LongDesc", "The head of a Hyena")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81013_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Hyena head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81013_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18311_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18311_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to hyenas, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11058_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a Hyena")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11058_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Pelts, even scabby and half-rotted ones, are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52551_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52551_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91295_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52958_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52958_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91074_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91074_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52951_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52957_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52956_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

column4:

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51402_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted of horn, wood and sinew")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51402_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Kerim Shah had unslung the powerful Turanian bow that killed at five hundred paces, and the Irakzai looked to their own lighter and less lethal bows.</> - The People of the Black Circle

This bow is made in the Hyrkanian style, using different materials to strengthen different areas of the bow and allowing it to be shorter than a longbow. For Hyrkanians, who spend most of their lives shooting from horseback, this is a necessity.

Hyrkanians are widely considered the best archers in the world, raised to the hunt and the art of shooting from horseback. Their bows, however, are not as well made as those of the Shemites, who have spent centuries perfecting the art.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52410_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52410_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These boots are designed to protect the feet from blows during combat from the back of a horse.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored nights.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18040_ShortDesc", "Frozen water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18040_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Soft bellied fools sitting on velvet cushions with naked girls offering them iced wine on their knees...</> - Beyond the Black River\n\nNormally, ice is found only in the frigid north, the highest peaks, or the deep winters. To the people of the Hyborian Age, ice is a rare commodity. Sometimes, the very wealthy are able to acquire the frozen treat, commissioning massive blocks of ice to be brought down from the mountains, so that a tiny speck of it might survive the melting in order to reach their greedy tongues.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10024_ShortDesc", "An ice-shard blessed by Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10024_LongDesc", "The ice shard is cold as death to the touch and seems to writhe in your hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_ShortDesc", "Arrows crafted from shards of ice infused with the power of Ymir")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53658_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53659_ShortDesc", "Bolts crafted from shards of ice infused with the power of Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53659_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18274_ShortDesc", "A medicinal brew that smells of honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18274_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis brew, a recipe from far away Khitai, revitalizes one\'s stamina in small measures, and moderately heals the wary and injured over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12514_ShortDesc", "A viscous, foul smelling fluid collected from arthropods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12514_LongDesc", "Medicine men and herbalists tend to pay well for the ichors of exotic and dangerous species killed in the wilds, but it has other, hidden properties.\nIn Stygia, ichor is mixed with fibers and used to harden stone under very high heat, adding a glaze to the stone that makes it impervious to normal weapons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18312_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw imps")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18312_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to imps, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_ShortDesc", "A skull impaled on a stake")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88887_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about the grinning skull attached to this stake. Though the eye sockets are hollow and the skin and flesh have been long since scoured from the bones, it still appears to be watchful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88888_ShortDesc", "A skull impaled on a stake")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88888_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about the grinning skull attached to this stake. Though the eye sockets are hollow and the skin and flesh have been long since scoured from the bones, it still appears to be watchful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88889_ShortDesc", "A skull impaled on a stake")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88889_LongDesc", "There is something disconcerting about the grinning skull attached to this stake. Though the eye sockets are hollow and the skin and flesh have been long since scoured from the bones, it still appears to be watchful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_ShortDesc", "A warning sign as good as any.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88892_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18523_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for crafting armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18523_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With the firelight glinting from his blue steel armor, he seemed like an image of steel - dynamic power for the moment quiescent; not resting, but motionless for the instant, awaiting the signal to plunge again into terrific action.</> - Black Colossus\n\nCreating armor, particularly metal armor, requires a large number of exotic tools. This armormaking bench can be used to create anything from the lightest leather armor to hardened steel armor. Provided that the raw materials are available, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18501_ShortDesc", "Buzzing hive of honey-producing bees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18501_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">They ran full into a cloud of stinging death.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nEven the most devolved of savages rarely fails to note the wiliness of beasts to endure countless stings in order to acquire that coveted, golden jelly of the bees. Humankind first learns to remember where wild hives grow and devise clever ways to acquire the treasure inside. As hunters become gatherers and gatherers turn to agriculture, humankind learns to propagate their own hives close to home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89302_ShortDesc", "A bench covered in tools for shaping metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89302_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale's teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age

Smithing is a well-known and oft-used profession in the Hyborian kingdoms. In the larger cities and towns, smiths are forced to join guilds that offer them a certain amount of political protection, while enforcing a rigorous set of standards of work and tools.

This bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89106_ShortDesc", "A cauldron for mixing concoctions")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89106_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails

The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals.  However, the versatility of the cauldorn means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.

Smelting catalysts such as Steelfire, can only be created by an alchemist who knows the particular combination of ingredients.

This particular type of cauldron was first used commonly in Vendhya.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89102_ShortDesc", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89102_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18522_ShortDesc", "An improved planter for quickly growing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18522_LongDesc", "When man discovered the secrets of agriculture, the world changed. No longer roving bands of battling tribes, the first villages and cities formed around the idea that going out hunting food was a lot harder than just growing it safely behind walls.\n\nSowing seeds in this planter will cause them to grow quickly over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18508_ShortDesc", "A cold box for preserving")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18508_LongDesc", "Though salting and drying are common methods to preserve food, some use containers filled with ice to slow the process of decay. This larger icebox holds more food and preserves it longer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18515_ShortDesc", "A stone cooking surface")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18515_LongDesc", "Cooking brought indoors. Whereas cooking on a campfire merely involved throwing food on a pan and letting it burn, now the art of food preparation can become more complex and varied.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89105_ShortDesc", "A tannery for processing hides into leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89105_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were young men, but hard and sinewy, with a bearing that comes only to men rendered desperate by adversity. They were clad in mail shirts and worn leather; swords hung at their girdles.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

The stench of the tannery is easily identifiable in the major cities of the world and tanners are often relegated to the outskirts of cities or villages, preferably downstream. 

Bark is the most common form of tannin used to convert hide into leather. During the process it breaks down into Tar, which is a useful catalyst for alchemists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41031_ShortDesc", "A fast burning brand of scavenged materials")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41031_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Torches flared murkily on the revels in the Maul, where the thieves of the East held carnival by night.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Fire is the first marker along the journey to civilization. Heat, light and the ability to cook food is the first shaky step upwards from the bowels of primal savagery.

This torch is a loose bundle of plant leavings wrapped around the end of a scavenged branch. It can be used to light the surroundings or to fend off creatures frightened of fire, but it will burn quickly and break easily.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80759_ShortDesc", "A stick of incense that burns to sweeten the air")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80759_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Smoke and exotic scent of incense floated up from a brazier on a golden tripod, and behind it sat an idol on a sort of marble couch.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Incense is often associated with religious ceremonies. It is burned to honor the memory of brave spirits, to create a miasma of mystery in the shrines of the gods and to cleanse the scent of the dead upon a funeral pyre.

Good tavern keepers will keep a supply near the latrine, to keep the smell from ruining the appetite of their guests. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53549_ShortDesc", "A brush for copying warpaint designs.")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53549_LongDesc", "The application of symbols and paints to the body during war is a time honored tradition of the Nordheimers. In days past, tattoos were traditional, but the ever-shifting tides of battle and alliance between those war-like tribes made it difficult to be certain who would be friend or foe in the future.

One well known tale tells of a chieftain's son, married off to a neighboring tribe to seal a hasty alliance. When he brought his new bride to the bedchamber and eagerly removed her dress, he was shocked to discover a picture of his father and the words "limp-pricked whore monger" tattooed across her back. The alliance did not last very long.

Since that time, inks have been popular. Less durable, yes, but also less chance of making a permanent mistake. Through the use of this brush, warpaints can quickly be copied and used again.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90292_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90292_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11108_ShortDesc", "Wood treated with resin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11108_LongDesc", "Wood is an abundant source of fuel and building material.
Readily available and easily shaped with the right tools, wood is ubiquitous in the weapons and buildings of primitive tribes and mighty nations.

Wood allows for the creation of fire and its easy transport.

This wood has been treated with resin, making it stronger and more weather resistant.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90074_ShortDesc", "Insulated Wooden planks supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90074_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90075_ShortDesc", "Insulated Wooden planks supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90075_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90287_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of insulated wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90287_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90055_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90055_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")
