column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90319_ShortDesc", "A wall made of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90319_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.\nA barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90245_ShortDesc", "A ceiling piece of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90245_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the blizzards at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90250_ShortDesc", "A door of reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90250_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90246_ShortDesc", "A doorframe of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90246_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90252_ShortDesc", "A low fence of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90252_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90260_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90260_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90243_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90243_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90249_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90249_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90262_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90262_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90261_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90261_LongDesc", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90251_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Insulated Wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90251_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90312_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of insulated wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90312_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90313_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of insulated wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90313_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90049_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90049_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90080_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Insulated Wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90080_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90026_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90026_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from plant fiber and flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Sloped rooves are practical for channeling debris from the roof.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column2: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90278_Name", "Inverted Tiled Wedge Black Ice-Reinforced Wooden Sloped Roof")
column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90278_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped, sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90278_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90985_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90985_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_ShortDesc", "An unadorned axe of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Traders had come, and priests of Mitra who walked with bare feet and empty hands, and died horribly, most of them; but soldiers had followed, men with axes in their hands and women and children in ox-drawn wains.</> - Beyond the Black River

This axe could have been crafted at any smithy the length of Hyboria.
Axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes. This axe does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11501_ShortDesc", "Basic iron ingot for crude metalworking")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11501_LongDesc", "The ability to work iron is a step along the road from savagery to civilization. The streets of the great cities of the world resound with the ring of hammer on anvil a song to the march of progress.\nIron weapons and armor offer superior protection, but the additional weight means carrying less supplies.\nIron can be treated with Steelfire in a Furnace to produce steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80649_ShortDesc", "A bowl of forged iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80649_LongDesc", "A simple iron bowl for holding or preparing food.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80667_LongDesc", "A simple iron bowl for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80505_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80505_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_ShortDesc", "A serviceable broadsword of iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans. This sword does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90986_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90986_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41036_ShortDesc", "A crudely crafted cleaver")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41036_LongDesc", "Hunters in the wild use whatever they have available to butcher their kills and the results are often less than perfect.

The cleaver, a tool perfected by butchers for slicing through flesh, muscle, ligaments and bone, allows the luxury of harvesting more useable flesh from every creature killed. And removing heads without damaging them.

Just don't try to use it as a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51189_ShortDesc", "A broad-headed iron pike")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51189_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80704_ShortDesc", "An iron decanter for pouring liquids")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80704_LongDesc", "Forged of iron, this is used to store liquids such as wine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90984_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90984_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51012_ShortDesc", "An axe of wrought iron for chopping wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51012_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The rest were toilers, without armor save for shirts of toughened leather, but they were brawny stalwarts, and skilled in the use of their hunting bows, woodsmen's axes, and boar-spears.</> - The Black Stranger

One need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unweildy weapons.

This axehead, created from smelted ironstone, is able to cut down trees more quckly and with less wasted wood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80650_ShortDesc", "A jug of beaten iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80650_LongDesc", "Forged of iron, this jug is used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80911_ShortDesc", "An iron trap for capturing medium sized animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80911_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The jaws of an iron trap had closed on his leg, with teeth that sank deep and held. Only the ridged muscles of his calf saved the bone from being splintered.</> - Red Nails

These traps were originally conceived by noblemen in Zingara to prevent human poachers from trespassing on their estate. The effectiveness of the traps was legendary and it wasn't very long until the traps were being used by hunters across the western kingdoms to capture animals.

When the jaws close on the hapless creature, it is stuck fast, unable to move until it is freed from the trap. Iron and steel traps are in special demand due to the ability to reuse them almost immediately.

This trap is only effective on medium sized animals and humanoids.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51302_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51302_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80700_ShortDesc", "A simple iron mug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80700_LongDesc", "Holds liquids - or indeed - helps pouring them down your throat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80663_ShortDesc", "An iron pan")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80663_LongDesc", "While they vary from culture to culture, iron pans are generally used for cooking in the hot ashes of a fire or on warmed stones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51002_ShortDesc", "An iron pick for mining ironstone ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51002_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Remember the law, my black-haired savage - you go to the mines for killing a commoner, you hang for killing a tradesman, and for murdering a rich man, you burn!</> - The God in the Bowl

A pick shaped on the forge and bound to a solid wooden handle. This will last longer and be more efficient when mining stone, but when mining harder metals, such as ironstone, this pick will be less efficient than one of steel. The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51711_ShortDesc", "A broad-headed iron pike")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51711_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">- Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80703_LongDesc", "Forged of iron, this is used to store liquids such as wine.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80705_LongDesc", "A simple plate for holding or preparing food.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80706_LongDesc", "A simple plate for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

Crafted of iron, these poniards taper quickly to a sharp point that can be used to puncture holes in armor and flesh.

A thin groove in the center of the poniard can be filled with venom harvested from various creatures of the Exiled Lands. Venoms cause excruciating pain before death but are particularly effective for incapacitating large animals.

This poniard does not bear any markers of origin.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80661_ShortDesc", "A simple iron pot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80661_LongDesc", "For those who can afford to work in iron, metal pots are the fastest way to boil water for cooking, bathing and pouring onto the heads of enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16002_ShortDesc", "An iron frame used to reinforce stone walls.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16002_LongDesc", "The weakness of stone lies in the spaces between the bricks themselves and the materials that bind them together. This reinforcement, crafted of iron, helps to create a solid frame for the stones.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51309_ShortDesc", "A curved iron skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51309_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80702_ShortDesc", "An iron tankard")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80702_LongDesc", "Holds liquids - or indeed - helps pouring them down your throat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51611_ShortDesc", "A targe covered by iron shielding")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51611_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> In ecstasy warriors clashed their notched swords on their riven shields, and the people of the town, ragged beggars and rich merchants, harlots in red kirtles and dames in silks and satins, fell to their knees and cried out for joy to Mitra, tears of gratitude streaming down their faces. </> - The Scarlet Citadel

Strengthened with iron, this targe sacrifices some of its manoeuvrability for additional durability. The knobs on the front of the shield are designed to notch the weapons and claws of foes. 

The rivets and design work do not point to a particular cultural tradition, but rather reflect the experimental nature of smith work in the Exiled Lands.

The targe is a shield designed for attack as much a defence. A well placed strike with the shield can stagger an enemy and leave them open to attacks from a weapon in the main hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51306_ShortDesc", "A weighted club for knocking out foes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51306_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he stumbled over a corpse, and a bludgeon knocked the dented helmet from his head; the next instant the club fell full on his unprotected skull.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Used by watchmen and criminals alike, the truncheon is designed for incapacitating enemies without killing them.

Shemitish slavers have been known to waylay travelers leaving taverns in the meadowland cities and expertly knocking them out. The poor wretches awaken the next day in a wagonful of other captives with sore heads, on their way to the slave markets of the east.

It takes a great deal of experimentation to understand how to hit an enemy just hard enough to knock them out without smashing their skull.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51195_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed iron axe")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51195_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Shaped of steel and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51151_ShortDesc", "A solid-iron Warhammer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51151_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The wild Kushites rushed into the shambles, spearing the wounded, bursting the helmets of the knights with stones and iron hammers.</> - Black Colossus

Forged of iron, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Iron weapons last longer than stone weapons, but the iron found in the Exiled Lands is brittle and poor quality.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53612_ShortDesc", "Arrows with iron heads")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53612_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53512_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with iron heads")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53512_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11001_ShortDesc", "Greyish chunk of stone that can be smelted to obtain iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11001_LongDesc", "Run through with metallic veins, this ore can be treated in a furnace to create Iron bars.\nIronstone can be strengthened with additional catalysts during the smelting process. Alchemists guard the secrets of their catalysts jealously, so experimentation with a cauldron is required.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11071_ShortDesc", "A white, bonelike material from the tusks and teeth of animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11071_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

The great herds of elephants which roam the Black Kingdoms are hunted daily for their tusks and there is no reason for men to suspect that the creatures will not continue to roam forever.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_ShortDesc", "An arrow formed from ivory ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51471_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

This ivory arrow, honed to perfection, is excellently balanced and will cause great damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51472_ShortDesc", "A bolt formed from ivory")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51472_LongDesc", "Like cultures and customs, the value of ivory depends upon the kingdom where it is seen.

In the Hyborian kingdoms, where elephants and other creatures are rare, it is a tangible sign of both wealth and power. In the Black Kingdoms, it is common - few warriors exist in those lands who do not possess an ivory handled dagger or jewelry.

It is a great source of trade between the north and the south - indeed it could be said that ivory is the primary reason that merchants dare make the dangerous journey along the Black Coast to trade for it in Kush.

This ivory bolt, honed to perfection, is excellently balanced and will cause great damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80761_ShortDesc", "A decorative drinking horn")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80761_LongDesc", "Usually drinking horns are hollowed out and filled with liquid, but the crafter of this particular horn was lazy, so it is just for show. They did take the time to polish the ivory though.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80762_ShortDesc", "A huge ivory warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80762_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.

This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defense in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies - I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15514_ShortDesc", "A jagged piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15514_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82050_ShortDesc", "The head of a Jaguar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82050_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82056_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Jaguar head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82056_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51544_ShortDesc", "A great sword that glows and hums")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51544_LongDesc", "This sword once belonged to the great troubadour, Jedias Manbaebe, who travelled the known kingdoms telling great sagas about a group of monks who fought evil knights a long time ago in a land far, far away.

During his shows, he would act out the battles using this sword, causing gasps from the crowd as he swung its glowing length back and forth as it hummed in the night.

Unfortunately, as the legend of his sword grew, two bandits (Dis and Knee) took an interest. They ambushed him one day, and took his sword, but were disgusted to discover that the sword was just an ordinary sword smeared with glowing paste and with a concealed noisemaker.

They stabbed Jedias with his own sword and left him to rot.

This sword does very little when equipped but make noises and light.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80314_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80314_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52440_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52440_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.\n\nThis armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15518_LongDesc", "This small key opens a door in Sepermeru,  which is where Razma returned after being freed from the Mask of the Witch Queen.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82009_LongDesc", "The head of a King Rocknose")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_ShortDesc", "An extremely sharp pair of ancient daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_LongDesc", "When these weapon were recovered from the body of the King Below, they had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the handle of the dagger is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.\n\nWhatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_ShortDesc", "An extremely long and ancient polearm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_LongDesc", "When this weapon was recovered from the body of the King Below, it had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the haft of the polearm is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.

The oddly shaped blade makes it more like a long-handled sword than a spear, yet it is balanced perfectly in the hands, as if eager to seek blood.

Whatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80811_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden ladder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80811_LongDesc", "Somewhere, far from the Exiled Lands, a scholar sits writing frantically. His master has given him the task of writing hundreds of descriptions of mundane items, from swords and armor, to plant fiber and stones. He glances at the next item on his list. Ladder. 

He stops, sets his quill down and looks at his reflection in a nearby mirror. He is a man grown old before his time, a slave in all but name to his masters. 

'What am I doing', he wonders. His life is a series of decisions that he almost didn't recognize that he was making.  As his thoughts spiral into the past and as he traces that inevitable trajectory backwards he realizes that there was no single point, no decision that brought him to this point. It was an accumulation of decisions across his entire lifespan, building around him like sand in the desert that leaves him living a life of quiet desperation, drowning slowly as the quicksand fills his throat.

As the realization hits him, he feels a vast sadness, an aching in his soul that he could have been so much more than simply this. A single, crystalline tear seeps from his eye and drips down onto the parchment he is working on, blurring the ink.

Resolving to make more of this life, the man stands, pushing aside his parchment, and moving to the door.

Which bursts open and, before the surprised scribe can even gasp, he is run through by a wild-eyed thief who has crept into the mansion in search of valuables.

The thief wipes his knife on the dead scholar's clothing, and glances around the room. His gaze wanders across the parchment on the table, filled with a list of items and descriptions written in the neat hand of the deceased scholar. He grins, and reaches for the quill.

Later, when the guards find the dead scholar, lying facefirst in a mingled pool of blood and ink, they will be briefly distracted by the bizarre message scratched into the parchment beside the word ladder. It simply reads: "Something you climb, idiot".

The guards shrug. Nobody really cares about the text anyway.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51622_ShortDesc", "A large shield with a slot for a lantern")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51622_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus stood in a vast corridor, lighted by huge candles in niches along the walls. These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Shields traditionally serve a single purpose defense. The lantern shield attempts to broaden that definition, however, by providing adventurers with a series of options for both attack and defense.

Developed in Argos, this small shield was originally designed to protect the watchmen of that city as they went about their nightly rounds, providing them with a handy light source for the darkest alleyways and corners of the city. However the wily gladiators of Messantian fighting pits soon saw that the focused light of the lanterns mounted on the shield could be used to bedazzle and confuse their foes especially in the darkness.

Lantern shields come in many designs, from buckler shapes with jutting sword breakers and attached gauntlets, to simply large shield with an enclosure for holding the lantern that gives the shield its name.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80733_ShortDesc", "A purple patterned Stygian banner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80733_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80214_ShortDesc", "A crude cage made out of branches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80214_LongDesc", "A makeshift cage, suitable as a place to keep ones more unruly... possessions.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_ShortDesc", "A  large campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89011_LongDesc", "The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around.\nCampfires can be used to cook meat - which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.\nWith the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility.  A fire this large is very difficult to hide.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80622_ShortDesc", "A big, patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80622_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80852_ShortDesc", "A large chest for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80852_LongDesc", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this chest is made from sturdy materials. It can be locked against strangers, and all but the most determined thief will be deterred. No system is perfect, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80212_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80212_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80755_ShortDesc", "Wind chimes crafted of human bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80755_LongDesc", "The cannibal tribes of Darfar have developed a unique mechanism to warn them against the sandstorms that occasionally sweep through their lands. These wind chimes, made from the bones of humans, begin to chime when the wind picks up. If a sandstorm is coming, the noise of the chimes becomes impossible to ignore.\nWhen the wind moves sluggishly through the Darfari camps, however, the chimes create an eerie, ghostly music. Perhaps this unsettling tune contributes to the unsettling reputation of the Darfari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80664_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80664_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, this container is used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80665_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80665_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, this container is used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80666_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80666_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, this container is used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80770_ShortDesc", "A large, shabby shadecloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80770_LongDesc", "This motheaten shadecloth has seen better days. But shade is shade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80132_ShortDesc", "A large well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80132_LongDesc", "Made from well-fitted, tight stonework, this well captures a generous amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89901_ShortDesc", "Lashing Post (1 slot)")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89901_LongDesc", "Lashing Post (1 slot)")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18247_ShortDesc", "A heavy and fatty meal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18247_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18054_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a beast")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18054_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron\n\nPelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength. Furs are prized by both the savage and the civilized.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12515_ShortDesc", "A strong, light thread spun from gossamer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12515_LongDesc", "Silk is a valuable commodity in the Hyborian kingdoms and it flows from Khitai in the east and Stygia in the south. Khitan silk is drawn from silkworms whereas Stygian silk is harvested from the giant spiders that inhabit the dark reaches of the southern lands.\nKhitan silk is prized for the clinging, sensual fabric that it creates. It is very tolerant of dyes and holds brilliant color. Any nobleman of note has at least one outfit of Khitan silk.\nStygian silk is stronger and more durable, offering greater protection at the cost of a coarser weave. Dyes tend to fade quickly but the tenacity of the fabric makes it a favorite among the merchant class.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12511_ShortDesc", "Tanned hide that is commonly used for lightweight armors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12511_LongDesc", "Supple material that offers enhanced protection. Leather can be stiff and difficult to work if it has not been correctly treated, but there is a fine line between softening the leather too far and having it lose its protective properties.
Leather will help to stop the claws and fangs of a beast, but a determined foe will be able to break through the material.
Used to create armors at an Armorers Bench
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_ShortDesc", "A leather apron for smithing")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_LongDesc", "Across the Hyborian kingdoms and beyond, in every village in every province, the smith is a necessity in daily life. From blades to ploughsnares, blacksmiths craft the tools and weapons to feed and arm the population.\nIn every village or town, the Blacksmith is recognized by their uniform - this simple leather apron. Offering protection from errant sparks and pockets for storing small tools, this apron is as much a badge of craft as the smiths hammer or the forge itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51963_ShortDesc", "Bindings strong enough to constrain a captive for a long while")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51963_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. The stronger the material of the rope, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30002_ShortDesc", "A leather journal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30002_LongDesc", "Gods curse this sandstorm! 
We were forced to take refuge before the wind scoured the skin from our faces. 
There is something in the storm. Beasts. We hear the skittering of their paws outside the ruins and their howls mingled with the screaming winds.
The men are scared. I've put them to work crafting rudimentary weapons and torches from the loose stones and rough plants that dot this place.
I've yet to meet a beast that liked fire, or the bite of the axe.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_ShortDesc", "Thick leather gloves offering crafting protection")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_LongDesc", "These gloves are made of thick leather molded over a padded inside. Made to protect the hands from damage while working with dangerous crafting elements, they offer a small amount of protection in combat.\nAs a secondary usage, the heavy gloves can be donned and worn during brawls to avoid damaging the hands in combat.\nOne famous sailor, known only as Dorgan of the Python, makes a large sum of gold by fighting his way across the Vilayet sea and betting on his own fights. He claims that the gloves keep his prize possessions safe.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18001_ShortDesc", "Yeast used in the baking of bread and fermentation of alcohol.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18001_LongDesc", "Certain yeasts, harvested by any number of means, creates a softer, tastier bread than flatbreads. This yeast, harvested from certain plants, makes a most effective leavening agent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11097_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11097_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90276_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90276_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90256_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90256_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90298_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90298_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90296_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90296_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90294_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90294_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41037_ShortDesc", "A toolkit for repairing damaged weapons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41037_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He rushed in, hacking madly, but Conan, recognizing him, shattered his sword with a short terrific chop and with a powerful push of his open hand sent him reeling to the floor.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the fury of battle has subsided and the lightning clash of weapons has stilled, the victors are left to count the cost. And sometimes the price of battle is the very weapons that are used to wage it.

This kit, containing a whetstone, a hone and a small portion of blade oil, will allow even unskilled crafters to repair the worst damage to their blades, though it will never be able to renew them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51592_ShortDesc", "A long spear in the style of sunken Lemuria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51592_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then the Cataclysm rocked the world. Atlantis and Lemuria sank, and the Pictish Islands were heaved up to form the mountain peaks of a new continent.</> - The Hyborian Age

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The Lemurians were an island people, inhabiting an island chain off the eastern coast of the Thurian continent - until their kingdom sank beneath the waves. Their story took a brutal turn when they landed on the eastern coastline - and were promptly enslaved by the race of people who dwelt there.

What Lemurian artefacts are doing here is a mystery. Just like the Exiled Lands themselves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52468_ShortDesc", "Ornate bracers designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52468_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.\n\nThe royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_ShortDesc", "An ornate gown designed for Lemurian royalty")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.

The royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.

It is clear that the designers of the royal Lemurian clothing were also responsible for the design of the bracelet that imprisons people in the Exiled Lands. Another mystery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51593_ShortDesc", "A sword in the style of sunken Lemuria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51593_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then the Cataclysm rocked the world. Atlantis and Lemuria sank, and the Pictish Islands were heaved up to form the mountain peaks of a new continent.</> - The Hyborian Age

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

The Lemurians were an island people, inhabiting an island chain off the eastern coast of the Thurian continent - until their kingdom sank beneath the waves. Their story took a brutal turn when they landed on the eastern coastline - and were promptly enslaved by the race of people who dwelt there.

What Lemurian artefacts are doing here is a mystery. Just like the Exiled Lands themselves.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese boots protect the lower part of the leg and foot, while offering a simple mechanism for quick release in the event that the warrior needs to be barefoot in a hurry.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe chestpiece is designed to protect the vitals of the warrior\'s head and neck, while allowing freedom of movement for swimming. It\'s not as light as some other armors, but it is not going to drag a warrior down into the depths. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese gauntlets are designed to protect the hands and lower arms, but the hands are freed to take up the work of the sailor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe mask can be used to hide the face of the wearer, as they plunder an enemy in the open ocean.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_ShortDesc", "A tasset worn by Lemurian warriors")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.

This tasset is designed to be quickly kicked off if a warrior falls into water, freeing the warrior from its protection and weight before they are sucked into the depths.

The metal discs sewn on to this garment depict Dagon, the god of the Lemurians.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_ShortDesc", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89911_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \n\nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53618_ShortDesc", "An arrow treated with a glowing substance")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53618_LongDesc", "The head of this arrow has been treated with a glowing substance, causing it to glow. This is useful for marking points in dark caverns and seeing how deep those bottomless wells really are.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17100_ShortDesc", "A flask of light ash dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17100_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17051_ShortDesc", "A flask of light blue dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17051_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52934_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52934_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91004_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91004_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52922_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17002_ShortDesc", "A lightening agent for dyes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17002_LongDesc", "When this light substance is added to a dye, it lightens it to produce a shade that is lighter than the original dye, without changing the color.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15003_ShortDesc", "The last lingering presence of the soul")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15003_LongDesc", "Unlike the other religions of the age, worshippers of Mitra favor dignified and elegant rituals. They frown upon human sacrifice and prefer to perform purification rituals upon the dead.\nOstensibly, this ritual involves positioning the Ankh of Mitra over the body of the deceased and saying a few quiet prayers. The ankh is then touched to the corpse, in order to cleanse it of any last impurities.\nSome of the more experienced priests have noticed that at the moment of contant, their ankh becomes slightly heavier, as if something is clinging to the instrument. Those priests are often given vows of silence, shortly thereafter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80271_ShortDesc", "A crude log bench")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80271_LongDesc", "Benches like this are common in the taverns and alehouses of the world. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth wrapping that protects the groin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that winds between the legs to keep everything in its place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11115_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11115_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_ShortDesc", "A common, thin bladed, double-edged sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.
The only description of a longsword that seems to be agreed upon is that they are double-bladed and straight. Beyond that they vary wildly from grooved blades to smooth blades, long hilts to short hilts, one-handed and two-handed variations.
This example is plain, straight and intended to be wielded in a single hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51547_ShortDesc", "A club that refuses to kill")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51547_LongDesc", "This crude club once belonged to Sergius of Khrosha who, before he became a captain, was the first-mate of a ship called The Beast. Sergius had one job when the ship was in port - to waylay drunken soldiers and drag them back to The Beast.

For that purpose, he used the club he knew affectionately as Lovetap.

Perhaps it was some combination of materials, or perhaps it was some bizarre sorcerous trait, but either way, the club became extremely good at knocking people out - but it would not damage them beyond that.

Eventually, Sergius lost the club in a gambling den, and Lovetap dropped out of sight and mind.

This club deals only concussion damage to enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80205_ShortDesc", "A low wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80205_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a low wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18281_ShortDesc", "Chunks of succulent meat floating in a stew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18281_LongDesc", "Meat chopped up and cooked in a broth of vegetables makes for a simmering stew that smells both inviting and filling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11109_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11109_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51464_ShortDesc", "A powerful sword blessed by Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51464_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

This sword, suggestively shaped, seems to twist and bend as light plays across the blade. There is a dark ritual, performed naked by the priests and priestesses of Derketa, that involves this blade, a sacrificial victim and necrophilia. 

Derketa it is said, appears in person to lick the blood from the blade.

This is a sacred weapon, imbued with the blessing of a deity. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17093_ShortDesc", "A flask of magenta dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17093_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82024_ShortDesc", "The head of a Mammoth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82024_LongDesc", "The head of a Mammoth")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82023_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Mammoth head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82023_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'He had hunted bears and panthers, but he had never dreamed the beast lived which could make such a red ruin of a human frame in the flicker of an instant.'</> - Beyond the Black River

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved mammoth's brings glory to those who can organize and bring down this most massive of beasts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55100_ShortDesc", "A spiritual residue left on religious altars")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55100_LongDesc", "Over time, a place that is used for religious ceremonies takes on a certain significance. Not simply in the minds of the followers of that religion, but also in others who pass through an area.\nIn the oldest groves and shrines of the world, the presence of those ancient, gloomy gods can still be felt. In the shining altars of Mitra or the bloody slabs of Set, the manifestation of this spiritual presence is palpable.\nWhen a shrine is defiled, this effect leeches slowly away, but if the defilers are of an opposing religion, they actually absorb the power that they have stolen. Thus altars are a precious commodity in the Exiled Lands and worship brings great bounties to those who pursue it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_ShortDesc", "A map showing the ancient kingdom of the Giant-kings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90000_LongDesc", "This room is a copy of the maproom that exists beneath the Unnamed City. In times past, the Giant-kings used sorcery to quickly move their slaves around their kingdom, attuning their bracelets to different areas and then using the map room to get there.

While the terrain is slightly different, owing to the eons that have passed since the creation of the original map, this map room still retains the ability to quickly send anybody with a bracelet to one of the attuned obelisks.

It is speculated that in the dim past, the obelisks served as a form of permission for slaves - the more trusted the slave, the more access to obelisks. Now, it is simply a matter of finding them, wherever they are.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15508_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by the Witch Queen of Lemuria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15508_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Many Lemurians escaped to the eastern coast of the Thurian Continent, which was comparatively untouched. There they were enslaved by the ancient race which already dwelt there, and their history, for thousands of years, is a history of brutal servitude.</> - The Hyborian Age

This mask was used by the Witch Queens of Lemuria to communicate with their primary deity, Dagon, before their kingdom sank into the ocean during the cataclysm.

When the Lemurians crossed into the land of the Giant-kings, they negotiated for somewhere to settle. The Witch Queen, weary of the forced exile of her people, helped the Giant-kings to forge the bracelets, originally to facilitate communication between the two races.

Later, this mask possessed the exile Razma, controlling her thoughts and forcing her to start rebuilding the palace at the heart of Xel-ha.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41023_ShortDesc", "A patch kit for repairing damaged armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41023_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan's dark scarred face was darker yet with passion; his black armor was hacked to tatters and splashed with blood; his great sword red to the cross-piece.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

A warrior needs to be able to rely on their armor in the heat of battle. When the broadswords swing, a layer of leather or steel can mean the difference between life and death.

This patch kit, containing scraps of metals, leather and hide, can be used to repair the most egregious insults to a piece of armor, though it will never be able to repair them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41027_ShortDesc", "A toolkit for repairing damaged weapons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41027_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He rushed in, hacking madly, but Conan, recognizing him, shattered his sword with a short terrific chop and with a powerful push of his open hand sent him reeling to the floor.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the fury of battle has subsided and the lightning clash of weapons has stilled, the victors are left to count the cost. And sometimes the price of battle is the very weapons that are used to wage it.

This kit, containing a whetstone, a hone and a small portion of blade oil, will allow even unskilled crafters to repair the worst damage to their blades, though it will never be able to renew them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18076_ShortDesc", "Drink made from fermented honey")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18076_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">You laugh greatly, drink deep and bellow good songs; though I never saw another Cimmerian who drank aught but water, or who ever laughed, or ever sang save to chant dismal dirges.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nMany lands and many people claim the discovery of mead, to be the first to learn that the already wondrous foodstuff of the bee could be fermented into something yet more wondrous. The Aesir and Vanir of Nordheim often seal pacts made in Ymir\'s name with three successive drinks of mead. A sip of this honeyed brew warms the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18233_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18233_LongDesc", "Both the savage and the civilized mouth water when strips of meat sizzle and hiss on the skewer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18223_ShortDesc", "Various meat scraps cooked together")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18223_LongDesc", "Waste not, want not. When a variety of meat scraps accrue, it is prudent to gather them and cook them all together before they spoil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80722_ShortDesc", "A green patterned Stygian banner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80722_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52915_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52915_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52015_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52015_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52011_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52013_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")
