This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30023_ShortDesc", "A page from a mercenary\'s diary")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30023_LongDesc", "Low risk, high pay they said. Bah, I should have listened to my instincts. But how could I have foreseen 
this? Every now and then a deal goes sour and if your wit and sword are sharp, you can usually land on 
your feet, but this? 
The notice was under the seal of King Ctesphon himself, calling for adventurers and mercenaries 
interested in making good gold for little work to meet at the central plaza in Khemi. I was out of work 
and out of coin and there was nothing odd about the notice. Every so often the bandits who haunt the 
desert highways grow too bold and the King hires a small army of ruffians to scare them back into their 
hideouts for a while. It's boring work out in the desert with nary a whore or tavern in sight, but it pays 
well and bandits are more interested in running away from overwhelming odds than fighting so your 
chances of coming back again are pretty good. Better than any war I've ever fought in.
In any case, I thought this would be the same thing. But it wasn't.
Quite a few of us gathered at the muster in the square - mostly Stygian, of course, but there were a few 
freebooters from the northern lands. They stood in their own little group, some distance from the rest 
of us, looking uneasy.
The royal guards showed up and cleared a space in the center of the square for the royal herald.
"We're looking for treasure hunters" he announced, looking around the square at the assorted scum 
that the summons had gathered. "We've discovered the ruins of an ancient city and we need those souls 
brave enough to travel into the ruins and recover all of treasures found therein. For every treasure that 
you recover, you will be paid a sum of gold. The ruins are, as far as we can tell, uninhabited. Because we 
don't want the whereabouts of these ruins - and the treasure- to become common knowledge, if you 
agree to join us there are three conditions.
Firstly, you will be blindfolded and transported by wagon to the ruins.
Secondly, you will be not be allowed to have contact with anybody outside of the ruins while you are 
there.
And finally, you will wear one of these." He was holding up a golden bracelet, which glinted with a green 
jewel. I was too far away to make out much detail but I remember thinking immediately that the price of 
the bracelet - if it was real - was worth taking the job for anyway.
"What's the trick?" A burly, leather-clad man holding a fearsome looking maul demanded. I agreed. 
Something was not right here. This all sounded far too good to be true.
"The trick" said a black robed man, pushing past the royal herald to confront the mercenary who had 
shouted, "is really very simple." He lifted an arm, and it was clear that he was holding a golden bracelet 
exactly like the one that the herald had been holding a moment before.
"If you try to keep anything you find in the ruins, or you run away from the ruins with the thought that 
you might sell this bracelet - you will be punished" The man in the black robe flicked his hand and it 
wasn't a golden bracelet he was holding, but a small golden snack with glittering green eyes. He threw it 
full in to the face of the burly mercenary.
The man shrieked and clawed at his face, but it was far too late. He began to convulse, frothing at the 
mouth and turning a dreaful pale color. He fell to the ground, still twitching.
The man in the black robe stepped over the dying man, and picked up the glittering snake from the 
ground. By the time he did, it was simply a bracelet once more.
The crowd murmured uneasily. We were used to the priests of Set and their bloody knives, but such 
blatant sorcery implied a pact with even darker powers, the type of pact that stains a mans soul in 
darkness that can never be erased.
"Now, if our terms are acceptable to you, please step forward." The royal herald has stepped forward to 
talk to the crowd again, the black robed sorcerer had withdrawn back behind the guards.
About half of the crowd moved toward the herald immediately, eager for the adventure. Quite a few 
people left immediately, clearly disquieted by the demonstration of power that they had seen.
I lingered. I'm not a superstitious man, but I knew there were things beyond my understanding in this 
world and I wanted no part of them. 
On the other hand, my purse was hanging limply at my side and my lips were parched for lack of strong 
drink.
I should have listened to my instincts. But I chose the path of the fool, and now I am destined to die in 
the Exiled Lands. Just another exile, lost in the desert...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17112_ShortDesc", "A flask of midnight blue dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17112_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18402_ShortDesc", "Flower of deepest blue hues")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18402_LongDesc", "This particular flower is only found in the colder regions of Hyboria. Its deep blue hues, taken from the moan-soaked night skies of winter, are coveted for the making of fine dyes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11099_ShortDesc", "Seeds that can be planted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11099_LongDesc", "Though not as exciting as the life of the adventurer, the life of the farmer is still considered a vital and noble pursuit. Without food, after all, how can any hope to survive the rigors of the wilderness?")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51569_ShortDesc", "A long-forgotten burial shield")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51569_LongDesc", "Mist clings to the surface of this shield and chills the arm of any who hold it.  Nothing is known of who crafted the shield, or what strange sorceries cause it to remain chilly on even the warmest of days.

Just some runes in ancient Atlantean, spelling out the name.

Equipping this shield gives a boost to heat protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51304_ShortDesc", "An Ankh used in the ritual purification of the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51304_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Mitra would have folks stand upright before him - not crawling on their bellies like worms, or spilling blood of animals all over his altars.'</> - Black Colossus

The purification of the dead is considered an important part of the death rites of Mitra. When one dies, the vessel that was the body is usually consigned to the flames in a rite that was borne from the legend of the phoenix. It is said that in cleasning the body with fire, a new soul can be reborn from the ashes.

However, before a body is burned, it is ritually purified using an Ankh of Mitra. The body is struck with the Ankh to push out any trace of spirit left trapped within the body, preventing the corpse from rising again and sealing it against necromancy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52524_ShortDesc", "A simple pair of breeches")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52524_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese breeches reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52523_ShortDesc", "A simple pair of gloves")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52523_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese gloves reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52525_ShortDesc", "A simple pair of shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52525_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese shoes reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52522_ShortDesc", "A simple tunic")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52522_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThis tunic reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18282_ShortDesc", "Cooked strips of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18282_LongDesc", "Waste not, want not. When a variety of meat scraps accrue, it is prudent to gather them and cook them all together before they spoil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51546_ShortDesc", "A mace that swings with great force")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51546_LongDesc", "This mace is forged of a metal that defies common description. It is heavy and ponderous to lift and swing, but when it connects it does so with bone-breaking force.\n\nThe massive amount that it weighs is a small tradeoff for the damage that it does to foes.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80662_ShortDesc", "A metal vessel for preparing food")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80662_LongDesc", "Popular in Nemedia and Aquilonia, the mortaria are shallow bowl used for mixing, beating and pounding food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82026_ShortDesc", "The head of a Mountain Goat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82026_LongDesc", "The head of a Mountain Goat")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82025_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Mountain Goat head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82025_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18241_ShortDesc", "Hot and smelling of winter spices")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18241_LongDesc", "This special brew, heated and loaded with mulled spices, heavily warms a soul even on the longest of winter nights.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18239_ShortDesc", "A stew floating with mushrooms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18239_LongDesc", "A surplus of mushrooms can make a surprisingly hearty stew.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18243_ShortDesc", "Shroom tea with a zesty kick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18243_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The full lips opened and spoke a single word, in a rich vibrant tone that was like the golden chimes that ring in the jungle-lost temples of Khitai.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nThe mystics of jungle-cradled Khitai know of certain fungi to brew in their tea, for the purposes of expanding their consciousness to fathom realms both resplendently bright and dark as the nighted voids.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17105_ShortDesc", "A flask of muted brown dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17105_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18270_ShortDesc", "Under the delicious broth is something that was recently...human")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18270_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Yet what creature but man breaks bones for their marrow? Perhaps those remnants were mute evidence of a horrible, cannibalistic feast...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nA delicacy out of Darfar. The proper way to serve this delicious, hot broth is with a hull human skull in the bowl, slowly revealed with every slurping spoonful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80105_ShortDesc", "A comfortable wooden bed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80105_LongDesc", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. They consider it an important part of civilization and sneer at those who sleep on the ground as uncouth savages.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80758_ShortDesc", "A huge warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80758_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.
This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defence in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80313_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80313_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80315_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80315_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80316_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80316_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18401_ShortDesc", "Bandages coated in medicinal agents")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18401_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'\'Are you sure he still sleeps?\' Tarascus demanded again, setting his teeth against the bite of the herb juices with which Orastes was bandaging the long, ragged gash in his shoulder and ribs. \'Ishtar, Mitra and Set! That burns like the molten pitch of hell!\'\'</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThese bandages use the medicinal value of aloe and honey to keep wounds clean and speed the healing process.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11064_ShortDesc", "Black glass formed from lava flows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11064_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nLegend persists that obsidian weapons are very powerful against certain undead creatures, but serious scholars insist that this was a lie perpetuated by the troubadour Grey Rain Rant Martinous in his well-known Ballad of Flame and Snow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51503_ShortDesc", "Arrows tipped with sharp, black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51503_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these arrows are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51504_ShortDesc", "Bolts tipped with sharp, black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51504_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these bolts are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_ShortDesc", "Short, sharp blades of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these daggers are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nDaggers are a weapon used with passion by the untrained and with a cold dispassion by the trained. Unseasoned warriors consider swords the superior weapon - until they come across a master, twin blades flashing as they dash and dart within the reach of their enemies and disembowel them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun. 'By Crom, man, if you don't get under way, I'll drench this galley in the blood of its crew!'</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this hammer is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_ShortDesc", "A massive hammer of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nMauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51582_ShortDesc", "An axe of obsidian for chopping wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51582_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\"> The rest were toilers, without armor save for shirts of toughened leather, but they were brawny stalwarts, and skilled in the use of their hunting bows, woodsmen\'s axes, and boar-spears.</> - The Black Stranger\n\nOne need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unweildy weapons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51585_ShortDesc", "A javelin with a head of obsidian")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51585_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. \nIt is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_ShortDesc", "A mace of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this mace is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51581_ShortDesc", "A pick made out of obsidian, hard enough to mine anything")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51581_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I know him not,' he answered. 'He is mad to say I hired him. Let him take his just desserts. He has a strong back and the toil in the mines will be well for him.'</> - The God in the Bowl

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.
Created in the fires at the burning heart of the forge and wrought in ornate patterns as it cooled, this pick is strong and durable. It almost seems a shame to waste it on rocks.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51488_ShortDesc", "A shield of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51488_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this shield is made of obsidian. Nobody knows what the purpose of a glass shield is, but perhaps the black glass is strengthened when formed into such a lattice.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51583_ShortDesc", "A sickle made from obsidian")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51583_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula\n\nSickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51314_ShortDesc", "A curved skinning knife made of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51314_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51491_ShortDesc", "A pike of black glass")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51491_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this spear is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51494_ShortDesc", "A sword of black glass")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51494_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nSwords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51944_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51944_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18031_ShortDesc", "A viscous liquid used for fuel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18031_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With one motion he extinguished the lamp and drew his sword.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis viscous liquid is harvested from plants, animals, and the bowels of the earth itself. It has myriad uses, including fuel for fire. Oil lamps offer a long-lasting flame, taking humanity another wrung up the ladder of civilization, combatting the dark that teems with predators.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17096_ShortDesc", "A flask of olive green dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17096_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17090_ShortDesc", "A flask of orange dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17090_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14192_ShortDesc", "An orange, water-dwelling plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14192_LongDesc", "Plucked from the bottom of a lake or river, this plant can be used to produce a bright orange dye that sets in even the most stubborn of material.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11100_ShortDesc", "A cutting taken from a Phykos plant")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11100_LongDesc", "Underwater plants cannot be simply grown from seeds. They need to be cut, and the living sample placed in a special type of tank.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80625_ShortDesc", "A patterned, Stygian carpet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80625_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80648_ShortDesc", "An ornamented ceramic jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80648_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18314_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw an ostrich")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18314_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling matter bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to ostriches, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18261_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from an oyster")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18261_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from an oyster. It is known as a delicacy in many places, and rumored to increase virility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18209_ShortDesc", "Omelette filled with delicious muscles")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18209_LongDesc", "A tasty combination of food from the land and the sea.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82039_ShortDesc", "The head of a Panther")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82039_LongDesc", "The head of a Panther")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82040_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Panther head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82040_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80311_ShortDesc", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80311_LongDesc", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41063_ShortDesc", "A kit that can be used to reduce the weight of a weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41063_LongDesc", "This paring blade is designed to shave slivers of metal from weapons and tools, thus allowing a decrease in weight while maintaining the strength and durability of the weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52905_ShortDesc", "A basic lining for use when crafting armors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52905_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52899_LongDesc", "Armor protects the body, but it can harm the body without the proper padding. This cushioned layer goes between the wearer and the actual armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_ShortDesc", "A broadsword carved with the symbol of the phoenix")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And as he stood, bewildered at the strangeness of his dream, he realized that he was gripping his sword in his hand. And his hair prickled at the nape of his neck, for on the broad blade was carven a symbol- the outline of a phoenix.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the world was young, there was a great sage known as Epemitreus. Little is known of the shadowy past in which he fought with Set, the arch-demon, but it is known that for all the days of his life he strove against the worshippers, votaries and acolytes of the Old Serpent.

It is rumored that in times of need the ghost of Epimetreus flies on unseen wings to aid the kingdom of Aquilonia, and that the symbol of the phoenix belongs to the sage as much as it does to Mitra.

In any case, there is nothing to distinguish this sword from any other - save the glowing symbol of the phoneix carved into the blade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18070_ShortDesc", "Clear, strong drink with an orange tint")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18070_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They\'re not drunk,\' he muttered presently. \'They\'re not even drinking. What devil\'s game is this?\'</> - The Black Stranger\n\nThe orange phykos, an aquatic plant normally prized for the dyes that can be rendered from it, can also be fermented into a crude sort of rum. Sailors know that phykos rum goes down with a rough burn and leaves the belly warm.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51021_ShortDesc", "A combination of hatchet and pick for cutting stone and harvesting wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51021_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">From his shoulders hung a loose black cloak, and over one shoulder he bore a heavy ax, the shape of which was that of neither tool nor weapon.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A combination of hatchet and pick, the pickaxe is patterned off the peculiar tools used by the Afghuli tribes to break up the ice, stone and hardy trees that grow in their mountain ranges. The Afghuli may be considered uncivilized, but their wily cunning and resourcefulness has given them the ability to survive in one of the most inhospitable mountain ranges on the Thurian continent.

The Pickaxe can harvest wood and stone equally well and allows adventurers to focus on carrying more weapons and other tools.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80631_ShortDesc", "A soft pillow")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80631_LongDesc", "Pillows can be anything from a sack stuffed with rags to a masterwoven spider silk. They can be found from hovels to palaces and anywhere in between. Even the hardiest of warriors like to have somewhere to lay their head at night.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80961_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80961_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Somewhere near by had been the pit, dark and awful, wherein screaming victims were fed to a nameless amorphic monstrosity which came up out of a deeper, more hellish cavern.</> - Black Colossus

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12001_ShortDesc", "Assorted stalks, leaves and sprigs torn from plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12001_LongDesc", "The most basic materials that can be gathered by hand from plants. These fibers can be woven into rough clothing, but it will only provide simple protection against the elements.\nAnything woven from such crude material cannot be expected to stop a swinging blade.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18521_ShortDesc", "A planter for growing plants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18521_LongDesc", "When man discovered the secrets of agriculture, the world changed. No longer roving bands of battling tribes, the first villages and cities formed around the idea that going out hunting food was a lot harder than just growing it safely behind walls.\n\nThis planter is a standard design, and seeds sown in it will grow at a regular rate.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80946_ShortDesc", "A pleasure temple dedicated to the goddess Derketo")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80946_LongDesc", "Derketo is a fertility goddess and she is worshipped for her ability to grant bounteous crops and good calving seasons. Her rituals, however, involved deviant orgies that can last for weeks and include necrophilia and bestiality.\n\nHer places of worship are therefore chosen for comfort, style, and the freeing of inhibitions. They are places where life and death intertwine like a pair of lovers. Those who visit the pleasure places of Derketo are reminded what it is to live and die - and how pleasurable both can be.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_ShortDesc", "A hollowed out arrow filled with a poisonous powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53619_LongDesc", "This arrowhead has been hollowed out and filled with a poisonous powder. Designed to split upon impact, the arrow releases a cloud of poisonous spores into the air, damaging any standing within.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11074_ShortDesc", "A floating foundation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11074_LongDesc", "This wooden pontoon can be placed on water and used as a basis for building. It is worth noting, however, that unlike building foundations pontoons cannot be stacked vertically.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90323_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90324_ShortDesc", "A wedge-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90324_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11077_ShortDesc", "A handful of odorous, yet powerful, matter")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11077_LongDesc", "This compost is particularly potent for growing living things. The addition of blood and ash to the regular organic matter seems to have stimulated a particularly strong reaction.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18275_ShortDesc", "Bigger is always better no matter what they say")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18275_LongDesc", "Some tinctures are useful. Others are merely... engorging.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30003_ShortDesc", "A brief prayer to Hanuman")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30003_LongDesc", "Oh lord of the darkness,
Of men who are not men,
Give us strength and suffering,
In equal measure.

Let our bodies be pleasing to you,
And our minds quieted from this conscious thought.
Let us find the inner rages,
And loose them upon the earth.

We give our sacrifice into your hands,
Appease your thirst in the slickness of blood.
Grant us the power of your might,
The eternal strength of Hanuman.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18507_ShortDesc", "A cold box for preserving")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18507_LongDesc", "Though salting and drying are common methods to preserve food, some use containers filled with ice to slow the process of decay.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30019_ShortDesc", "A leather bound journal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30019_LongDesc", "It is amazing to me that the other people who share this place with me call this The Exiled Lands. If I could name it, I would call it the Blessed Lands, because it truly is a place of great blessings.
In my youth, I was a rash and foolish man, the youngest son of a minor noble of Poitain. At that age I was consumed by my love of wealth and status and I drank and gambled with other young men of questionable character.
Eventually my father, when confronted with my gambling debts, gave me no choice. He simply shipped me off to a monastery, to contemplate my sins.
I was not an admirable monk, I confess freely. More concerned with my own amusement than the state of my soul, I often stole from the monastery by night and returned with stolen casks of ale and food. I was popular among the other monks, of course, but the Abbot began to see my influence upon his entire congregation.
Eventually, he decided to be rid of me.
One night I awoke, bound hand and foot with sturdy ropes, while two burly men lifted me from my bunk and carried me down the winding stone staircase of the monastery. The Abbot accompanied them, wringing his hands and pleading to me with his eyes.
"My child, the choice breaks my heart, but I am losing the others. These men will take you away, somewhere far away, where you can start a new life away from your father or Mitra. It will be the best for this monastery and the best for you. Tell me that you understand?" he pleaded.
"What if they decided to slit my throat, Abbot? Then my death will be on your hands." I spat.
"I have assurances that they will not." He glanced nervously at the men carrying me. "I wish you the best of your new life, child". He turned away.
I was put into the back of a wagon, covered with a sackcloth, and left to my terrified thoughts.
For how long I traveled, I cannot say. I was passed from one set of hands to another, always with the clink of gold to seal the exchange. Other captives joined me in the wagon - men and women from different lands. Some were nobleman, some were commoners. All were as confused as I was about where we were going and why. Most of us assumed that our captors were Shemitish slavers.
On the last night of my old life, we were given our rations, a thick heavy stew of vegetables and meat. Like the others, I ate ravenously. And like the others, when whatever poison they had put into the food kicked in, the darkness swallowed me.
The next day, my new life began.
I awoke, stripped naked, in the sands of a vast desert. There were no people to be seen, just some ruins and the vast emptiness of the sands. I was disoriented, but I chose a direction and set out, hoping to find anybody or anything.
I almost died. A sandstorm came sweeping in, swirling sand and lightning and I fled before it, taking shelter in the shadow on an old tumbled statue.
There were beasts in the sandstorm. I could hear them moving around and howling with the screeching wind.
I repented my life then, thinking of my family for the first time in years.I prayed to Mitra to protect my soul and I forgave the Abbot, who had been a good man trying to protect his flock.
Mitra spoke to me then, and his words were for me alone. He wrapped me in his presence, and kept the creatures from finding me. I gave myself wholly to Mitra, there in the darkest hour of my life. 
I came from the desert a new man and, guided by Mitra, I found this place. This shrine is dedicated to my god and to every Exiled soul, far from home and weary, who could use a place to rest.
I leave this story here in the hope that it will inspire others. I have gone ahead, deeper into the Exiled Lands. Mitra has told me that there is much work to do.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80502_ShortDesc", "An upgraded torch that can be placed in the ground")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80502_LongDesc", "A large torch that can be placed in the ground to create light in an area. Some use these as beacons, to light their way home on the darkest of nights.\nIn the Exiled Lands, the torches of the Darfari Cannibals are prominent in the darkness. In their camps, the cannibals dance madly to the throbbing of skin-covered drums and their frenzy amongst the flickering light of torch and cookfire seems oddly appropriate.\nThese torches can be lit and unlit without fuel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18008_ShortDesc", "A mushroom that violently discharges poisonous spores")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18008_LongDesc", "For a very long time, alchemists ignored the properties of the puffball mushroom in favour of studying the various types of lotus and their effects.\nIn recent times, however, puffball mushrooms have become a popular area of study since they are less deadly and ultimately easier to grow and handle than lotus.\nThese mushrooms can be harvested for their spores, which can be used to fill a glass orbs and dispersed to form a poisonous cloud at the discretion of the wielder.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53501_ShortDesc", "Flesh that has been ritually purified")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53501_LongDesc", "Devotees of Yog have purified this flesh in the firepits of sacrifice. It can be eaten to gain the favour of Yog.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18211_ShortDesc", "Crystal-clear water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18211_LongDesc", "Water is necessary for life, yet it is not always pure. One can risk sickness by drinking from a strange water source. Humankind has learned different methods of purifying their water, from charcoal to boiling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17080_ShortDesc", "A flask of purple dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17080_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11083_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving purple lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11083_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

As such it has become extremely popular as a blade coating and for treating the small needles used in traps and trick rings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18296_ShortDesc", "A potion of squeezed purple lotus juice")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18296_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

One wonders at the purpose of such a potion, because if all stories are to be believed, the juice of the purple lotus causes temporary paralysis. Why anyone would imbibe it willingly is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11084_ShortDesc", "A small bag of purple lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11084_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

What effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11085_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the purple lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11085_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is steeped in the juice of the purple lotus which grows in the ghost-haunted swamps of southern Stygia, said the magician.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The purple lotus plant, which grows in the southern swamps of Stygia, is a favorite weapon of sorcerers. The juice of the plant causes a temporary paralysis - a seemingly sorcerous effect that does not require the actual use of sorcery.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13599_ShortDesc", "Whatever this used to be, it is inedible now")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13599_LongDesc", "Meat which has begun to putrefy has an odor and flavour all of its own.\nEating it might stave off starvation, but at the price of becoming violently ill. Even carrion eaters shun putrid meat.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80531_ShortDesc", "An odd gem that glows when rubbed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80531_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80533_ShortDesc", "An ornate standing torch topped with radium")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80533_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.

This standing torch can be placed in the ground to light an area or show the path home. Adding dye to the radium torch, will change the color of its glow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80535_ShortDesc", "An ornate wall torch topped with radium")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80535_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

The product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.

This wall torch can be attached to a building. Adding dye to the radium torch will change the color of its glow.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82061_ShortDesc", "A dried and stuffed fish mounted on a wooden plack")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82061_LongDesc", "Fishermen often keep their most memorable catch as a trophy. Some are kept for the memories, others to impress, and yet others are kept for the sole reason of having something on the wall. Looking at this piece, you cannot help but wonder what reason could possibly be behind this one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11102_ShortDesc", "Cold, lifeless ashes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11102_LongDesc", "What was burned to create these ashes is not apparent but mixing them into compost increase its potency. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18279_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from a wild boar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18279_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80111_ShortDesc", "A rawhide bedroll for sleeping on the ground.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80111_LongDesc", "Roughly sewn together from the hides of animals, this bedroll offers warmth and some small protection from sharp rocks and twigs on the grounds.\nThe price, of course, is the sharp smell of untreated leather and the occasional unwanted attentions of passing animals.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bedroll will set it as your spawn point temporarily, until you have died once.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51962_ShortDesc", "Bindings strong enough to constrain a captive for a while")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51962_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">How long Conan lay senseless he never knew. His first sensation of returning consciousness was that of being dragged by one arm over rough and stony ground, and through dense underbrush. Then he was thrown carelessly down, and perhaps the jolt brought back his senses.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Ropes have dozens of uses, but the most common in the Exiled Lands is the binding and capture of slaves. Once an enemy is rendered unconscious, their ankles are bound with rope and they are dragged into captivity.

Ropes abrade on sharp stones and unravel often. The stronger the material of the rope, the further the captive can be dragged.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30006_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30006_LongDesc", "When my father died, I knew they would be coming for me. It was only a matter of time.
What I didn't expect was this....to be crucified and left to rot on the edge of a wasteland that I have 
never seen before.
It makes sense to me that the cowardly fools that they sent to do the job would not have the courage to 
kill me. They are mongrels, the cast off bloodlines of slaves and commoners, and such as they do not 
dare to spill royal blood.
Instead, I was bound hand, foot and mouth and smuggled out to god knows where.
They left me for the vultures, but I was rescued by a man. 
Such a man! Clean-limbed and bronze-skinned, I have never seen his like in the citystates that dot the 
meadowlands of Shem. He came to me as I hung from the cross and his icy blue stare was a challenge. 
Did I dare to live?
Now I crouch at the edge of this wasteland, once a daughter of princes, now a nameless exile in an 
unfamiliar land. In my hands, the shaft of the double-bladed axe that he gave me is a comforting weight. 
The answer is yes. I will live.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30007_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30007_LongDesc", "I am not alone here. That was the first revelation that came to me as I crouched, shivering, on the banks of the river. There are others, ragged and broken men and women, who light bonfires on the shores of the river and huddle close together for warmth.
Fools. The light draws unfriendly eyes and I would never put myself at such risk.
My father always taught me that the best way to survive was not to make the mistakes that other people make. Life is not always about the choices we make, but about the foolish choices we avoid making. 
But father is dead and I am alone in the darkness.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30008_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30008_LongDesc", "My father told me that there is something to be learned from all the peoples of the world. I do not yet know what these Darfari will teach me.

I was captured as I moved north from the river. They clubbed me senseless and dragged me back to their camp, thrusting me into a woven cage full of prisoners.

They've been dragging us out, one by one, to their sacrifice pits. The screams of the victims fill the air and the scent... my mouth waters and I hate myself.

I've seen the bloody sacrifices that Set requires and the corpulent orgies of Derketo, but these brutes with filed teeth and blood running down their chins... I don't like this darkness. It makes my skin crawl.

Some of the other prisoners here are from further north. One of them claims to be a Stygian bounty hunter who came here chasing treasure. He says there is a whole city of them in the north.

And in the cage beside us is a woman who is dressed...like a pirate? Does that mean we are somewhere near the ocean?

I need answers. I've been so busy running. Surviving. 

There's a loose branch on the weaving of this cage. My Stygian friend and I are working it slowly loose and then we will vanish into the night.

I realize now that I have been foolish to avoid others. If I am to escape these exiled lands, I need to find people who know what the stakes are. I need other people. 

Lesson learned.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30009_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30009_LongDesc", "I walk among giants.

My Stygian friend (his name is Jakkad) and I found this place after we fled the Darfari. I can't even say for certain that we managed to lose them - they shied away from entering this place. Perhaps they consider it sacred.

When we came to the entrance, our bracelets flared and the tablets by the great door were lit from within by a light like devil's fire.

A voice spoke within our minds, alien, arrogant. It spoke and in my mind I saw the black spires of an ancient city and the stately, unearthly creatures that dwelt within.

I fell down in a faint, dreaming as one who has inhaled the pollen of the Black Lotus.

In my dream, I walked with them along black stone avenues and sat with them as they communed with primordial beings and took counsel with blasphemous minds from outside the veil. I watched as they observed humans entering their lands, at first amused and then alarmed.

I watched as they changed, hardening their hearts against the humans who came to them, begging for refuge. They sealed their borders. They enslaved the humans that they captured. They bonded them, with these bracelets that we wear today.

When I awoke, hours later, Jakkad and I spoke of what I had seen. Apparently, he had none of my visions, just heard the voice in his mind warning him to stay away from this place.

It is becoming clear to me that there is more going on here than just the politics that I learned at the feet of my foster-father. There are answers to be found. For those who would seek. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30010_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30010_LongDesc", "I think I must be dreaming. I visited pirates today. Pirates! In the middle of a desert!

It's as ridiculous as it sounds. Landlocked pirates who've built themselves a ship of stone and iron on a mesa in the middle of a canyon. They dress in pirate garb and call themselves ?The Black Hand?.

They claim to be searching for a way out of the Exiled Lands, the same as Jakked and I, but it doesn't seem as though they have made much progress. There was a lot of talk about hidden maps and secret treasures. I did not speak to their leader, the Butcher of Khwarizm, but I saw her from a distance. A formidable woman. Whatever these fools who follow her think, she has a real plan.

Jakkad and I have agreed to continue west. According to Jakkad there are more ruins out there - an entire city! - though he claims that it is dangerous. But beyond it, in the northwest is the city where his people can be found.

Our search continues...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30011_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30011_LongDesc", "Jakkad is gone. Swallowed by the darkness and desolation. A winged demon screeches a haunting dirge as it flees with my companion towards the stars.
 
Ever since we took our first steps into this city, we knew that something was waiting for us. The darkness is a tide, lapping at the shore of my sanity, eroding it. Blood seeps from wounds I didn't know I had. 

The ruins cast insane shadows on the landscape and they cast a shadow on my mind. The past and the present run together in my mind and--
I am a slave rushing to help my master and--
I am a woman screaming in the ruins and--
I am a god planning wars and wickedness and?
I am a sandstorm, scouring the lands and-

I am...myself. Alone. Exiled.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30012_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30012_LongDesc", "For a long time, I drifted between worlds. I dreamed of lives that I never lived, faces that I never knew, loves that I never had. And in one of my dreams, I found the answer. But I must return to the city. And I dare not do that alone. 

I don't know where they found me, these rough people dressed in the skins of hyenas. They carried me back to their camp - somewhere north of the city, and left me sleeping on a pile of furs by one of their tents.
I don't think they expected me to wake up.

I've been watching them while pretending to sleep. There is something very strange going on. Their body language is wrong. I grew up on the streets of Asgalun and I could read the body of a haggling merchant before I could walk. 

But these people... They remind me of the mangy curs that used to wander the streets, begging for scraps. They stand too close. They sniff at one another. When one of them shouts, the others cower.

I need to get out of here. 

They are gathering in the old arena among the ruins, howling like hyenas. They are performing some ritual. A naked man is cloaked in a blood soaked Hyena skin.

I dare not waste this chance. I must slip away.

I will go west and find Jakkad's people. I'm going to need their help.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30013_ShortDesc", "A journal entry written by Razma the Exile")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30013_LongDesc", "I am ready.

Jakkad's people were skeptical when I first stumbled into their city. But they knew his name and then... Shemites! My countrymen! Familiar faces. Some recognized my face, but I quieted them with a glance.

It has been good for me to be here. I have been able to rest and relax. The Exiled Lands are a fearsome place, but the people here have managed to build something.

I have spoken with men who have been here for a score of years. They told me of the Purge, when soldiers ride through the land, slaying and pillaging. They have told me of the sandstorms that arise with such fury out of nowhere and disappear just as quickly.

I told them of the vision I had in the ruined city. Of the room, nestling beneath the secret heart of the ruins. Of the map, which shows the land that traps us. Of the gems, which can free us all.

They've agreed to send an expedition. I will lead them into the ruins.

And then... to freedom.

I leave the last page of my journal here. My journey thus far has been one written. Action speaks louder than words.

May we never meet again in the Exiled Lands. 

- Razma of Shem")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53613_ShortDesc", "Arrows with sharpened steel heads")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53613_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53513_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with sharpened steel heads")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53513_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Arus the watchman grasped his crossbow with shaky hands, and he felt beads of clammy perspiration on his skin as he stared at the unlovely corpse sprawling on the polished floor before him. It is not pleasant to come upon Death in a lonely place at midnight.</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nWithout bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53201_ShortDesc", "A poison that can be applied to daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53201_LongDesc", "The toxin gland of the Sand Reapers is difficult to obtain due to the ferocious nature of the creatures. When properly prepared, it becomes a poison that can be applied to certain weapons, such as daggers, and then used to debilitate foes. In Vendhya, assassins often use poison to kill their targets - the current king has weathered no less than five attempts on his life thus far, though the five skulls bleaching on the Tower of the Kites are evidence of their failure.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51576_ShortDesc", "An axe coated in strange substance")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51576_LongDesc", "The axe has long been a staple of the Red Brotherhood who terrorize the Turanian vessels that travel on the Vilayet.

The axes are coated in an alchemical substance that dampens their ability to strike sparks on metal, to prevent accidental fires during ship to ship combat.

This axe, when equipped, is more effective at penetrating armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82043_ShortDesc", "The head of a red dragon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82043_LongDesc", "The head of a red dragon")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82045_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Red Dragon head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82045_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17040_ShortDesc", "A flask of red dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17040_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90291_ShortDesc", "A door made to fit a hatch frame")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90291_LongDesc", "One of the strongest doors that can be crafted, the heavy door offers protection against everything but the most powerful of enemy tricks.\nRaging hordes have been kept at bay by such doors and with a simple locking mechanism they become proof against incursions into structures.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90325_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Insulated Wood foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90325_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90203_ShortDesc", "A ceiling made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90203_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmned in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_ShortDesc", "Crenelated walls for placing siege cauldrons and archers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90223_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Under the walls the mailed figures swarmed, battering at the gates, rearing up scaling-ladders, pushing storming-towers, thronged with spearmen, against the turrets.'</> - The Scarlet Citadel

The strength of walls during a siege is determined by two things - the strength of building itself and the ability of defenders to cleanly shoot enemies that are attacking.

These crenelated walls are a common design, effective at giving archers a clear space for firing on enemies as well as providing a niche for placing siege cauldrons and other defensive mechanisms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90204_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90204_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90210_ShortDesc", "A low fence made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90210_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90220_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90220_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90207_ShortDesc", "A frame made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90207_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90222_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90222_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90221_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90221_LongDesc", "The best battle, they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90209_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90209_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90310_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90310_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90311_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of reinforced stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90311_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90079_ShortDesc", "A staircase made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90079_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90202_ShortDesc", "A wall made of reinforced stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90202_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90067_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90068_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_ShortDesc", "A door of reinforced wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90108_LongDesc", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90034_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90034_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41065_ShortDesc", "A reinforcement that can be used to make weapons and armor more durable")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41065_LongDesc", "A warrior relies on their strength, their skill and their weapon to carry them in battle. If any of these are broken in the clash of swords, it puts life and limb at risk.

This reinforcement can be used to find the flaws in a weapon or piece or armor and buttress them against the storm of battle.

This simple reinforcement will increase the durability of a weapon or piece of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80739_ShortDesc", "A patterened banner in the fashion of the Relic Hunters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80739_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with the signature motif of the Relic Hunters.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52545_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52545_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52543_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52543_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")
