column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52542_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52542_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91043_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52541_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52541_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51031_ShortDesc", "Heavy, unwieldy hammer for repairing structures")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51031_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Khosatral Khel rose and lived and waxed mighty once more. It pleased him to restore the city as it was in the days before its fall.</> - The Devil in Iron

Crafted for utility, this hammer is an unwieldy tool when used for anything other than pounding on stone or wood.

It is inevitable that time, the elements, and the beasts of the Exiled Lands will take their toll on structures. With the repair hammer and the correct combination of materials, almost anything can be repaired with a few hefty swings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12013_ShortDesc", "Hide harvested from a reptile")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12013_LongDesc", "Along the reaches of the Styx, the great crocodiles of Stygia are feared as man-eaters and messengers of the gods. Although not as bound to the Stygian religion as the great snakes that haunt the blood-mad streets of Khemi, crocodiles are still revered and considered sacred.\nPoachers and hunters from the Black Kingdoms to the south, however, do not share this reverence for the crocodile and willingly hunt them for their skins which make a fine leather.\nThis reptile skin might have been taken from a crocodile or a large lizard.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52020_ShortDesc", "Boots made of thick reptile leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52020_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18030_ShortDesc", "A syrupy substance bled from trees")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18030_LongDesc", "Known as the blood of trees, particularly of those growing in the highlands. Resin weeps from the wounds cleaved into bark, protecting the plant from injury and illness. Humankind has found some uses for the viscous stuff, including certain perfumes and incenses precious to religious rites.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18077_ShortDesc", "A dark wine with a burning bouquet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18077_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Ascalante turned again to his wine. Over the jeweled spires was rising a dawn crimson as blood.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword\n\nThis wine is made using resin, darkening its color. It leaves the drinker feeling warmed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18246_ShortDesc", "Soup from a great beast\'s head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18246_LongDesc", "There is a very specialized school of divination magic that suggests the future can be divined in a broiled rhinoceros head. There are also hunters who swear the powder of a rhino horn will imbue a man with virility. The veracity of these claims is highly suspect. What is known is that a soup, boiled from the head of a rhino, will imbue the eater with greater power to carry a heavy load.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11057_ShortDesc", "The untreated skin of a beast")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11057_LongDesc", "The extremely thick hide of a Rhino
Sought after for their horns and skins, Rhinos are prized by hunters throughout Stygia.

Due to their aggressive nature many hunters are lost every year. Sometimes perhaps it is better to leave the Rhino with their skin, than risk losing your own.

Taken from any number of wild beasts, hide can be processed into leather using a tannery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82003_ShortDesc", "Rhino King Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82003_LongDesc", "The head of a Rhino King")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81003_ShortDesc", "Rhino King Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81003_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18315_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a rhinoceros")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18315_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling matter bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to a rhinoceros, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80962_ShortDesc", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80962_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At the edge of the desert, beyond the houses, there is a clump of palm trees, and within that grove there is a pit. And within that pit have been found human bones, charred and blackened. Not once, but many times!</> - Shdows in Zamboula

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.

It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90277_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90277_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90257_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90257_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90303_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90303_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Black Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90302_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90302_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90301_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90301_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.
Reinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90299_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90299_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90300_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90300_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.

Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90117_ShortDesc", "A sloping wallpiece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90117_LongDesc", "These walls are useful for filling out gaps left by odd building pieces.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13503_ShortDesc", "A cooked haunch of exotic meat ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13503_LongDesc", "Taken from one of the more unusual beasts of the Exiled Lands, this mouth-watering meat is the height of culinary grace in this savage land.\nIn the great palaces of the Hyborian kingdoms noblemen hold lavish feasts where the reek of intrigue and exotic meats fill the smoky air. The quests that their servants undertake - and the dangers that they face - to obtain the near-mythical fare is the stuff of epicurean legend.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18240_ShortDesc", "Bowlful of cooked mushrooms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18240_LongDesc", "Some mushrooms are poisonous, it is true, but many can be cooked into a culinary delight. Properly prepared, roasted mushrooms are good for the eater\'s health over time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80203_ShortDesc", "A slab of rock")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80203_LongDesc", "This rock slab serves the dual purpose of being both a place to sit and eat and a sacrificial altar. Entirely depending on the purpose to which it has been put, those stains on the surface are either bloodstains or gravy stains.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82008_ShortDesc", "Rocknose Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82008_LongDesc", "The head of a Rocknose")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81008_ShortDesc", "Rocknose Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81008_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18316_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a rocknose")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18316_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling matter bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to a rocknose, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13598_ShortDesc", "A stinking mass of black matter")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13598_LongDesc", "Whatever this once belonged to, it is now unrecognizable. Any occult properties it may have once possessed are probably expired.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80252_ShortDesc", "A round wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80252_LongDesc", "Useful for sitting and hurling at enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_ShortDesc", "A round wooden table")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88901_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82041_ShortDesc", "The head of a Sabretooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82041_LongDesc", "The head of a Sabretooth")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18317_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a sabretooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18317_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meat bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to sabretooths, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82042_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Sabretooth head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82042_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I am like a hunter who crouches by his small fire amid the forest, and hears stealthy feet padding in the darkness, and almost sees the glimmer of burning eyes.'</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved sabretooth tiger's head bespeaks of a hunter who can bring down a beast who would have happily devoured them in turn.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30017_ShortDesc", "Salaceo\'s Instructions")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30017_LongDesc", "On the EAST side of the Black hand Ship, there is an anchor.
From the Anchor, take 45 steps (walk don't run) NORTH
Turn EAST, take 50 steps, then turn SOUTH and take 25 more steps.
Finally, turn EAST and take 150 steps. 
There, hidden at the base of a mighty tree, is my chest.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82049_ShortDesc", "The head of a salamander")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82049_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82055_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Salamander head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82055_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18263_ShortDesc", "White, crystalline granules")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18263_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Nay, my men are sick to stretch their legs ashore, and nigh to scurvy from chewing salt pork.</> - The Black Stranger\n\nCivilization pivots around salt, communities forming, like growths, around sources of the stuff. Salt is mined, and it is boiled from salt-laden water. It flavors food. Sometimes, it serves as a form of currency. Perhaps most importantly, salt is the best know food preserver, especially for meat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18259_ShortDesc", "A small snack both savory and sweet")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18259_LongDesc", "A common food practice in Turan is to mix salt with certain sweet fruits. This snack, of salted berries, is both tasty and a little better preserved.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18287_ShortDesc", "A salted piece of meat with perfect texture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18287_LongDesc", "Salted to perfection, this meat will last.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18283_ShortDesc", "Salt and fat in a succulent combination")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18283_LongDesc", "A meal heavy with fat will stay in one\'s stomach, and keep them well fed for some time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80972_ShortDesc", "A sanctuary dedicated to the worship of Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80972_LongDesc", "Considered a good god, Mitra is worshipped throughout the Hyborian kings, replacing the worship of Bori from which those primitive tribes took their name.

Mitra's symbol is that of the phoenix, but when he is depicted it is in the form of a well built, bearded man. He abhors the bloody rituals of other religions and prefers for his followers to perform dignified, purification rituals.

Mitra's priests preach a monotheistic doctrine and as such their followers tend to persecute the members of other nearby religions. Due to this tendency, Chapels to Mitra cannot be built within a very long range of shrines to other gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80953_ShortDesc", "An altar to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80953_LongDesc", "Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine altar will not remain so for long. \nThe hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.\nAltars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18313_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a sand reaper")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18313_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling meats bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to sand reapers, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14102_ShortDesc", "Toxin gland taken from the monstrous reaper")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14102_LongDesc", "The Sand Reapers spit a venomous toxin that causes the skin to rot from the body on contact. Harvesting this toxin is a foolhardy but valuable undertaking.\nApplying this toxin to specially prepared grooved blades allows precise delivery of the toxin to enemies in melee.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14196_ShortDesc", "A bile gland taken from a supernatural creature")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14196_LongDesc", "When the sandstorm comes howling across the Exiled Lands, it is accompanied by the strange screams of the beasts that inhabit it. What they are and why they follow the storms is one of the many mysteries of the Exiled Lands. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_ShortDesc", "A square ceiling piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90003_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_ShortDesc", "A doorframe made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90004_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_ShortDesc", "A fence piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90010_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. 
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90020_ShortDesc", "A foundation for placing walls and fences")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90020_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_ShortDesc", "A square foundation piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90001_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting sandstone buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_ShortDesc", "A sandstone wall with space for a window")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90007_LongDesc", "Windows provide great vantage points for archers without forcing them to leave the safety of stout walls.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90284_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90284_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90009_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90306_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of sandstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90306_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90307_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of sandstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90307_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90005_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90069_ShortDesc", "Stairs of sandstone")
column4:

")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_ShortDesc", "A square wall piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90002_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90316_ShortDesc", "A wall made of Sandstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90316_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.\nA barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of sandstone ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90006_LongDesc", "Wedge shaped building pieces allow greater flexibility in the shapes available to builders.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90019_ShortDesc", "A square window piece made of sandstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90019_LongDesc", "Sandstone Window")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_ShortDesc", "A mask that filters out the sandstorm debris")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_LongDesc", "When the sandstorm wails across the Exiled Lands, the choices are to take cover from the scouring sands, or be blinded and eventually, killed.
This breather mask, crafted with very small slits for the eyes that keep out most of the debris while allowing visibility and a cloth mouthpiece that filters the air, allows free movement within the sandstorm.
What lies at the heart of the storm is one of the many mysteries of the Exiled Lands.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18208_ShortDesc", "Heaps and heaps of glorious meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18208_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Wolves prowled openly along the grass-grown highways, and bands of gaunt, masterless men slunk through the forests. Only in Tarantia was feasting and wealth and pageantry.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nLarge game, in quantity, make for a meal that would put an army of bellies glad. Such a meal offers good health to the eater.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18011_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18011_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from fish known for being good eating. It is easy to cook and full of flavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18232_ShortDesc", "Strips of succulent meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18232_LongDesc", "Many a hungry soul, when seeing a fine cut of meat from large game, desire to devour it all in one sitting. The wiser sort know when to ration off a bit and salt and dry it for hungrier nights ahead.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18021_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18021_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from shellfish known for being good eating. It is easy to cook and full of flavor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13002_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from common wild animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13002_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.
This flesh has been harvested from large game. It is easy to cook and full of flavour.
Unless this meat is cooked quickly, it will spoil and become inedible.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51827_ShortDesc", "A tool for sawing wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51827_LongDesc", "A tool specifically designed to enhance the user-experience of slaving away as a thrall. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18318_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a scorpion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18318_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling matter bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to scorpions, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30001_ShortDesc", "A note scrawled on flimsy paper")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30001_LongDesc", "I am beaten. Left to rot among the ruins of the past.
There are others here. Slaves, bandits and cannibals. Exiles from lands I've never heard of.
Some of them try to scrape a life from the wasteland, scrabbling in the rocks and sand for their own place.
I cannot go on. The life that I left behind haunts me. The sun over the glittering spires of Belverus is forever denied me. The smell of my daughter's hair...
I will pass the ghost fence and this cursed land will finally end me. 
To whoever reads this note, I leave the last of my water and this message.
Stranger, you have my pity. You do not know how cursed you truly are.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30004_ShortDesc", "A note speculating about the nature of strength")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30004_LongDesc", "What is strength? I find myself pondering that question more and more as the days turn.
I've seen strong, confident men killed because they tried to fight when they should have run away. I've 
seen those who people consider weak, sharing their food with others and gaining their gratitude and 
protection.
In the past, I was a blacksmith and I was considered the strongest man in my village. But I sold a sword 
to the wrong man, and ended up here.
And now that I am here, I see clearly that it is the things that I know - how to work the forge and the 
creation of weapons and tools - that carries true value.
Knowledge is strength. That is the lesson.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41032_ShortDesc", "A sealed leather skin for storing water")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41032_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Let him wait until we get to camp. It's only ten miles. If he's fit to live in the desert he'll live that long without a drink.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

Pitch has been used to seal this waterskin, slowing the inevitable leaks and keeping the water level stable. The addition of pitch, however, adds a nasty sulphurous aftertaste to the water.

The Zuagirs and other tribes of the eastern deserts of Shem have long had the practise of soaking the outside of their waterskins before a long journey. As water evaporates from the outside of the skin, it cools the contents. Some enterprising merchants have been known to use the same trick to chill their wines when on a long journey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18237_ShortDesc", "A soup of boiled seeds")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18237_LongDesc", "The bounty of plants are many, and a surplus of seeds can be turned into a filling soup.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13015_ShortDesc", "Small seeds taken from the foilage of the Exiled Lands")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13015_LongDesc", "These small seeds can be ground into a paste and made into a thin gruel. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80951_ShortDesc", "A shrine to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Ships did not put unasked into this port, where dusky sorcerers wove awful spells in the murk of sacrificial smoke mounting eternally from blood-stained altars where naked women screamed, and where Set, the Old Serpent, arch-demon of the Hyborians but god of the Stygians, was said to writhe his shining coils among his worshippers.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine shrine will not remain so for long. 

The hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.

Altars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14101_ShortDesc", "Venom swollen glands harvested from serpents")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14101_LongDesc", "The serpents of the Exiled Lands vary in the potency of their venom from mildly irritating to lethal. 
The use of serpent venom for coating weapons before battle is a myth. Venom needs to be injected directly into the blood to have an effect and the act of plunging a weapon into a body is a far more efficient way to damage foes than to wait for a slow acting venom.
Alchemists and healers, however, do tout the efficacy of ingesting small amounts of venom to build an immunity. It is said that King Yezdigerd of Turan ritually ingests small amounts of many different poisons to build his protection against assassination attempts.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51529_ShortDesc", "An arrow made in a blasphemous ancient style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51529_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51530_ShortDesc", "A bolt made in a blasphemous ancient style")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51313_ShortDesc", "A curved iron skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51313_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51517_ShortDesc", "A sword in a blasphemous ancient style")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51945_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51945_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_ShortDesc", "A Khopesh stamped with the symbol of the serpent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The common men of Stygia were not allowed to wear swords, and the mantle was not voluminous enough to hide the Cimmerian's long blade, but Conan buckled to his hip a Ghanta knife, a weapon borne by the fierce desert men who dwelt to the south of the Stygians, a broad, heavy, slightly curved blade of fine steel, edged like a razor and long enough to dismember a man.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

It is forbidden in the kingdom of Stygia for the common man to bear a sword, but the khopesh, particularly one that has taken part in the bloody rituals of Set, is allowed.

This khopesh appears to be made of steel, yet it is tinted the bronze color that Stygian ceremonial garb requires. The symbol engraved on the blade is the symbol of Set, the sacred serpent. Blades such as these are passed among the priesthood and given to those who show particular fervor when participating in the rites of blood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53503_ShortDesc", "A potent antidote to poison")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53503_LongDesc", "Set commands that his followers revere serpents above all creatures, even requiring that his devotees allow themselves to be devoured by the giant temple snakes if the creatures so desire. This reverence means that many priests are bitten by the venemous serpents that roam the stone temples. Rather than simply accept their fate at the hands of a petulant snake, the priests often keep a supply of this antidote handy. Created during the rituals of sacrifice from the hearts of humans, it is a literal trade of a life for a life and Set does not seem to hold any grudges against followers who spare themselves in this manner.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80504_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80504_LongDesc", "This small brazier, made of bronze worked into the shape of a serpent, is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set. \nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_ShortDesc", "A choker worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_LongDesc", "Crafted from the finest golds, this garment is light and supple. It molds pleasingly to the form and accentuates the chest. The mysteries of Set are not all blood and death - the ritual that depicts the coupling of Set with his mistress, Derkheto, has been described by Mitrean scholars as \"a blasphemous orgy of wine and blood.\" Though they always take the opportunity to vist any temple of Derkheto during such rites. For the purposes of research, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_LongDesc", "The dispassionate features of the serpent have been modeled and refined in this mask. It distorts the features of the wearer and brings them closer to the cold beauty of the serpents so beloved of their god.\nUsed primarily in rituals within the temple of Set, this mask nevertheless offers a certain level of protection for the face of the wearer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51902_ShortDesc", "A formal dagger used for ritualistic killings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51902_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> She has instituted human sacrifice, and since her mating with Constantius, no less then five hundred men, women and children have been immolated. Some of these have died on the altar she has set up in the temple, herself wielding the sacrificial dagger, but most have met a more horrible doom. </> - A Witch Shall be Born

The devotees of Set are spread far and wide in the lands of Stygia and the Old Serpent demands human sacrifice as a part of his worship.

These daggers are crafted in the thousands at the forges of Luxur and then spread to the priesthood of the Serpent god.

While the rituals of Set are many and depraved, the fastest is bending a victim over an altar and cutting their heart from their chest.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_ShortDesc", "A pair of sandals worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_LongDesc", "These ceremonial sandals were not designed for the harsh environment of the desert, but rather the stone floors of the temple. Runnng in sand wearing these is an uncomfortable experience and fighting in them is almost impossible due to poor balance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_ShortDesc", "A shendyt worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_LongDesc", "Woven silk edged with golden trim has been used to shape this ornamental shendyt. Worn by devotees of Set during their rituals, these shendyts are often stained in the blood of sacrifice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51625_ShortDesc", "A ceremonial shield dedicated to Set")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51625_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Among the rituals of the cult of Set, is the ability to render special properties into base metals. In particular, gold is much favored by the priests of Set to be used in the creation of these divine shields, which they claim will offer the blessings of Set.

Some have pointed out that the process which hardens the gold darkens it almost to the color of bronze, and that the specialized priests who perform the process often move on quickly to new cities and villages. But not too loudly. That would be blasphemous.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_ShortDesc", "A severed human arm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan rose, still smiling, as if to reach into a near-by cooking pot; then quick as a cat he struck Aja a terrible blow with the heavy bone. The Bakalah war-chief slumped over, his skull crushed in, and instantly a frightful yell rent the skies as the Bamulas went into action like blood-mad panthers.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

Once, this limb belonged to a dangerous criminal, but now he can be considered 'armless. It looks like a left arm though, so he is all right. He can stump his enemies by pretending to surrender. Still, this entire incident has made him half as handy as he used to be. 
At least from now on you'll be well armed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_ShortDesc", "A severed human leg")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan brained him with the beef bone, took his poniard and his keys, and made a leisurely departure.</> - Rogues in the House

This leg, severed from the corpse of an enemy, is bloodless and stiff. Carrying it around might not be a good way to make friends, but then again it might help to make a different kind of friend.
The important thing is that it can be used as a weapon. And beating someone to death with a limb is an itch that rarely gets scratched in civilized society.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81010_ShortDesc", "The decorative skeleton of a Shaleback Hatchling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81010_LongDesc", "Nothing says more about the owner of a building than their choice of furnishing. The clean-picked bones of this hatchling speak to the taste and sophistication of a person who would club a baby animal to death and then use it as a decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_ShortDesc", "The shell from a Shaleback Hatchling")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88891_LongDesc", "This shell, taken from a Shaleback Hatchling, is brittle and easily chipped. It cannot be used to make weapons or armor nor is it useful for potions or food. Essentially a baby Shaleback was killed for no reason. Way to go.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82013_ShortDesc", "The head of a Shaleback")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82013_LongDesc", "The head of a Shaleback")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81014_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Shaleback head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81014_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82014_ShortDesc", "The head of a Shaleback King")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82014_LongDesc", "The head of a Shaleback King")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81015_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Shaleback King head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81015_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16021_ShortDesc", "Shaped wood for construction")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16021_LongDesc", "It is possible to create basic weapons and items from branches collected from the ground, but any flaws in the wood quickly become apparent and such items break quickly.\nShaped wood is harvested wood that has been shaped by the carpenters hand to avoid structural weakness and provide additional resilience.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15515_ShortDesc", "A shattered piece of stone that pulses with power")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15515_LongDesc", "This is a piece of the legendary Scourgestone. But it is broken and must be reassembled by one who understands the power that it holds.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80695_ShortDesc", "A shelf for displaying objects")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80695_LongDesc", "This simple shelf can be placed against almost any wall and used to display small objects.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51500_ShortDesc", "A shield made from shaleback shell")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51500_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

The shell of the shaleback provides them with excellent protection against the elements and predators of the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable, though it tends to chip and flake in the midst of battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18503_ShortDesc", "A submersible cage used to catch shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18503_LongDesc", "Much of humanity\'s earliest exercises in cunning and ingenuity came from staring at the water and devising an easier way to catch fish. Submersible cages made from wooden boards, and sometimes a mesh of metal, are employed in the pursuit of tasty shellfish.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_ShortDesc", "A pair of Shemitish gloves")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91022_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91024_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91024_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88904_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying a shield")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88904_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11116_ShortDesc", "A shield frame required for crafting high end shields")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11116_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis frame is functional and will prevent shields from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51568_ShortDesc", "An extremely strong shield")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51568_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">In the swirling red chaos a terrible apparition suddenly appeared before Conan's rearing steed. It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loin-cloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood.</> - Black Colossus

Prince Kutamun of Stygia is a legendarily fearless warrior. His savage fury is well known among his subjects and he is rumored to be invincible in battle.

This shield, however, has never seen battle. Prince Kutamun does not deign to use a shield in battle and, despite the effort that his mother went to have this forged to keep her darling child safe, he refuses to use it.

This hurt the feelings of his overprotective mother. 

Don't blame me when somebody stabs you to death with a dagger then! she told him, tossing the shield on a rubbish pile, where it was promptly stolen by an urchin.

Equipping this shield will increase the armor value of the bearer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11114_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11114_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13501_ShortDesc", "Cooked scraps of feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13501_LongDesc", "Tough, chewy meat that spoils quickly. Preferential to scavenged foods or raw meat, this gamy meat is hard on the teeth and the palate.\nThe taverns of the great cities are known using this type of meat for stewing though in Shadizar it is more likely to be cat or rat scraps that find their way into the pot.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80971_ShortDesc", "A holy shrine dedicated to the worship of Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80971_LongDesc", "Considered a good god, Mitra is worshipped throughout the Hyborian kings, replacing the worship of Bori from which those primitive tribes took their name.

Mitra's symbol is that of the phoenix, but when he is depicted it is in the form of a well built, bearded man. He abhors the bloody rituals of other religions and prefers for his followers to perform dignified, purification rituals.

Mitra's priests preach a monotheistic doctrine and as such their followers tend to persecute the members of other nearby religions. Due to this tendency, Chapels to Mitra cannot be built within a very long range of shrines to other gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18007_ShortDesc", "May not be safe to eat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18007_LongDesc", "Mushrooms can be used to enhance an otherwide bland dish. Or poison it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18081_ShortDesc", "Smells kind of funny, but tastes ok")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18081_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The dullest was struck by the contrast between the harsh, taciturn, gloomy commander, and the pirate whose laugh was gusty and ready, who roared ribald songs in a dozen languages, guzzled ale like a toper, and?apparently?had no thought for the morrow.</> - The Pool of the Black One\n\nThere are those who like to put a little something extra in their drink. This beer adds particular strains of mushrooms to the brewing process. Some claim they receive visions in the night after such a draught, but these may just be the dreams of the drunk. This beer heats the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89851_ShortDesc", "Ammunition for the trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89851_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'No man living could throw that rock across this glade. It's a task for siege engines. Yet here there are no mangonels or ballistas.'</> - Shadows in the Moonlight

In the so-called civilized kingdoms of Hyboria, nobles build great palaces with walls of mighty stone to protect themselves from their enemies at court and abroad.

The solution to sturdy walls and cowardly nobility is the steadfast trebuchet. A machine of immense power, the trebuchet can be used to fling stones, corpses and even specially designed explosives.
Their weakness is their immobility, they cannot be easily moved once placed and finding the correct range and angle requires time and patience. With repeated use, it is almost certain that some or all of the pieces of the trebuchet will degrade and need to be replaced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_ShortDesc", "A cauldron attached to a simple lever")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90227_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Take your plots to hell with you!' he roared, and like a sack of salt, he hurled the prince of Pellia far out, to fall through empty space for a hundred and fifty feet. The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Crafting fortifications is the beginning of a coherent siege strategy but it is the least interesting and least creative part of the equation. A good fortification includes structures that are built for a specific purpose - such as murder holes created to lure enemies through a gauntlet of deadly traps.

These siege cauldrons, filled with boiling tar, are simply another tool in the arsenal of a siege engineer. They can be used to discourage eager climbers or to wreak havoc on enemies trapped in a murder hole.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_ShortDesc", "A foundation for building siege equipment")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He had sent his light riders, his spahis, inland to ravage the country, and had reared up his siege engines in the plain.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This foundation is designed to be a reinforced base for building siege engines that require stability as they are fired.

Siege engines require immense amounts of labor to craft and maintain. They are expensive to transport, and the working parts break often, requiring constant supervision.

It is undoubted, however, that beneath the gods themselves, they are one of the most powerful weapons available to any army.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52607_ShortDesc", "Ancient plated boots with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52607_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Crom, I do not like this place, where dead men rise, and sleeping men vanish into the bellies of shadows!</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

These eldritch boots bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the name of the Witch Queen.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52605_ShortDesc", "Ancient gauntlets with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52605_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Those eyes grew and became gigantic, and in them the Cimmerian glimpsed the reality of all the abysmal and blasphemous horrors that lurk in the outer darkness of formless voids and nighted gulfs.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These eldritch gauntlets bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper of the hybrid half-child of the humans and the Giant-kings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52603_ShortDesc", "An ancient helmet with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52603_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is sorcery - grisly black magic from the grim youth of the world. An awful shape has risen out of the shades of the Past, and none can stand before it.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This eldritch helm bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Deathbringer, Kinscourge, and Maimer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52604_ShortDesc", "An ancient chestpiece with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52604_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I have lain in your arms, panting with the violence of our love; you have held and crushed and conquered me, drawing my soul to your lips with the fierceness of your bruising kisses. My heart is welded to your heart, my soul is part of your soul! Were I still in death and you fighting for life, I would come back to the abyss to aid you--aye, whether my spirit floated with the purple sails on the crystal sea of paradise, or writhed in the molten flames of hell! I am yours, and all the gods and all their eternities shall not sever us!</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This eldritch chest armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Tyros and Telith.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52606_ShortDesc", "Ancient leg armor with a ghastly aura")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52606_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Wits and swords are as straws against the wisdom of the Darkness...</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This eldritch leg armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Klael the Warmaker, The Archivist, and the Priestking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12513_ShortDesc", "A strong, light thread spun from gossamer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12513_LongDesc", "Silk is a valuable commodity in the Hyborian kingdoms and it flows from Khitai in the east and Stygia in the south. Khitan silk is drawn from silkworms whereas Stygian silk is harvested from the giant spiders that inhabit the dark reaches of the southern lands.\nKhitan silk is prized for the clinging, sensual fabric that it creates. It is very tolerant of dyes and holds brilliant color. Any nobleman of note has at least one outfit of Khitan silk.\nStygian silk is stronger and more durable, offering greater protection at the cost of a coarser weave. Dyes tend to fade quickly but the tenacity of the fabric makes it a favorite among the merchant class.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90993_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90993_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11055_ShortDesc", "A soft metal ingot that can be polished to a deep shine")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11055_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Do you think he is dead?' she asked, with seeming irrelevancy.
He did not ask her to whom she referred.

'I believe so. Silver and fire are both deadly to evil spirits, and he got a belly-full of both.'</> - The Black Stranger
Too weak to create effective weapons, silver is primarily for currency, ornamentation and the backing of polished mirrors. 
Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.

This metal can be smelted and used to forge weapons, but any such weapon will break after anything more than a single hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90995_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90995_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90994_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90994_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11065_ShortDesc", "A silver coin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11065_LongDesc", "This coin is made of silver. \nThese coins are of dubious mercantile value but can probably be melted down to obtain base metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11067_ShortDesc", "A pouch of silver dust")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11067_LongDesc", "Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.\n\nSilver dust is used in alchemical potions to create a wide-range of effects.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90992_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90992_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11052_ShortDesc", "A chunk of ore flecked with silver fragments")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11052_LongDesc", "Too weak to create effective weapons, silver is primarily for currency, ornamentation and the backing of polished mirrors. 

Silver can be effective against demonic creatures and spirits. Many a mercenary always keeps a single silver coin with them to ward off curses and dark creatures.

This chunk of ore can be smelted and used to forge weapons, but any such weapon will break after anything more than a single hit.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41075_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for making armor more pliant and flexible")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41075_LongDesc", "Uri the Mastersmith once stated that creating an armor set was a balance of three forces - flexibility, strength and coverage. He claimed that in developing a suit of armor, you could have two of these things, but never three. He demonstrated this principle by crafting the King of Nemedia a suit of armor that made him completely impervious to assassins; but also left the King completely unable to move once encased within.
Uri was executed not long afterward.

This small kit contains tools for stretching leather and working metal joints to make them more pliable. 

Using this simple kit on an armor set will make it slightly more flexible when climbing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41020_ShortDesc", "A patch kit for repairing damaged armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41020_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan's dark scarred face was darker yet with passion; his black armor was hacked to tatters and splashed with blood; his great sword red to the cross-piece.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

A warrior needs to be able to rely on their armor in the heat of battle. When the broadswords swing, a layer of leather or steel can mean the difference between life and death.

This patch kit, containing scraps of metals, leather and hide, can be used to repair the most egregious insults to a piece of armor, though it will never be able to repair them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41072_ShortDesc", "A set of tools for improving the poise of a set of armor")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41072_LongDesc", "In Poitain, the shining southern province of Aquilonia, it is common for men to engage in contests of arms wearing full plate armor. And among those people it is commonly understood that a once a warrior falls in full plate, they will be battling to return to their feet.

This kit, developed by the smiths of that fair land, is designed to resettle the weight of the armor set such that it matches the wearers center of balance. This means less chance of falling in battle and more time spent on the feet.

This simple kit will increase the poise value of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41059_ShortDesc", "A blunted fitting that can be applied to a weapon to increase concussive damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41059_LongDesc", "Sometimes the best course in combat is not to defeat an enemy, but to see them humiliated and begging for mercy. Or dragged back to spend some time whimpering on the Wheel of Pain.

This fitting can be attached to almost any weapon and increases the chance of knocking an enemy out before they bleed to death.

Applying this simple fitting will increase the concussion damage of a weapon slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80210_ShortDesc", "A bundle of sharpened stakes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80210_LongDesc", "These makeshift bundles of sharpened wooden stakes are usually placed around mercenary camps and other temporary fortifications.\nNo sane soldier wants to charge an enemy who has ringed their camp with barricades such as these.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41064_ShortDesc", "A reinforcement that can be used to make weapons and armor more durable")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41064_LongDesc", "A warrior relies on their strength, their skill and their weapon to carry them in battle. If any of these are broken in the clash of swords, it puts life and limb at risk.

This reinforcement can be used to find the flaws in a weapon or piece of armor and buttress them against the storm of battle.

This simple reinforcement will increase the durability of a weapon or piece of armor slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80765_ShortDesc", "A simple tent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80765_LongDesc", "The Zuagir, a tribe of shemite nomads who roam the sands from Zamora to Zamboula, created these tents as a rather novel way to ride out the sandstorms which sweep the deserts of Hyboria.

Made of woven camel-hair, these tents are deployed quickly and with little fuss and are actually quite a comfortable place to ride out a sandstorm.

Sandstorms in the Exiled Lands contain more than just wind-blown sand and flying fragments. There are darker terrors against which woven camelhair may not prove particularly effective.

Once a tent is placed, gaining shelter is a simple as crouching inside it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41056_ShortDesc", "An assortment of upgrades to make tools more efficient")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41056_LongDesc", "There is wisdom among the simple peoples of the world; those who spend their time tilling, hunting, growing and harvesting.

The time-tested techniques for improving the harvesting capacity of tools have been distilled into the upgrades found in this kit.

Applying this simple upgrade to a tool will increase its harvesting capacity slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41052_ShortDesc", "A bag of unpleasant things that can be attached to weapons to increase their damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41052_LongDesc", "Some warriors adorn their weapons to intimidate their foes and make them a memorable presence on the battlefield.

But the collection of spikes and studs contained in this bag have a single purpose - to wreck foes. Whether hammer, sword, or spear - there is something here to bring ruination, laceration, and devastation to the bodies and minds of enemies everywhere.

Applying this simple kit to a weapon will increase its damage slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41024_ShortDesc", "A toolkit for repairing damaged weapons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41024_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He rushed in, hacking madly, but Conan, recognizing him, shattered his sword with a short terrific chop and with a powerful push of his open hand sent him reeling to the floor.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the fury of battle has subsided and the lightning clash of weapons has stilled, the victors are left to count the cost. And sometimes the price of battle is the very weapons that are used to wage it.

This kit, containing a whetstone, a hone and a small portion of blade oil, will allow even unskilled crafters to repair the worst damage to their blades, though it will never be able to renew them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden door")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90008_LongDesc", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88903_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88903_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80741_ShortDesc", "A decorative skeleton piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80741_LongDesc", "While tastes in interior design may vary, few visitors would complain about skeletal decoration pieces such as this. Mostly out of fear of being added to the owners bone collection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82017_ShortDesc", "The head of a Skeletal Serpentman")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82017_LongDesc", "The head of a Skeletal Serpentman")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81018_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Skeletal Serpentman head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81018_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11073_ShortDesc", "An ornate key that fits any number of chests")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11073_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The chest forged in unholy fires among the flaming mountains of Khrosha; the metal no chisel can cut. How many treasures has it borne, across the width and the breadth of the world! But no such treasure as it now holds.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nThis key is designed to fit a series of chests that are hidden across the breadth of the Exiled Lands. Rumor holds that they hold legendary treasures stolen from across the lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52008_ShortDesc", "Handwraps made of a thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52008_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These handwraps provide coverage against the warmth of the volcano, while allowing the hands to remain nimble enough to work the volcanic soil that clings to the caldera.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52007_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52007_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This hood covers the head and conceals the face, allowing the wearer to proceed with dark deeds in complete anonymity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52006_ShortDesc", "A robe of thick, dark material")
column4:
