NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52006_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

They dress in black robes which serve to protect them against the searing heat of the volcano where they make their home.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52009_ShortDesc", "A pair of thick leather sandals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52009_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These sandals offer good grip on the rough stone that covers the inside of the volcano. While they are not designed to withstand the extremes of the lava flows that run along the volcano floor, they still provide some protection against the scorching heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52010_ShortDesc", "A skirt of thick, dark material")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52010_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This skirt is often worn by cultists who work the volcanic soil to grow crops. The additional mobility provided by the skirt is useful for those who spend their days bending and crouching.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51153_ShortDesc", "A hammer created by Tsotha-lanti")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51153_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Of this Kothian wizard dark tales were told; tousle-headed women in northern and western villages frightened children with his name, and rebellious slaves were brought to abased submission quicker than by the lash, with threat of being sold to him. Men said that he had a whole library of dark works bound in skin flayed from living human victims, and that in nameless pits below the hill whereon his palace sat, he trafficked with the powers of darkness, trading screaming girl slaves for unholy secrets.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

There is a tale told that when the pits beneath the palace of Tsotha-lanti were being created, the work fell behind schedule. Tsotha-lanti demanded to know the reason for the delay and the trembling slave explained that they had encountered stone beneath the earth that was resistant to their hammers, which kept shattering on the hard stone.
Tsotha slew the unfortunate slave, and then passed the rest of the work gangs hammers through the blood, muttering an incantation. From that point onwards, the hammers smashed the stone easily and never seemed to chip or break.

When the work was complete, the hammers used disappeared and how they came to be where they are today is unknown.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51555_ShortDesc", "A hammer created by Tsotha-lanti")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51555_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Of this Kothian wizard dark tales were told; tousle-headed women in northern and western villages frightened children with his name, and rebellious slaves were brought to abased submission quicker than by the lash, with threat of being sold to him. Men said that he had a whole library of dark works bound in skin flayed from living human victims, and that in nameless pits below the hill whereon his palace sat, he trafficked with the powers of darkness, trading screaming girl slaves for unholy secrets.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

There is a tale told that when the pits beneath the palace of Tsotha-lanti were being created, the work fell behind schedule. Tsotha-lanti demanded to know the reason for the delay and the trembling slave explained that they had encountered stone beneath the earth that was resistant to their hammers, which kept shattering on the hard stone.

Tsotha slew the unfortunate slave, and then passed the rest of the work gangs hammers through the blood, muttering an incantation. From that point onwards, the hammers smashed the stone easily and never seemed to chip or break.

When the work was complete, the hammers used disappeared and how they came to be where they are today is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11111_ShortDesc", "A manifestation of unfulfilled desire")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11111_LongDesc", "The priests and priestesses of Derketo are well trained in the skills of pleasure and pain. They walk their congregations down an exquisite line between release and ecstasy, and their sweat-filled temples are filled with the moans and exultations of those who know the touch of the goddess.\n\nSuch pleasure, both fulfilled and unfulfilled, leaves a physical residue. The worshippers of Derketo offer it up to their goddess as proof that her bidding is being done on this earth.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53548_ShortDesc", "A mixture for removing warpaints")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53548_LongDesc", "Some part alcohol, some part water, this fluid is used to remove warpaints in times of peace and quiet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80721_ShortDesc", "A blue patterned Stygian banner")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80721_LongDesc", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80670_ShortDesc", "A small wooden barrel")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80670_LongDesc", "Used for long term storage or long haul transportation of goods, the sturdy barrel can be found in wagons, storehouses and taprooms.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80208_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80208_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80209_ShortDesc", "A wooden crate for storage")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80209_LongDesc", "A box made out of wood, as found in many a market. Crates allow large quantities of storage but being made solely out of wood, are much weaker than their strongbox and chest counterparts.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80771_ShortDesc", "A small, shabby shadecloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80771_LongDesc", "This motheaten shadecloth has seen better days. But shade is shade.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13014_ShortDesc", "A bite sized scorpion snack with extra sting")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13014_LongDesc", "A hard crunchy shell with a soft, satisfying center. These are considered a delicacy in some cultures.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53651_ShortDesc", "Venomous snakes transformed into deadly arrows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53651_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Better if steel and bowstring prevail without further aid from the arts, for the constant use of mighty spells sometimes sets forces in motion that might rock the universe.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_70001_ShortDesc", "A small idol depicting Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_70001_LongDesc", "Worshippers of Set are aware that displeasing their god can mean an altar and a blood drenched knife in their future. In order to keep the dictates of Set constantly on their minds, devotees place small statues around their dwellings to remind them of the precepts of the Old Serpent.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51467_ShortDesc", "A powerful set of daggers blessed by Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51467_LongDesc", "Rumored to be fangs that were shed by the great serpent himself, this matched set of carved daggers have been passed by archpriest to archpriest for centuries. They are stained to the hilt in the blood of sacrifice - glorious sacrifice in the name of Set.\nThese are sacred weapons, imbued with the blessing of a deity. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51570_ShortDesc", "A long-forgotten burial shield")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51570_LongDesc", "Warmth emanates from the surface of this shield and heats the arm of any who hold it.  Nothing is known of who crafted the shield, or by what strange sorceries it remains warm on even the coldest of days.\n\nJust some runes in ancient Atlantean, spelling out the name. Equipping this shield gives a boost to cold protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18224_ShortDesc", "A hearty bowl of broth and other bits of food")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18224_LongDesc", "When one has a fresh bone and water and a few other odds and ends left over, they have enough to make a satisfying soup.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11119_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11119_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18264_ShortDesc", "Powdered, exotic flavors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18264_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Some vagrant scent of spice or palm woke clear-etched images of strange coasts where mangroves grew and drums thundered, of ships locked in battle and decks running blood, of smoke and flame and the crying of slaughter...</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nTaken from the seeds, fruit, roots, and bark of plants, spices are used in cooking, medicine, and the arcane arts. These potent flavors hailed from the east, from Turan, Vendhya, and far away Khitai. The insatiable desire of Stygians to procure spices for their mummification rituals expanded trade along the continent. Flavoring one\'s food with spice warms the soul for a time.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18253_ShortDesc", "Zesty scraps of feral meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18253_LongDesc", "One of the best uses for strong spice is to improve the flavor of gamey meat, shredded to make up for this chewy toughness. Tavern owners share a proverb: \'A dead rat and a jar of spice will get you a lot further in life than just a dead rat.\' This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18255_ShortDesc", "Zesty cooked eggs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18255_LongDesc", "Eggs can be livened up with the right spices. This dish warms the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18288_ShortDesc", "A spiced piece of meat with perfect texture")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18288_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18217_ShortDesc", "A zesty haunch of exotic meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18217_LongDesc", "There are clubs and cliques among the elite nobles of Zingara that pride themselves on devouring exotic fare. The rarest of meals. There are rumors such organizations employ warlocks simply to summon otherworldly horrors, just so the dinner guests may dine on its spectral flesh. Whatever the truth, they do enjoy spicing their meats until they pleasantly heat the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18219_ShortDesc", "Cooked and zesty oysters")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18219_LongDesc", "Any Zingaran buccaneer will swear to a very specific regimen before a night of passionate romance:  to devour a dozen spiced oysters in quick succession. This seafood heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18284_ShortDesc", "Zesty slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18284_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18248_ShortDesc", "Zesty meat wrapped in crocodile skin")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18248_LongDesc", "It is said that pirates from the Black Coast created this delicacy by wrapping strips of meat in crocodile skin, heavily spicing the concoction, and then cooking it all until it is crackling crisp. This dish heats one\'s pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18235_ShortDesc", "A zesty soup")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18235_LongDesc", "Zingarans are known for making a spicy soup that puts a little fire in one\'s belly, heating the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18231_ShortDesc", "Zesty slab of succulent meat")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18231_LongDesc", "There are those who like the natural taste of the meat, cooked rare so that one\'s teeth still draw blood. And there are those who prefer to inundate their meat with all manner of spices. This dish heats the pallet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18227_ShortDesc", "A zesty brew")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18227_LongDesc", "Strong tea, steeped with potent spices, can drastically refresh one\'s stamina while heating the body and mind. Turanian guards who draw the late shift are said to be quite fond of this drink on cold, desert nights.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18319_ShortDesc", "A lure intended to draw a spider")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18319_LongDesc", "A bundle of urine-soaked hides and foul-selling matter bound in lengths of twine. While the ingredients were chosen specifically to appeal to spiders, they are nauseating to a human.\n\nLures can be equipped and thrown like any other throwing weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80171_ShortDesc", "This spike can be decorated with various skulls")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80171_LongDesc", "This sharpened wooden spike, once placed, waits patiently for something to be impaled upon it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80912_ShortDesc", "A pressure sensitive floor panel that releases sharpened spikes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80912_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Not the gray lotus, this time, but something just as effective. Nearly every chamber in my house is a trap.</> - Rogues in the House

Honest people defend their homes with stout walls and strength of arms. But devious people know that once a wall is breached, their enemy will be off guard. There are many traps that can be concealed within the walls and floor of a keep and thieves and conquerors alike would do well to keep their wits about them.

Nabonidus, the Red Priest, is rumoured to have filled his mansion with traps to kill the assassins and thieves which came to rob him of life and loot respectively. Ultimately they proved ineffective, as he was found murdered in his own mansion one morning, just inches from the trigger to one of his own traps.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41067_ShortDesc", "A spiked fitting that can be applied to a weapon to increase armor penetration")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41067_LongDesc", "When an opponent is covered in a layer of solid steel, it can be hard to find weak locations to strike. This modification solves that problem by providing the fastest way .\n\nApplying this fitting will increase the armor penetration of a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51559_ShortDesc", "A bow that fires arrows which always break")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51559_LongDesc", "A peasant from Koth was tired of mercenary troops riding across his fields on their way to war. He went out to confront them, with a simple bow made of a bent branch and arrows of simple twigs.

They laughed when he politely asked them to ride around his fields. One of them kicked him into the mud.

Humiliated, he levelled his bow at the leader. And fired. The twig flew straight and true, striking the mercenary leader in the breastplate, right above his heart.

The twig shattered, but before the mercenaries could react, a sharp splinter flew up and lodged itself it the mercenary leader's eye.

They slaughtered the peasant, of course. But the bow somehow made it to the Exiled Lands.

This bow cannot penetrate armor at all, but it does very high damage on impact.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13597_ShortDesc", "Gruel that has turned green")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_13597_LongDesc", "The only thing more disgusting than gruel, is spoiled gruel. This lumpy mixture of mold and clustered clumps of debris should not be eaten. By anything.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80251_ShortDesc", "A simple wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80251_LongDesc", "Sometimes after a day of killing and slaying, all an Exile wants to do is sit down and relax.\nStools are often used as makeshift weapons in tavern brawls across Hyboria, usually hurled at an opponent in between curses.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15505_ShortDesc", "A staff topped with a serpentine skull")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15505_LongDesc", "This staff, found in the acid pit alongside the Abysmal Remnant, is marked with an ancient language. The first runs along the length of the staff in glowing runes, whereas the second is carved rudely over the top of the first script, obscuring pieces of it.

While unintelligible at first glance, beneath the glow of the bracelet, the runes shape themselves into a recognizable script that reads:

"A gift from the ...B... give us advice ...E... and allow us to control the ...T... must be brought ...R... The Tower of the Bat where ...A... placed on the altar ...Y... awakened to share with us ...E... only awakened by ...R... and their blood."

Reading the script is one thing, understanding what it means is something else entirely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80501_ShortDesc", "A tall torch that can be placed in the ground")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80501_LongDesc", "A large torch that can be placed in the ground to create light in an area. Some use these as beacons, to light their way home on the darkest of nights.\nIn the Exiled Lands, the torches of the Darfari Cannibals are prominent in the darkness. In their camps, the cannibals dance madly to the throbbing of skin-covered drums and their frenzy amongst the flickering light of torch and cookfire seems oddly appropriate.\nThese torches can be lit and unlit without fuel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_ShortDesc", "Arrows with heads forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53656_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Now arrows fly between the hosts like stinging clouds that hide the sun.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

A well-made arrow can be the difference between a hit and a miss.

There is very little that can defend a target from such an exquisitely made arrow. But star metal is precious and rare, and not always available.

Arrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18061_ShortDesc", "An alloy created from the mysterious star metal ore")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18061_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'All substance is one to him who holds the key of the cosmos\' he said cryptically. \'To an adept nothing is immutable. At will steel blossoms bloom in unnamed gardens, or flower-swords flash in the moonlight.\'</> - The People of the Black Circle\n\nThis fallen metal from the sky, be it a gift from the gods or a curse from the wells of night, has mysterious properties that sages and sorcerers are only beginning to understand. This strange material is not as easy to work with as earthly metals, but those of esoteric skill have devised a way to smelt star metal ore, with a technique that employs brimstone and black ice, to create ingots.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53657_ShortDesc", "Crossbow bolts with heads forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53657_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan bounded back from the waving bills and his leap carried him outside the ring of his foes, to where Arus stood fumbling at his crossbow. A savage kick in the belly dropped him, green faced and gagging, and Conan's sandalled heel crunched square in the watchman's mouth.</> - The God in the Bowl

Without bolts, a crossbow is just a really poorly shaped club.

Bolts of start metal pass through armor like a heated knife through tallow.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51586_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Star Metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51586_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41030_ShortDesc", "A cleaver forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41030_LongDesc", "Hunters in the wild use whatever they have available to butcher their kills and the results are often less than perfect.

The cleaver, a tool perfected by butchers for slicing through flesh, muscle, ligaments and bone, allows the luxury of harvesting more useable flesh from every creature killed. And removing heads without damaging them.

Just don't try to use it as a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51967_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51967_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">When I was a fighting-man, the kettle-drums they beat; The people scattered gold-dust before my horse's feet; But now I am a great king, the people hound my track; With poison in my wine-cup, and daggers at my back.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These impossibly sharp daggers are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51063_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51063_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Something came writhing up the steps, something that slithered and rustled and brought a chill in the air with it. Conan lashed down with his great sword and felt the blade shear through something that might have been flesh and bone, and cut deep into the stair beneath.</> - Red Nails

This impossibly sharp great sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51159_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51159_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This devastating hammer is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51015_ShortDesc", "An axe of Star Metal for chopping wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51015_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Then his manner changed again, with lightning-like abruptness; he recoiled with a startled curse, knife and hatchet flashing as they leaped to positions of defense.</> - The Black Stranger

One need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unwieldy weapons.

Constructed from superior materials, and marked with intricate designs, this hatchet is as much a display of workmanship as a tool for cutting wood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51081_ShortDesc", "A mace forged from mysterious Star Metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51081_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This mace is forged of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

This mace is exquisitely balanced, the metal forged with the perfect ratio of weight to power in mind. It gives off a satisfying whoosh as it passes through the air, as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18060_ShortDesc", "Both stone and metal from other the heavens")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18060_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'This is a grisly thing,\' shuddered the clerk. \'It\'s too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world? It seems less destructible than Aquilonian steel, yet see how it is corroded and eaten away in spots.\'</> - The God in the Bowl\n\nThis ore, fallen from the sky, is a gift from the firmament. Put it to your ear and it practically hums with cosmic secrets like the ocean in a seashell.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51023_ShortDesc", "A pick forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51023_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The acolytes seemed to be following this thread, and there suddenly came to him Khemsa's cryptic words - 'Follow the golden vein!' On the brink, under his very hand as he crouched, he found it - a thin vein of sparkling  gold running from an outcropping of ore to the edge and down, across the silvery floor.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Tools made from material are preternaturally strong, able to break rocks of adamantine toughness.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51469_ShortDesc", "Heavy, unwieldy hammer for repairing structures")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51469_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Khosatral Khel rose and lived and waxed mighty once more. It pleased him to restore the city as it was in the days before its fall.</> - The Devil in Iron

Crafted for utility, this hammer is an unwieldy tool when used for anything other than pounding on stone or wood.

It is inevitable that time, the elements, and the beasts of the Exiled Lands will take their toll on structures. With the repair hammer and the correct combination of materials, almost anything can be repaired with a few hefty swings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51631_ShortDesc", "A shield forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51631_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

This impossibly durable shield is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51042_ShortDesc", "A sickle forged from mysterious star metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51042_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula\n\nSickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51312_ShortDesc", "A curved star metal skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51312_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51723_ShortDesc", "A spear with a head forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51723_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They met like a thunderclap. The Nemedian's lance, striking his foe's helmet, snapped bolts and rivets and tore off the casque, revealing the features of Pallantides. But the Aquilonian's lance-head crashed through shield and breast-plate to transfix the baron's heart.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This impossibly sharp spear has a head made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Spears are two-handed weapons with an ungainly tall wooden haft, but their reach is second to none.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51069_ShortDesc", "A sword forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51069_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'This day you become knights!' he laughed fiercely, pointing with his dripping sword towards the hillmen horses, herded nearby. 'Mount and follow me to hell!'</> - Black Colossus

This impossibly sharp sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_ShortDesc", "An axe forged from star metal and balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a queen by fire and steel and slaughter...</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly sharp throwing axe is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15511_ShortDesc", "A gleaming jewel on an ornate pin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15511_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">So you could steal from him the only thing he would never give you -- the ring with the jewel men call the Star of Khorala -- the star stolen from the queen of Ophir, who would pay a roomful of gold for its return. He would not give it to you willingly, because he knew that it holds a magic which, when properly controlled, will enslave the hearts of any of the opposite sex.</> - Shadows in Zamboula

The Star of the Champion is a gem of unsurpassed beauty - glowing with a white light that sets the world to shimmering. 

Once, in the ancient past, it was awarded to Tyros the Deathbringer for becoming the champion of the Giant-kings arena. 

In his final battle, he was to fight the mightiest dragon created by the Giant-kings, a magnificent creature of enormous stature. Tyros defeated the beast, but in his victory, he saw the death of something noble and he wept. He pinned the Star of the Champion to the corpse of the creature - and the might beast was buried right there, beneath the sands of the arena.

Later, when Tyros was cursed with immortality, the dragon inherited the curse and rose again to stalk the arena.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that radiates holy light")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80976_LongDesc", "It is said that the lights on these statues will burn eternally as long as Mitra has a single faithful follower. It can be argued, of course, that a single faithful follower of Mitra would also keep the light burning to perpetuate the mysteries of Mitra and therefore create a paradox which has theologians everywhere going to sleep each night with a sore head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_ShortDesc", "A statue in the image of Mitra that pours forth water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80975_LongDesc", "Through the mysteries of Mitra it is possible to call water to well forth eternally. This affirmation of Mitra\'s power is marred somewhat by those who claim that the worshippers of Mitra only build these over pre-existing streams.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80757_ShortDesc", "A carved statue to Ymir")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80757_LongDesc", "While individual Nordheimer clans may worship different minor deities, Ymir is considered the chief of all gods. The god of Storm and War is said to send his daughter Atali to fetch the souls of dead and dying warriors to fill the halls of Valhalla.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18230_ShortDesc", "Slice of meat and sizzling eggs")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18230_LongDesc", "When one can spare a cut of succulent meat, a breakfast of eggs becomes a heartier meal that makes the heart happy and the belly more than full.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90989_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90989_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11502_ShortDesc", "An alloy that is stronger and less brittle than iron")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11502_LongDesc", "Barring some enchantment, steel is the strongest metal alloy available for the construction of weapons. The crafting of steel requires iron and Steelfire, a peculiar additive made from Tar and Brimstone.\nThe smiths of Akbitana in Shem are the finest in the world and a weapon made of Akbitanan steel is considered to be unbreakable. Due to their great demand, it is rare to find a Akbitanan weapon outside of Shem.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90991_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90991_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90990_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90990_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41028_ShortDesc", "A cleaver made from steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41028_LongDesc", "Hunters in the wild use whatever they have available to butcher their kills and the results are often less than perfect.

The cleaver, a tool perfected by butchers for slicing through flesh, muscle, ligaments and bone, allows the luxury of harvesting more useable flesh from every creature killed. And removing heads without damaging them.

Just don't try to use it as a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90988_ShortDesc", "A piece of delicate craftsmanship")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90988_LongDesc", "This piece of jewelry is purely ornamental and offers no bonus to the wearer. Well perhaps a slight amount of charisma, but this isn?t that type of game.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51013_ShortDesc", "An axe of strengthened steel for chopping wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51013_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Then his manner changed again, with lightning-like abruptness; he recoiled with a startled curse, knife and hatchet flashing as they leaped to positions of defense.</> - The Black Stranger

One need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unwieldy weapons.

Constructed from superior materials, and marked with intricate designs, this hatchet is as much a display of workmanship as a tool for cutting wood.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51621_ShortDesc", "A heater shield of beaten steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51621_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> Black Collossus

Usable by both infantry and cavalry, the heater shield is known for its unique shape and large area of protection.

As a defensive material, there is very little than can match the quality of steel. The additional weight is worth the extra protection.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51206_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51206_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51305_ShortDesc", "A mace of shining steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51305_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes.

Though it bears no makers-mark, this mace is excellently balanced and made of strong steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51003_ShortDesc", "A reinforced steel pick that is hard enough to mine anything")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51003_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I know him not,' he answered. 'He is mad to say I hired him. Let him take his just desserts. He has a strong back and the toil in the mines will be well for him.'</> - The God in the Bowl

The pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads.
Created in the fires at the burning heart of the forge and wrought in ornate patterns as it cooled, this pick is strong and durable. It almost seems a shame to waste it on rocks.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_ShortDesc", "A pair of sharp-bladed off-hand daggers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan did not reply; he merely stood and glared at her with his burning eyes, testing the edge of his poniard with a callused thumb.</> - Rogues in the House

While all poniards are capable of fast stabbing attacks with their venom coated blades, the extra strength of a steel poniard means that it can also be used to parry the attacks of enemies.

Using a poniard to parry requires more skill than a shield, but if successful such a parry will leave the enemy open for counter attack. Poniards are the off-hand weapon of choice in Zingaran duels for exactly this reason.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16003_ShortDesc", "A steel frame used to reinforce stonebrick walls.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16003_LongDesc", "The weakness of stone lies in the spaces between the bricks themselves and the materials that bind them together. This reinforcement, crafted of steel, helps to create a solid frame for the stones.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51470_ShortDesc", "Heavy, unwieldy hammer for repairing structures")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51470_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Khosatral Khel rose and lived and waxed mighty once more. It pleased him to restore the city as it was in the days before its fall.</> - The Devil in Iron

Crafted for utility, this hammer is an unwieldy tool when used for anything other than pounding on stone or wood.

It is inevitable that time, the elements, and the beasts of the Exiled Lands will take their toll on structures. With the repair hammer and the correct combination of materials, almost anything can be repaired with a few hefty swings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51040_ShortDesc", "A sickle made from steel")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51040_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The blade glinted in the starlight, and blood spurted.</> - The Man-Eaters of Zamboula

Sickles are one-handed tools sporting a crescent-shaped blade. Made for harvesting crops, such a tool can just as easily sheer flesh and bone and reap a bloody bounty.

Forged of hardened steel, this sickle's blade shows the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51310_ShortDesc", "A curved steel skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51310_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51209_ShortDesc", "A spear with a steel head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51209_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">- Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51201_ShortDesc", "A steel axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51201_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51721_ShortDesc", "A heavy, three pronged spear")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51721_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Spears! he muttered. What a blasted fool I am not to have thought of that before! That shows what a pretty woman does to a man's mind.</> - Red Nails

Originally used for fishing along the Argossean coastline, the flamboyant gladiator Aros of Koth decided to adopt the trident as his signature weapon.

The extremely broad head of the weapon makes it top heavy and too thick to be used in a shield wall while the barbed prongs are prone to getting caught on armor and flesh. 

The trident is best used against large creatures where stopping power is more important than precision. Aros of Koth discovered this the hard way, earning renown and fortune for taking down the Beast Lizard of Messantia, but then being killed in a later encounter with a swarm of Darfari Cannibals.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51307_ShortDesc", "A weighted club for knocking out foes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51307_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he stumbled over a corpse, and a bludgeon knocked the dented helmet from his head; the next instant the club fell full on his unprotected skull.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Used by watchmen and criminals alike, the truncheon is designed for incapacitating enemies without killing them.

Shemitish slavers have been known to waylay travelers leaving taverns in the meadowland cities and expertly knocking them out. The poor wretches awaken the next day in a wagonful of other captives with sore heads, on their way to the slave markets of the east.

It takes a great deal of experimentation to understand how to hit an enemy just hard enough to knock them out without smashing their skull.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51154_ShortDesc", "A steel Warhammer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51154_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The sheer weight of his shackles would have slain a lesser man with exhaustion. The locks that held band and chain were massive affairs that a sledge-hammer could hardly have dinted.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Forged of steel, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Steel weapons are the standard in the civilized kingdoms of Hyboria and savages find themselves at a distinct disadvantage when they find themselves pitting weapons of stone or wood against hardened steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14173_ShortDesc", "A volatile mix of tar and brimstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14173_LongDesc", "An unfortunate smith in Khoraja found himself homeless when his premises burned to the ground. Unable to explain the fire or its root cause, he nevertheless noticed that the steel he had been working on had survived the fire intact and was hardened beyond any metal that he had worked with before.\nBeing a cautious man, he experimented with different variations of the equipment in his newly rebuilt smithy until he reached the conclusion that tar from his poorly sealed roof had dripped into his bloomery and tainted the brimstone that he was using as a catalyst.\nHe gave his new catalyst the fanciful name of Steelfire and made a great deal of money before other smiths were able to replicate his results.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10001_ShortDesc", "Roughly hewn chunk of stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10001_LongDesc", "Most humble of materials and most common, stone is the building block of civilization. From the primitive weapons of Picts to the marble sheathed palaces of Aquilonian Kings, stone is the foundation upon which all is predicated.\nEven the elder races, who vanished from the earth without a trace, left behind great ruined cities of brooding stone to mark their passing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41034_ShortDesc", "A crudely crafted cleaver")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41034_LongDesc", "Hunters in the wild use whatever they have available to butcher their kills and the results are often less than perfect.

The cleaver, a tool perfected by butchers for slicing through flesh, muscle, ligaments and bone, allows the luxury of harvesting more useable flesh from every creature killed. And removing heads without damaging them.

Just don't try to use it as a weapon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51301_ShortDesc", "A lump of stone on a stick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51301_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> She saw clubs swing and descend with brutal force on kinky heads. Brands were kicked out of the fires, scattering sparks; hut-thatches smoldered and blazed up.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

A simple arrangement of sticks and stones equally useful for bashing in skulls and breaking bones.

Yoggites believe that rending the flesh of their sacrifices causes great offence to their god. Thus they favour blunt weapons when capturing sacrifices to be dragged screaming to their flesh pits. 

Though stone itself can survive for aeons, the bindings on any stone weapon have little chance of lasting through more than a single battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16001_ShortDesc", "A mixture for hardening stone pieces")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_16001_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands stand as a testament to the efficacy of weather at destroying the works of man. When the wind howls across the landscape and the sand scours everything in its path, there are few buildings that survive for very long.\nHowever, the supernaturally large insects of the Exiled Lands have developed a natural secretion that helps to protect them against the environment. \nIchor from these creatures, when soaked into twine and bound to a stone surface, can be placed into a furnace and hardened into bricks that provide excellent protection against the rigors of the Exiled Lands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51011_ShortDesc", "An axe of sharpened stone for chopping wood")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51011_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> There are tools in your fort, and plenty of trees in yonder forest.</> - The Black Stranger

One need only see the smoke curling from the chimneys of hamlets across the Thurian continent to understand the ubiquity of the humble hatchet. Gathering wood for cooking and construction are a part of daily life and the hatchet serves admirably for this purpose. Primarily used to hack down trees and fallen logs, hatchets can also be used in combat though they make unwieldy weapons.

This stone hatchet, crafted of a sharp rock jammed into the wedge of a fallen branch, will probably last a few swings when gathering wood before it reverts to its original components.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51152_ShortDesc", "A crude two-handed stone hammer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51152_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> His devotees died about that tomb in a crimson holocaust, but the barbarians could not burst the door, nor ever mar the structure by maul or fire.</> - Black Colossus

Crudely put together using a long branch and a large, heavy stone, this weapon will deteriorate quickly with use.

Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51001_ShortDesc", "A stone pick for mining sandstone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51001_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\"> For a cataclysmic instant the sky seemed to rain shards of marble. Then a rubble of shattered stone lay whitely under the moon.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThe pick is one of the simplest tools known to man. Used extensively in mines across Hyboria to split rocks and, if necessary, split heads. This pick is made of crude stone crudely attached to a scavenged branch and cannot be expected to last very long before falling apart. Still, only a fool would try to mine stone with their bare fists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51715_ShortDesc", "A dubiously crafted stone pike")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51715_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Well, the folk of the city can't help us just now. And they might not, if they could. The people of the Black Countries are generally hostile to strangers. Probably stick us full of spears.</> - Red Nails

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

This pike is heavy on one end and difficult to aim. The scavenged materials used in its manufacture will deteriorate quickly, making this a thrust-and-bust weapon.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51308_ShortDesc", "A curved stone skinning knife")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51308_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There's more than one way of skinning a panther.</> - Red Nails

Any warrior will tell you that a dagger balanced for battle is not designed to be used for skinning animals, though it will do in a pinch.
This skinning knife has a sharpened edge designed to easily split tendon, scrape flesh and free hides in a single piece. 

Using such a knife has the advantage of providing more hides with less effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51594_ShortDesc", "A dubiously crafted stone spear")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51594_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_ShortDesc", "A blunt, brittle sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> In the old free days, all I needed was a sharp sword and a straight path to my enemies. </> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This sword, created by binding a pair of sharpened stones to a hardwood branch, is unwieldy and unbalanced. More akin to a club than an actual bladed weapon, it will nevertheless be a capable tool for those trained in its use.

In the ice-locked lands north of Vanaheim and Asgard, adventurers tell of a tribe of man-apes who speak in the fashion of men and fashion rough weapons from stone and ice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80281_ShortDesc", "A throne made of stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80281_LongDesc", "Unlike other chairs, a throne gives the one who sits in it authority above and beyond that of an ordinary man.\nBattles have always been fought for this kind of power, and they always will be.\nSitting on a throne of any kind will increase confidence and prowess for a period.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51946_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51946_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_ShortDesc", "A ceiling piece of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90103_LongDesc", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials - from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_ShortDesc", "A doorframe of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90104_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_ShortDesc", "A low fence of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90110_LongDesc", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90120_ShortDesc", "A fence foundation of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90120_LongDesc", "Fence foundations can be placed in locations where fences and walls are needed, but the larger foundations of a building do not need to be placed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_ShortDesc", "A square-shaped Stonebrick foundation")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90101_LongDesc", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_ShortDesc", "A frame made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90107_LongDesc", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_ShortDesc", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90122_LongDesc", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_ShortDesc", "Framework for a large gate")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90121_LongDesc", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90285_ShortDesc", "A hatch frame made of stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90285_LongDesc", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.

A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.

The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_ShortDesc", "A pillar made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90109_LongDesc", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90308_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90308_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90309_ShortDesc", "A ramp made out of stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90309_LongDesc", "When moving huge wheeled wagons filled to the brim with rare resources, luxury goods or even slaves, ramps are much preferred over stairs, for self-evident reasons.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90078_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90078_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90105_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90105_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_ShortDesc", "Stairs made of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90070_LongDesc", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built - if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_ShortDesc", "A wall of Stonebrick")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90102_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90317_ShortDesc", "A wall made of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90317_LongDesc", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.\nA barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped piece of Stonebrick")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90106_LongDesc", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90111_ShortDesc", "A wedged shaped Stonebrick foundation")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90111_LongDesc", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18509_ShortDesc", "A stone cooking surface")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18509_LongDesc", "Cooking brought indoors. Whereas cooking on a campfire merely involved throwing food on a pan and letting it burn, now the art of food preparation can become more complex and varied.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51580_ShortDesc", "A strangely familiar battle-axe ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51580_LongDesc", "This axe looks familiar. Thought it is not easy to place it, the shape of the blade, the width of the haft and even the smell of the metal are like old friends.\n\nCarrying this axe is like having an old friend around, together anything can be overcome.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51198_ShortDesc", "A studded mace of unadorned iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51198_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11117_ShortDesc", "A strengthened length of string required for crafting high end bows and crossbows")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11117_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis length of string is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80744_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80744_LongDesc", "This small brazier is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80750_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80750_LongDesc", "This small brazier is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80749_ShortDesc", "A stygian instrument")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80749_LongDesc", "Typically found on board Stygian slave ships, the designs for these drums have seemingly made it into the sweltering desert.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80747_ShortDesc", "A piece of Stygian earthenware")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80747_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88897_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88897_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88898_ShortDesc", "A shaped earthenware jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88898_LongDesc", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80701_ShortDesc", "A free standing Stygian flag")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80701_LongDesc", "Moth eaten and ragged, this flag is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_ShortDesc", "A headdress popular among Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_LongDesc", "It is rumoured that the noble class that rules Stygia are the results of intermingling between the ancient, pre-human race that ruled Stygia and the savage humans who overthrew them. Occasionally, there are throwbacks to this ancient bloodline born among the nobles, and these half-human creatures are forced into service in the temples of Set, kept beneath the earth and away from prying eyes.

The fashions and designs of Stygia are unique amongst the races, again a side-effect of human culture crossed over with something alien.

This clothing is the type that would be worn by Stygian nobles to a feast, a festival or an orgy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80748_ShortDesc", "A Stygian metal jug")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80748_LongDesc", "These jars are sought after by merchants for their light weight and compact size. They usually contain rare ingredients such as lotus honey.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80216_ShortDesc", "A plate made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80216_LongDesc", "A simple plate for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52423_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52423_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91052_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91052_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91051_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91051_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")
