column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52065_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by the Stygian nobility")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52065_LongDesc", "It is rumoured that the noble class that rules Stygia are the results of intermingling between the ancient, pre-human race that ruled Stygia and the savage humans who overthrew them. Occasionally, there are throwbacks to this ancient bloodline born among the nobles, and these half-human creatures are forced into service in the temples of Set, kept beneath the earth and away from prying eyes.

The fashions and designs of Stygia are unique amongst the races, again a side-effect of human culture crossed over with something alien.

This clothing is the type that would be worn by Stygian nobles to a feast, a festival or an orgy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51624_ShortDesc", "An ornate Stygian shield")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51624_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.'</> - Black Colossus

This ornamental shield, usually used by Stygian soldiers in ceremonial parade, is strong enough to offer formidable protection against attacks. The ridges and ornamentations provide an advantage in battle, catching the blades of the enemy as they slide along the rim while allowing full visibility of the enemy.

Ceremonial versions of this shield are usually wrought in brass and gold, but the more practical versions use tinted iron and steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_ShortDesc", "An ornate pike made in the Stygian style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus

The Stygian armies are famed for using chariots into battle. This frees their hands to use either the bow or the spear to great effect.

The Stygian spear is heavy, two handed, and bronze tipped. Wielded with the momentum of a charging chariot it is devastating to infantry and cavalry alike.

Stygian hunters use the broad bladed spears to hunt lions and rhinoceros on the rocky plains around the Styx river.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_ShortDesc", "A wooden table of Stygian design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88900_LongDesc", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80503_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80503_LongDesc", "This small brazier, made of bronze worked into the shape of a serpent, is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set. \nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52062_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Stygian nobility")
column4:

This clothing is the type that would be worn by Stygian nobles to a feast, a festival or an orgy.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17108_ShortDesc", "A flask of tan dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17108_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_ShortDesc", "A tannery for processing hides into leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89104_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were young men, but hard and sinewy, with a bearing that comes only to men rendered desperate by adversity. They were clad in mail shirts and worn leather; swords hung at their girdles.</> - A Witch Shall be Born

The stench of the tannery is easily identifiable in the major cities of the world and tanners are often relegated to the outskirts of cities or villages, preferably downstream. 

Bark is the most common form of tannin used to convert hide into leather. During the process it breaks down into Tar, which is a useful catalyst for alchemists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80551_ShortDesc", "A patterned tapestry in earthen colors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80551_LongDesc", "Tapestries such as this travel the Lotus road between Khitai and the Kingdoms of the West daily. Woven of plant fibers or silk, they vary in quality and quantity based entirely on the skill of the weaver and the materials used. \nThat these can be made in the Exiled Lands, without a loom, is impressive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80552_ShortDesc", "A patterned tapestry in earthen colors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80552_LongDesc", "Tapestries such as this travel the Lotus road between Khitai and the Kingdoms of the West daily. Woven of plant fibers or silk, they vary in quality and quantity based entirely on the skill of the weaver and the materials used. \nThat these can be made in the Exiled Lands, without a loom, is impressive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14172_ShortDesc", "Thick black substance used for sealing wood")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14172_LongDesc", "Prized by alchemists and sailors alike, tar is a black oily substance derived from the dry heating of bark. It is a by-product of using bark in the tanning process.\nFrom the Vilayet to the Western Ocean, shipwrights know the value of tar as a water repellent. The legendary purple-sailed fleet of Turan owes the color to the unusual mix of tar and local chemicals used to soak the sailcloth.\nIn the gladiatorial arenas of Argos, tar is used to seal cuts and abrasions and ward off minor infections.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_ShortDesc", "An arrow containing a sticky solution")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53620_LongDesc", "The hollow arrow is filled with a pair of special reactants that mix together on contact with the ground and form a sticky pool. This will slow anyone who gets caught in the effect.\n\nArrows can be equipped by dragging them over the bow in the inventory. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80746_ShortDesc", "A decorative tea pot")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80746_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He was a magician from far Khitai, returning to his native kingdom after a journey to Stygia. He took me with him to purple-towered Paikang, its minarets rising amid the vine-festooned jungles of bamboo, and there I grew to womanhood under his teaching.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nThis tea pot is purely decorative.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15509_ShortDesc", "A crystalline tear from Tyros the Deathbringer")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15509_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Tears rolled from the sightless eyes, and Conan's gaze strayed to the limbs stretched on the marble couch. And he knew the monster would not rise to attack him. He knew the marks of the rack, and the searing brand of the flame, and tough-souled as he was, he stood aghast at the ruined deformities which his reason told him had once been limbs as comely as his own. And suddenly all fear and repulsion went from him to be replaced by a great pity.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Long- This single tear, shed by Tyros the Deathbringer, is an object of immense power. Tyros, was the half-blood child of  the Priestking and an unknown human slave. Whether his birth was natural or aided by sorcery, is not known, but it is known that Tyros had children of his own with his wife, Telith.

Tyros was raised a gladiator, fighting in the arena for the benefit of the Giant-kings, but when war broke out with the Lemurians, he became a leader in their armies. Through great feats of strength and will, he won the outpost of Xullan from the Lemurian army. Just south of there, he met Telith, a daughter of Lemuria, and everything changed...

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51066_ShortDesc", "An ancient sword, haunted and grim")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51066_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This ancient sword pulses with blasphemous power.

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51075_ShortDesc", "An ancient sword, haunted and grim")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51075_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80973_ShortDesc", "A temple dedicated to the worship of Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80973_LongDesc", "Considered a good god, Mitra is worshipped throughout the Hyborian kings, replacing the worship of Bori from which those primitive tribes took their name.

Mitra's symbol is that of the phoenix, but when he is depicted it is in the form of a well built, bearded man. He abhors the bloody rituals of other religions and prefers for his followers to perform dignified, purification rituals.

Mitra's priests preach a monotheistic doctrine and as such their followers tend to persecute the members of other nearby religions. Due to this tendency, Chapels to Mitra cannot be built within a very long range of shrines to other gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90032_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90032_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from plant fiber and flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Sloped rooves are practical for channeling debris from the roof.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90023_LongDesc", "Cobbled together from plant fiber and flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Sloped rooves are practical for channeling debris from the roof.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51535_ShortDesc", "A saw-edged, crescent Yuetshi blade")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51535_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Shifting his reddened scimitar to his left hand, he drew the great half-blade of the Yuetshi. Khosatral Khel was towering above him, his arms lifted like mauls, but as the blade caught the sheen of the sun, the giant gave back suddenly.</> - The Devil in Iron

Forged of a meteor, which flashed through the sky like a flaming arrow, this long, crescent blade is of another world. 
It was used to cut down and enthrall Khostral Khel, an unearthly being of untold power, before it suddenly disappeared - and reappeared here, in the Exiled Lands.

When used, it gives unearthly strength in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51550_ShortDesc", "A mace that seems to break constantly")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51550_LongDesc", "This mace evokes a legendary amount of swearing in the wielder and their enemies alike. When it strikes, it does massive damage, causing foes to curse it with every blow. But alas, it also falls apart constantly, requiring regular repair and often, during battle, leaving its owner without a weapon.\n\nA bastard it is, and a bastard it will always be.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51536_ShortDesc", "A set of matched poniards bearing the inscription Grim ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51536_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He inspected the weapon the girl had given him and smiled grimly. Whatever else she might be, she was proven by that dagger to be a person of practical intelligence. It was no slender stiletto, selected because of a jeweled hilt or gold guard, fitted only for dainty murder in milady's boudoir; it was a forthright poniard, a warrior's weapon, broad-bladed, fifteen inches in length, tapering to a diamond-sharp point.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

About twenty years ago, a murderer stalked the streets of Belverus, the capital of Nemedia. Every night, young men and women would go missing from the streets, and their corpses would be found later, mutilated and laid at the doorsteps of their homes.

The people cried out for the murderer to be captured and the watchmen found a suspect, a middle-aged lamplighter who was captured with two blood-stained poniards during his rounds one night.

For his part, the lamplighter told an unbelievable story. He claimed to have seen the poniards floating through the air of their own accord. He said that when he moved towards them, they turned and flew at his throat. Ducking aside, he turned to find that they had embedded themselves in the sideboard of his cart. 

Despite this wild story, he was hanged for his crimes. The murders ceased. And the city slept. And the poniards were never seen again.

These poniards, when used in battle, will increase the damage of every strike.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51560_ShortDesc", "A legendary bow that boosts survival")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51560_LongDesc", "When the Lemurians fled their islands, they were captured and enslaved by the mysterious race that lived on the eastern shores of the Thurian continent.

A remnant of a remnant escaped that slavery and crossed the world in search of succor.

Thousands of people, weary and terrified, needed to be protected and fed as they crossed hostile kingdoms, ghost-haunted moors and the jungles full of dangerous creatures.

A group of women, known as Dagon's Daughters, volunteered to protect the group. They were experts with the bow, and agile fighters at close range.

This bow, simply known as The Huntress, once belonged to Dagon's Daughters. It gives anybody who is desperate to survive a higher chance of making it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51574_ShortDesc", "A pike used by Turanian warlords")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51574_LongDesc", "The Turanian army is feared throughout the west for their ever-expanding grasp and long-standing plans of conquest. There is a sense of impending doom over every kingdom that stands like a bulwark, border to border, with Turan.

When the Turanians conquer a city, they offer a single chance to surrender. If refused, they are without mercy, killing every man, woman and child. If they are accepted, they simply impale the city leaders outside the gates, as a reminder not to test their authority.

This pike was specially designed to impale enemies. The sharp point passes easily through armor and flesh, though, not being designed for battle, it is easily broken.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15517_ShortDesc", "A keystone that unlocks the bracelet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15517_LongDesc", "This keystone, created through a ritual, contains the essence of the artefacts that were used to create the slave bracelets of the Giant-kings.

It can be used to remove a slave bracelet from one who is exiled. This is an extremely powerful artefact and must be used with caution.
Simply use the item to remove the bracelet

WARNING: REMOVING THE BRACELET WILL END THE GAME AND DELETE YOUR CHARACTER")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51543_ShortDesc", "A razor thin two-handed sword")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51543_LongDesc", "At first glance, this sword appears impossible, the blade a paper-thin sheet of metal that looks like it would bend and break at the slightest contact.

Instead, the sword is incredibly formidable against armored opponents, being able to slide into the gaps and crevices in armor with the greatest of ease.

The only disadvantage to the thinness of the blade is that it becomes more difficult to sheath, meaning that those who do not pay attention will find themselves with a thin, deadly cut on the inside of their thighs.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15510_ShortDesc", "A crazy angled stone kept within an alien box")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15510_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It was treasured and placed in its curious box by the crinoid things of Antarctica, salvaged from their ruins by the serpent-men of Valusia... "</> - The Haunter of the Dark, H.P. Lovecraft

This artefact is spoken of in whispers by the nighted cults of the Hyborian age. It is rumored to be a window into all of space and time - but with the cost that the user risks baring their soul to powers from the outer dark.

The Serpentmen of Valusia were in possession of this object, and how they came to be living beneath the volcano in the Exiled Lands is a mystery. Perhaps fleeing their genocide at the hands of the legendary Kull of Atlantis, they made their way to the Exiled Lands where they befriended the Giant-kings through worship of their deity, Set. In return they were allowed to live in the Caldera of the volcano and build their cities there.

It was, however, too late for the serpent men, a degenerate and dying race, lacking the genetic diversity to continue. They found themselves coupling with snakes and lesser reptiles in the hope of preserving their species but as time passed, they lost all hope of survival and instead, preyed for bitter revenge upon the races.

They crafted a staff with their ancient magics and summoned a presence via the trapezohedron, to inhabit the staff and lead the Giant-kings to their downfall.

If they must die, they would take as many with them as possible and most especially, the cursed children of humankind.

This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51465_ShortDesc", "A powerful two-handed staff blessed by Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51465_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> But the voice called him on, and at last, in darkness that would have been impenetrable to his material eyes, he came into a strange crypt, and saw a vague white-bearded figure sitting on a tomb.</>  - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the world was young, there was a great sage known as Epemitreus. Little is known of the shadowy past in which he fought with Set, the arch-demon, but it is known that for all the days of his life he strove against the worshippers, votaries and acolytes of the Old Serpent.

It is rumored that in times of need the ghost of Epemitreus flies on unseen wings to aid the kingdom of Aquilonia, and that the symbol of the phoenix belongs to the sage as much as it does to Mitra.

This staff is crafted from a pattern created by the sage Epemitreus. It is marked with a simple script which reads By fire and steel and the juice of the Upas tree

This is a sacred weapon, imbued with the blessing of a deity. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51466_ShortDesc", "A powerful mace blessed by Yog")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51466_LongDesc", "The rough appearance of this mace belies the terrible power concealed within. Decorated with the swirling symbols that make up a single syllable of the unutterable name of Yog, this mace is heavy with the darkness of Yog.\n\nThis is a sacred weapon, imbued with the blessing of a deity. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51549_ShortDesc", "Fokove ces he fo lojani rudab gerere ta yi rofibu.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51549_LongDesc", "Oro se limetah de yacie rer ned dofat tihot leci. Jiso toku tetes yoqic itak lienan enapet bito? Bupi icarimir hal pe opine davec lu. Te totid yitijel pemepa nolon gisi tiefielit nabel. Pa ecoticel tetola totuhir tanielod ra alo lida? Ditemit na birig.\n\nBurusier igiweper fa roc losor mimecieb. Butara henile reg he ha lobo leru nape anilinor hat! Si pep otep lefuno usi. Lasec hecapah reterad ric hoh: Zaw eneranaj ro taso asat nerinah royogi: Nienasic inosine sin, cinoc ieri ciyet tote bunate rie tem. Ne enosem hopehi cipacih teruso veso omenigo afelo nuhilad ho.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51545_ShortDesc", "A two-handed blade with a single purpose")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51545_LongDesc", "This sword was crafted to serve as a simple blade for a watchman in the ancient kingdom of Valusia. Over the years, it was passed down, watchman to watchman, and the hilt was rebound, but the blade was never repaired.

Eventually, Valusia disappeared and the watchmen were gone, and the blade was forgotten.

When it was rediscovered, it was rusted and pitted by age, but it could still be swung in battle. 

Any attempts to remove the rust and stains are futile, but the weapon itself is as sturdy and steadfast as its name.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51533_ShortDesc", "A blade that glimmers with unholy life")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51533_LongDesc", "The scars of the war that tore the Exiled Lands apart thousands of years in the past are still apparent today. And the dead walk the ancient battlefields, carrying weapons that glimmer with ancient sorrow.

This blade, taken from one of the dead, allows the vitality of the dead to seep into the bearer. Its unearthly light reminds the wielder that death is the consequence of living, and thus encourages them to live just a little more strongly.

This weapon increases vitality.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41071_ShortDesc", "A set of reinforcing plates that can attached to increase the strength of armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41071_LongDesc", "esigned to protect in battle, it can be disastrous if armor shatters beneath a powerful blow. Wise warriors seek to shore up their weaknesses, often by reinforcing the weaker joints of their armor.\n\nAttaching these thick plates to any set of clothing will increase its armor value considerably.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12012_ShortDesc", "Some creatures have thicker skins than others")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12012_LongDesc", "Large beasts have developed thicker skins for defence against predators. This thickened skin, while harder to work, provides a superior leather. \nWorshippers of the beast-god, Jhebbal Sag have been known to clothe themselves in the hides of ferocious predators as a symbol of their pact.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12512_ShortDesc", "Offers a higher degree of protection than regular leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_12512_LongDesc", "Offering better protection than regular leather, but at the cost of flexibility.
Thickened leather requires regular oiling to prevent it from becoming inflexible and preventing movement.
Kordavan leather is famed for its pliability and durability, but to learn the secret of its durability would require access to the tanneries of the Zingaran capital.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41069_ShortDesc", "A set of reinforcing plates that can attached to increase the strength of armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41069_LongDesc", "Designed to protect in battle, it can be disastrous if armor shatters beneath a powerful blow. Wise warriors seek to shore up their weaknesses, often by reinforcing the weaker joints of their armor.\n\nAttaching these thin plates to any set of clothing will increase its armor value slightly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51912_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51912_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11120_ShortDesc", "A handle required for crafting high end weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11120_LongDesc", "As the materials used for crafting blades, heads and shields grows stronger, it is important that the other elements of the weapon are strengthened to compensate for the additional strains.\n\nThis handle is functional and will prevent weapons from breaking immediately upon entering battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82051_ShortDesc", "The head of a Tiger")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82051_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82057_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Tiger head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82057_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column2: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90274_Name", "Tiled Sloped Black Ice-Reinforced Wooden Roof")
column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90274_ShortDesc", "A tiled sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90274_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90254_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90254_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in blizzards as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90213_ShortDesc", "A tiled sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90213_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column2: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90275_Name", "Tiled Wedge Black Ice-Reinforced Wooden Sloped Roof")
column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90275_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped, sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90275_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBlack Ice-Reinforced Wood  is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column2: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90255_Name", "Tiled Wedge Insulated Wooden Sloped Roof")
column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90255_ShortDesc", "A wedge shaped, sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90255_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in blizzards as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of planks coated in resin for insulation, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90214_ShortDesc", "A tiled wedge sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90214_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nReinforced Stone is one of the hardest building materials that can be created in the Exiled Lands. Weapons barely chip it and even explosive powder is not enough to weaken it in a single blow. Siege weapons or divine intervention are really the only way to bring down walls this strong.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14181_ShortDesc", "Dust stolen from a tomb")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14181_LongDesc", "Those who rob the dead are either desperate, brave or possessed of such dark power that they no longer fear the dead.\nThe dust stolen from the tombs of dead Stygians is said to cause blindness when flung into the eyes of an opponent. It has darker uses that are detailed in the blasphemous Book of Skelos.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41057_ShortDesc", "An assortment of upgrades to make tools more efficient")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41057_LongDesc", "There is wisdom among the simple peoples of the world; those who spend their time tilling, hunting, growing and harvesting.

The time-tested techniques for improving the harvesting capacity of tools have been distilled into the upgrades found in this kit.

Applying this upgrade to a tool will increase its harvesting capacity.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41033_ShortDesc", "A torch that can burn for a long time")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41033_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The glimmering light of the torch, flickering through the bars, hinted at shadowy spaciousness and echoing depths. </> - The Hour of the Dragon

A smoke-wreathed, naked flame burning merrily atop a wooden fixture. Torches are the most common light source in the Hyborian Kingdoms. From tavern brawls to the clash of empires, torchlight has been witness to many of the greatest events of an age.

And afterwards, the purging fire of torches has been put to other uses than illumination.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30005_ShortDesc", "A piece of parchment with crazed scribblings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30005_LongDesc", "Nowhere is safe. Nowhere. The drums come every night now, a rhythmic pounding that raises terror in 
every heartbeat.
The Darfari are hunting and men are their quarry.
I used to hear their drums out in the desert groves beyond Zamboula and in that life, I simply thanked 
the gods that I had wealth and shelter.
But see me now, crouched among the boulders, filthy, ragged and half starved. My days are a constant 
scramble for food and water and my nights are spent huddled in whatever shelter I can find.
Soon I will drift off to the half-sleep of the terrified, to dream of filed teeth and wicked cudgels and the 
haunting beating of those gods-cursed drums...
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18514_ShortDesc", "A place for crafting objects of torture")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18514_LongDesc", "What elevates men above animals? Some scholars speculate that it is man's capacity for good that elevates him above the basic beast. 

Others, however, would argue that it is his infinite capacity for darkness.

This table, designed expressly for the purpose of crafting implements for inflicting pain and servitude on other peoples, is a good argument for the latter.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18229_ShortDesc", "Strips of exotic meat dried and salted")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18229_LongDesc", "There are those who say drying and salting such fare is a waste of superior meat, but there are also those who want a finer sort of dry ration to reach into their bag for on faraway and lonely trails.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80151_ShortDesc", "A training dummy for practising combat techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80151_LongDesc", "Made of stuffed straw and rough cloth, this dummy is a stand in for the horrendous creatures of the Exiled Lands.\nThe ability to guage hit locations from the markings on the dummy is a great way for warriors to increase their abilities.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89813_ShortDesc", "A siege engine for hurling heavy loads")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89813_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'No man living could throw that rock across this glade. It's a task for siege engines. Yet here there are no mangonels or ballistas.'</> - Shadows in the Moonlight

In the so-called civilized kingdoms of Hyboria, nobles build great palaces with walls of mighty stone to protect themselves from their enemies at court and abroad.

The solution to sturdy walls and cowardly nobility is the steadfast trebuchet. A machine of immense power, the trebuchet can be used to fling stones, corpses and even specially designed explosives.
Their weakness is their immobility, they cannot be easily moved once placed and finding the correct range and angle requires time and patience. With repeated use, it is almost certain that some or all of the pieces of the trebuchet will degrade and need to be replaced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_ShortDesc", "A rotating base for a trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the landward side mangonels rained boulders and tree-trunks among the defenders, shattering through roofs and crushing humans like beetles; rams pounded incessantly at the stones; sappers burrowed like moles in the earth, sinking their mines beneath the towers.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This base piece of the trebuchet, once placed on a siege foundation, can be upgraded with a  frame to reach full functionality.

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89812_ShortDesc", "A wooden frame for a trebuchet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89812_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">On the landward side mangonels rained boulders and tree-trunks among the defenders, shattering through roofs and crushing humans like beetles; rams pounded incessantly at the stones; sappers burrowed like moles in the earth, sinking their mines beneath the towers.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_ShortDesc", "A rack for displaying weapons")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88902_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such display racks useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14191_ShortDesc", "A plant with flowers of startling color")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14191_LongDesc", "Cultivated in Stygia, the petals of this plant produce a brightly colored dye which the Stygians use for decorating ceremonial clothing and armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55005_ShortDesc", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Derketo")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55005_LongDesc", ""<span style="italic">Some gods are strong to harm, others, to aid; at least so say their priests.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Learning true names is a study that sorcerers use to contact the demons of the Outer Void. Such sorcerers have volumes full of the names of their familiars and allies.

The true name of a god, however, burns brightly in the mind when spoken, then flares and fades into nothingness. Once spoken, such a name is forgotten immediately.

This name then, carved in stone, is a priceless gift. For a short period, the gaze of a god will be upon the speaker and they will be lifted to heights of power undreamed of. But men were not built to live as gods, so the power is fleeting."
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55003_ShortDesc", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Mitra")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_55004_ShortDesc", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Ymir")
column4:

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51303_ShortDesc", "A weighted club for knocking out foes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51303_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he stumbled over a corpse, and a bludgeon knocked the dented helmet from his head; the next instant the club fell full on his unprotected skull.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Used by watchmen and criminals alike, the truncheon is designed for incapacitating enemies without killing them.

Shemitish slavers have been known to waylay travelers leaving taverns in the meadowland cities and expertly knocking them out. The poor wretches awaken the next day in a wagonful of other captives with sore heads, on their way to the slave markets of the east.

It takes a great deal of experimentation to understand how to hit an enemy just hard enough to knock them out without smashing their skull.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51531_ShortDesc", "Legendary tulwar of a Wazuli Chief")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51531_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan lifted his knife and smote, and the watchers were dumbfounded to see his blow checked apparently in midair, with the loud clang of steel that meets an unyielding substance. He wasted no more effort. He knew that not even the legendary tulwar of Amir Khurum could shatter that invisible curtain.</> - The People of the Black Circle

Amir Khurum was a legendary prince and commander of the Wazuli tribe. The Wazuli revere his memory for his even-handed nature as a chief - he dealt honorably with all and led them to a great deal of treasure in his career.

If the legends are to be believer, this tulwar can pass through any armor, though it is hard to say if this is the original item or an elaborate forgery.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18053_ShortDesc", "A huge tooth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18053_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Conan stepped out into the nearest square of moonlight, so as to have all the advantage of illumination that he could; for the beast, he knew, could see better than himself in the dark. Instantly the brute saw him; its great yellow tusks gleamed in the shadows, but it made no sound.\'</> - The Hour of the Dragon\n\nAn oversized, protruding tooth recently ripped from the maw of a beast. Tusks are used in jewelry, tool-making, or simple as a trophy one can carry in their hand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14174_ShortDesc", "A small length of twine")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14174_LongDesc", "Created by twisting lengths of fiber together to create a sturdy length of string, twine is used for binding the most primitive weapons and and items together.\nThe advantage of twine is that it is easily created from scavenged ingredients, such as plant fiber, but it\'s tendency to unravel at unfortunate times makes anything crafted with it inherently fragile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51044_ShortDesc", "A two-handed Iron sword")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51044_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I pay my way with steel!\' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nGreat swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51047_ShortDesc", "A two-handed Steel sword")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51047_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I pay my way with steel!\' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nGreat swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51043_ShortDesc", "A  crude two-handed sword made out of sharpened stone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51043_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> His devotees died about that tomb in a crimson holocaust, but the barbarians could not burst the door, nor ever mar the structure by maul or fire.</> - Black Colossus

Crudely put together using a long branch and a large, heavy stone, this weapon will deteriorate quickly with use.

This sword is a straight-bladed, two-handed weapons, as heavy as it is powerful.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82059_ShortDesc", "A dried and stuffed fish mounted on a wooden plack")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82059_LongDesc", "Fishermen often keep their most memorable catch as a trophy. Some are kept for the memories, others to impress, and yet others are kept for the sole reason of having something on the wall. Looking at this piece, you cannot help but wonder what reason could possibly be behind this one.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18010_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from small fish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18010_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from small fish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18020_ShortDesc", "Raw flesh harvested from middling shellfish")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18020_LongDesc", "Raw meat is a dangerous temptation for the starving and desperate. Consuming it provides immediate relief from hunger - but at the risk of inheriting any disease or parasite that may have come along for the ride.\n\nThis flesh is harvested from shellfish not known for being good eating. It is not particularly filling or flavorful, and the shell-to-meat ratio is not very good.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15002_ShortDesc", "Carefully harvested, this meat is ritually pure.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_15002_LongDesc", "This flesh has not known the touch of a blade and is therefore ritually pure in the eyes of the Yog religion.\nThe desert men of Darfar, even those who are enslaved in the great city states that make up the kingdom of Shem, partake of ritually pure human flesh at least once every cycle of the moon.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82016_ShortDesc", "The head of an Undead Hyena")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82016_LongDesc", "The head of an Undead Hyena")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81017_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Undead Hyena head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81017_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52619_ShortDesc", "Reinforced and fur-lined boots of Vanir make")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52619_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan opened his eyes and stared into the bearded faces that bent over him. He was surrounded by tall golden-haired warriors in mail and furs.</> - The Frost-Giant's Daughter

These reinforced boots of leather and fur keep one's feet both safe and warm.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

With fur and pelts, man takes the protection wild beasts enjoy against the elements. Fur is used in making both practical and decadent things. Both the savage and the civilized prize fur.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52560_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52560_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They gave tongue like wolves and surged about the lone figure in the gray mail, and the clamor and din of steel drowned the cries of the circling raven.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard plated boots are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52979_ShortDesc", "A pair of furry boots worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52979_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These boots keep the feet warm while stumbling through banks and drifts of snow.")

column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91027_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These gloves are perfect for keeping the hands warm while working frozen soil.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52975_ShortDesc", "A pair of bone earrings often worn by Vanir commoners")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52975_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle. 

Thus not all Vanir that are encountered in the north are raiders and warriors, quite often the weary adventurer will stumble across a caravan of Vanir settlers, looking for fertile lands to settle their new clan.

These earrings provide no significant protection, but they are marked with clan symbols - so that if a dead settler is found, their possessions can be returned to the clan. Jokingly referred to by the Aesir as Vanearrings.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52976_ShortDesc", "A fur-lined vest worn by Vanir settlers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52976_LongDesc", "As the massive glaciers of the north expand and move southward, the kingdoms of Asgard and Vanaheim are pushed slowly southward. This, in part, contributes to the perception of the Vanir and Aesir as warlike people - they are continually looking to the south in search of new lands to settle.

This vest is designed to keep the settler warm, while freeing their hands for working with tools. It offers some basic protection against attacks due to its thickness, but is not as effective as true armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88893_ShortDesc", "A totem of Vanir design")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88893_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\"> \'Who are you to swear by Ymir?\' she mocked. \'What know you of the gods of ice and snow, you who have come up from the south to adventure among an alien people?\'</> - Gods of the North\n\nWhile individual Nordheimer clans may worship different minor deities, Ymir is considered the chief of all gods. The god of Storm and War is said to send his daughter Atali to fetch the souls of dead and dying warriors to fill the halls of Valhalla.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80914_ShortDesc", "A trap that releases a damaging vapor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80914_LongDesc", "Filled with a viscous, clinging vapor that eats the lungs and makes breathing impossible, this deadly trap is used by merchants in Zamora to discourage thieves. It is even proof against the sandstorm masks commonly crafted by desert tribesman to keep out sand partiles - evidently the gas is able to seep into the masks regardless.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80853_ShortDesc", "A vault for storing valuable items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80853_LongDesc", "This vault, made from steel and iron, represents the most secure location to store excess items and materials. Breaking into this vault will require a heroic effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51575_ShortDesc", "A pike with an easily bendable shaft")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51575_LongDesc", "This pike is, at first glance, completely normal. It is only when using it in battle, one notices that the haft has an extreme amount of flex.

These were originally designed in Khitai as training spears for the monks who followed Yun, the god of death. The flexible haft was used to perform death defying leaps over the spiked, burning sacrifice pits that burn outside the main temple building in Paikang.

Using this pike gives the wielder a boost to agility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90304_ShortDesc", "A wooden support beam")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90304_LongDesc", "Support beams offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11101_ShortDesc", "A length of vine ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11101_LongDesc", "This length of fibrous vine, cut in the swamps of the Exiled Lands. These vines can be broken down into tough plant fibers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53011_ShortDesc", "A brilliant purple potion that cures everything")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53011_LongDesc", "Extracted from the venom of various poisonous snakes, this violet potion seems to purge the system of all natural negative effects upon use. Commonly used by street performers in Vendhya to shrug off the effects of cobra bites, more fools have died trying to harvest the ingredients for the cure-all than would have died if the cure-all did not exist at all.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18188_ShortDesc", "A bizarre gland that can be used to make explosives")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18188_LongDesc", "Harvested from the corpse of a degenerate, imp-like creature found in the Exiled Lands, this gland is a key component for making demon-fire orbs.\nThe mechanism by which these creatures cause themselves to explode is not well understood, though scholars in other lands have reported similar incidents with frogs and ants. \nMost, however, simple agree that the explosions are sorcerous in nature and leave it at that.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80506_ShortDesc", "An ornate brazier")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80506_LongDesc", "A brazier provides both light and protection from the cold climates of the frozen north.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80515_ShortDesc", "An iron-sheathed lantern that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80515_LongDesc", "This ornate lantern bears patterning that seems to indicate that it is of Turanian origin. It is well known that the rich quarter of Agrapur has street lanterns placed at regular intervals to discourage thieves.\nLanterns have a steadier light than torches, and they remain lit for longer. However, the soft glow of a lantern fails to evoke the same primal urges as the naked flame.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80211_ShortDesc", "A barricade of high sharpened stakes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80211_LongDesc", "Designed as a foil to cavalry charges, the stakes on these barricades were originally about chest high to a horse. Over time it was discovered that the closer the spikes were to eye height on a horse, the less chance that the beast could be coerced into charging them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80302_ShortDesc", "A wall sign")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80302_LongDesc", "Designed to be placed on walls and provide information about the location, these signs are a mark of civilization beyond what most people would expect to find in the Exiled Lands.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53530_ShortDesc", "A warpaint declaring the accuracy of the bearer")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53530_LongDesc", "Some warpaints are designed to be prayers to the gods, infusing the wearer with their strength and skill. Some warpaints are merely decorative, worn to show allegiance or affiliation with a clan.\nWearing this warpaint will increase the accuracy of the wearer.")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53520_LongDesc", "Some warpaints are designed to be prayers to the gods, infusing the wearer with their strength and skill. Some warpaints are merely decorative, worn to show allegiance or affiliation with a clan.\n\nThis is a decorative warpaint.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53524_ShortDesc", "A decorative warpaint depicting the emblem of Ymir\'s Children")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53524_LongDesc", "Some warpaints are designed to be prayers to the gods, infusing the wearer with their strength and skill. Some warpaints are merely decorative, worn to show allegiance or affiliation with a clan.\n\nThis is a decorative warpaint.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51571_ShortDesc", "A warspear forged on Mount Yimsha")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51571_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Like a man in a trance the warrior thrust the butt of his spear against the base of the wall, and placed the keen head against his body, just below the ribs. Then slowly, stolidly, he leaned against it with all his weight, so that it transfixed his body and came out between his shoulders. Sliding down the shaft he lay still, the spear jutting above him its full length, like a horrible stalk growing out of his back.</> - People of the Black Circle

The Master of the Black Circle is a reclusive and mysterious figure, feared by all who dwell in the region of Mount Yimsha. The locals avoid the mountain as much as possible and few who venture up the winding path ever return to speak of it.

This spear, then, is an anomaly. How it came to be is unknown, whether it was forged on the mountain or brought wholesale into being via sorcery.

It has excellent balance in battle, allowing heavy swings at a fraction of their regular stamina cost - but it seems unable to penetrate armor in any meaningful way.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51973_ShortDesc", "A glass orb filled with water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51973_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'There is a crystal jar on that ivory table,\' he answered. \'Fill it with water and tie a strip of that torn hanging about its neck for a handle while I rip up this tapestry.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThis is simply a glass flask filled with water. It can be used to douse fires and to settle particles from the air. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80131_ShortDesc", "A well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80131_LongDesc", "Made from rough stones and wood, this well manages to capture a small amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14201_ShortDesc", "A glass flask filled with water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14201_LongDesc", "Glass is a fragile substance most often used by nobles and rich merchants for mirrors and windows. Alchemists also prize it for its ability to store volatile concoctions and their ability to observe reactions within the glass as they experiment. Experienced alchemists have hundreds of such flasks, filled with exotic materials from across the world. Less experienced alchemists are probably dead because they stored their concoctions in a less adequate container.\n\nThis flask is filled with water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30024_ShortDesc", "A waterstained parchment")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_30024_LongDesc", "This note has been under the water for a long time and most of the words have been washed away.
What is left reads:
...enius plan! If it is buried in...
...st pillar, opposite the riv...
...neath the skull of a mammoth...
...ash it! The only...")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41053_ShortDesc", "A bag of unpleasant things that can be attached to weapons to increase their damage")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41053_LongDesc", "Some warriors adorn their weapons to intimidate their foes and make them a memorable presence on the battlefield.

But the collection of spikes and studs contained in this bag have a single purpose - to wreck foes. Whether hammer, sword, or spear - there is something here to bring ruination, laceration, and devastation to the bodies and minds of enemies everywhere.

Applying this kit to a weapon will increase its damage.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80764_ShortDesc", "A pedestal for displaying a single weapon")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80764_LongDesc", "Boastful warriors and craftsman alike enjoy adorning their strongholds with the weapons of their conquered foes.\n\nHumbler heroes still find such pedestals useful, not least for being able to store weapons in places where they would otherwise seem out of place.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41025_ShortDesc", "A toolkit for repairing damaged weapons")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_41025_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He rushed in, hacking madly, but Conan, recognizing him, shattered his sword with a short terrific chop and with a powerful push of his open hand sent him reeling to the floor.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the fury of battle has subsided and the lightning clash of weapons has stilled, the victors are left to count the cost. And sometimes the price of battle is the very weapons that are used to wage it.

This kit, containing a whetstone, a hone and a small portion of blade oil, will allow even unskilled crafters to repair the worst damage to their blades, though it will never be able to renew them completely.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_ShortDesc", "This is a skull taken from a dead enemy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_88890_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the dead rise to fight once again. Perhaps they rise due to the long forgotten command of a necromancer. Perhaps they rise to the singing of a song that the living cannot hear. \nWhatever wakes them, they must still be put to sleep once more.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89912_ShortDesc", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_89912_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \n\nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80522_ShortDesc", "A white, beeswax candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80522_LongDesc", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nWhite candles are often burned in the temples of Mitra representing the purity of thought and knowledge that Mitra brings to his followers.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17115_ShortDesc", "A flask of white dye")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17115_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82001_ShortDesc", "White Rhino Head")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82001_LongDesc", "The head of a White Rhino")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81001_ShortDesc", "White Rhino Head Trophy")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81001_LongDesc", "The Exiled Lands is filled with fearsome creatures and every encounter is a matter of life and death. This souvenir commemorates a battle where an exile triumphed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82028_ShortDesc", "The head of a Wild Boar")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82028_LongDesc", "The head of a Wild Boar")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82027_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Wild Boar head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82027_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'He hunted only the living, in a life dedicated solely to slaughter. An awful hunger burned greenly in the wide, unwinking eyes; the hunger not alone of belly-emptiness, but the lust of death-dealing.'</> - Beyond the Black River

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved boar's head bespeaks of one who dares hunt these unpredictable, razor-tusked swine.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18078_ShortDesc", "Bounty of the grape, drink of the gods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18078_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Let me live deep while I live; let me know the rich juices of red meat and stinging wine on my palate, the hot embrace of white arms, the mad exultation of battle when the blue blades flame and crimson, and I am content.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nThe alcoholic beverage made from the grape. Different grapes and different techniques in their fermentation produce different vintages. Wine lightly cools the tongue.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52610_ShortDesc", "A coronal radiating winter\'s chill")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52610_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The glowing snow lay empty and bare; high above his head the witch-lights flashed and played in a frosty sky gone mad, and among the distant blue mountains there sounded a rolling thunder as of a gigantic war-chariot rushing behind steeds whose frantic hoofs struck lightning from the snows and echoes from the skies.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThis headpiece marks one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80532_ShortDesc", "A bag of witchfire powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80532_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate patch to radium gems.

Witchfire powder is created by combining glowing plants and brimstone. 

The powder can be used in the crafting of heatless, blue torches.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80536_ShortDesc", "A tall torch of witchfire that can be placed in the ground")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80536_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate patch to radium gems.

This standing torch burns blue and gives off no heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80538_ShortDesc", "A wall torch of witchfire that can be placed on walls")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80538_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate patch to radium gems.

Witchfire powder is created from the combination of strange glowing plants and brimstone. 

This wall torch burns blue and gives off no heat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82031_ShortDesc", "The head of a Wolf")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82031_LongDesc", "The head of a Wolf")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11069_ShortDesc", "The pelt of a wolf")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11069_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then he found something else to make him wonder. Among the furs on the dais was a gorgeous spotted skin, whose predominant hue was golden. It was not a clever copy, but the skin of an actual beast. And that beast, Conan knew, had been extinct for at least a thousand years; it was the great golden leopard which figures so prominently in Hyborian legendry, and which the ancient artists delighted to portray in pigments and marble.</> - The Devil in Iron

Pelts, skinned from beasts, with warm or tough or luxuriant fur, are among the earliest materials man has turned to clothing. To wear the skins of creatures the gods left less exposed to the elements - to take on their strength.

Wolf pelts are common apparel in the frozen northern lands, enjoyed for their warmth and the intimidation of wearing such a dangerous animal as a hat.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82030_ShortDesc", "A stuffed, mounted Wolf head")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_82030_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">' A wolf was no less a wolf because a whim of chance caused him to run with the watch-dogs. Bloodshed and violence and savagery were the natural elements of the life Conan knew; he could not, and would never understand the little things that are so dear to the souls of civilized men and women.'</> - Beyond the Black River

Trophies are not merely a visceral mark of bravado. They are totems to the stories of deeds past. They chronicle the skill and tenacity of hunters and barbarians - the ability to capture prey or fell a foe.

This preserved wolf's head offers some comfort when hearing the hungry howls in the night.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10011_ShortDesc", "A log hewn from a tree")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_10011_LongDesc", "Wood is an abundant source of fuel and building material.\nReadily available and easily shaped with the right tools, wood is ubiquitous in the weapons and buildings of primitive tribes and mighty nations.  \nWood allows for the creation of fire and its easy transport.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90065_ShortDesc", "Wooden planks supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90065_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90066_ShortDesc", "Wooden planks supported by wooden beams")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90066_LongDesc", "This provides no protection from the elements.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80272_ShortDesc", "A crude wooden bench")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80272_LongDesc", "Benches like this are common in the taverns and alehouses of the world. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80646_ShortDesc", "A wooden bowl")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80646_LongDesc", "A simple wooden bowl for holding or preparing food.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80851_ShortDesc", "A wooden box for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80851_LongDesc", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this box is made from simple materials. It can be locked against strangers, but a determined thief will be able to smash it open and take what they please.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80262_ShortDesc", "Wooden chair with backrest")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80262_LongDesc", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80217_ShortDesc", "A crude wooden fence")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80217_LongDesc", "A collection of crude wooden planks and branches, bound together with rope, these wooden fences offer little protection from intruders but are useful to encircle ones encampment.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80913_ShortDesc", "A wooden trap for capturing small animals")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80913_LongDesc", "This small trap is useful for capturing game and other small animals. It is not strong enough to keep anything larger than a rabbit pinned for very long.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90033_ShortDesc", "A sloped roof piece")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_90033_LongDesc", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51600_ShortDesc", "A rudimentary shield of loosely bound branches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51600_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Presently the intention of the pirates became apparent to all, as a group of some thirty men advanced, pushing before them a great shield made out of the planks from the boats, and the timbers of the boat-house itself.</> - The Black Stranger

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is a primitive bundle of branches, strapped together with rudimentary twine made from plant fibres. It will shatter under sustained blows, but it might be the difference between life and death.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80301_ShortDesc", "A wooden signpost")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80301_LongDesc", "In the Western kingdoms of Aquilonia and Nemedia, the practise of using wooden signs to provide warning and information for travellers and merchants has been established for centuries.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51602_ShortDesc", "A sturdy targe of wooden planks reinforced with iron")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51602_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Shields crashed against shields, and between them spears drove in and blood spurted.</> - Black Colossus

A round shield, reinforced with metal around the rim and leather straps for ease of holding. It is not uncommon to cover the front of the targe with a sheet of leather or hide and decorate it with patterns.

The targe is a shield designed for attack as much a defence. A well placed strike with the shield can stagger an enemy and leave them open to attacks from a weapon in the main hand.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80253_ShortDesc", "A woven wooden stool")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80253_LongDesc", "Crafted by weaving thin bands of hard wood into a strong yet pliable surface, this stool is comfortable to sit on and very lightweight.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000006_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000006_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80534_ShortDesc", "A hanging torch-holder containing an odd gem")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80534_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk\n\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000007_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_9000007_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80537_ShortDesc", "A wall torch of witchfire that can be placed on ceilings")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_80537_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">For an instant a dimming witchfire glimmered in those dusky depths; then it disappeared, and Conan lay staring down into the blackness of the ultimate abyss from which no sound came.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Witchfire is an alchemical component, created by ancient scientists as a waste product on their ultimate patch to radium gems.

Witchfire powder is created from the combination of strange glowing plants and brimstone. 

This wall torch burns blue and gives off no heat.")
