column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17070_ShortDesc", "A flask of yellow dye ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_17070_LongDesc", "This dye can be applied to textiles in order to color them. Different types of material will be affected differently by the dye, so the coloring of leather will appear differently to metals.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14151_ShortDesc", "Plucked from gently waving lotus blossoms")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_14151_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.\nThose who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53101_ShortDesc", "A potion that causes hallucinations and visions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53101_LongDesc", "The yellow lotus is used by sorcerers to provide visions and trances, with a strong hallucinogenic effect. It is said that those who survive the visions are given a deeper insight into the world, able to communicate with the inner world in a way that rewrites their very physique. In reality, the effect of the potion blanks the mind, freeing one to focus on a new set of skills at the cost of forgetting all previous abilities and skills.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11122_ShortDesc", "A small bag of yellow lotus powder")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11122_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.

Those who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.

What effect the dried powder of the flower will have, is unknown.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11082_ShortDesc", "Seeds of the yellow lotus")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_11082_LongDesc", "While the black lotus is feared for its deadly effect, the yellow lotus is known for its ability to cause visions and hallucinations of great import.

Those who lose themselves in the lotus dreams can have a difficult path back, but eternal renewal is worth the risk.

These seeds can be placed in a planter and together with fertilizer will grow a plant over time. These plants may then be collected or left as decoration.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18238_ShortDesc", "Soup boiled from that infamous blossom")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_18238_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He halted at an ebony door, in the center of which was a grinning silver skull, and pushed it open. He looked into a chamber of ebony and jet, and saw, on a black silken couch, a tall, spare form reclining. Yara the priest and sorcerer lay before him, his eyes open and dilated with the fumes of the yellow lotus, far-staring, as if fixed on gulfs and nighted abysses beyond human ken.</> - The Tower of the Elephant\n\nWhile the yellow lotus can make a mind forget its past, one may cook it into a soup and boil out this property. So prepared, it becomes a safe and rather mundane meal, despite the mystical mystique surrounding the flower.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52611_ShortDesc", "This chest piece protects one with a frost giant\'s might")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52611_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And in that instant she flung her arms toward the lights that glowed in the skies above her and cried out in a voice that rang in Conan\'s ears for ever after: \'Ymir! Oh, my father, save me!\' </> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThis frigid armor of adamantine strength marks one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52612_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets that give an icy touch")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52612_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Not so!\' cried an older man, whose eyes were wild and weird. \'It was Atali, the daughter of Ymir, the frost-giant! To fields of the dead she comes, and shows herself to the dying... She lures men from stricken fields into the wastelands to be slain by her brothers, the ice-giants, who lay men\'s red hearts smoking on Ymir\'s board.\'</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese gauntlets of ice and steel mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52613_ShortDesc", "Leggings marked by Ymir\'s runes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52613_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'Swear not so often by Ymir,\' uneasily muttered a warrior, glancing at the distant mountains.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese leggings, of a material both frosty and otherworldly, mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52614_ShortDesc", "Boots that crunch like snow with every step")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52614_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">Above him the skies glowed and crackled with strange lights and gleams. The snow shone weirdly, now frosty blue, now icy crimson, now cold silver. Through a shimmering icy realm of enchantment Conan plunged doggedly onward, in a crystalline maze where the only reality was the white body dancing across the glittering snow beyond his reach - ever beyond his reach.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThese boots of winter weirdness mark one as devout to Ymir, Father of Giants, Lord of Storm and War.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51854_ShortDesc", "A rudimentary axe created from a jawbone bound to a stout branch")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51854_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> On the heels of the shout came a clamor of blood-freezing screams, the shattering impact of axes on the gate.</> - The Black Stranger

Bladed weapons are generally frowned upon by the worshippers of Yog, but this jawbone is dull enough that it acts more like a club than a sword.
Yoggites believe that the consumption of human flesh gives them the Blessing of Yog for a period of time, which grants them invulnerability to normal weapons.

While Yog is considered a deity in Darfar, scholars in Hyboria classify him as a demon of the Elder night, referencing ancient documents that survived the drowning of Atlantis.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_ShortDesc", "A short spear of the Darfari style")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Black men came up the river in long boats with skulls grinning on the prows, or stole stooping through the trees, spear in hand.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Adorned with feathers and tipped with flint, this short spear represents the pinnacle of Darfari weapons.

The Darfari use these spears for hunting game, first pinning their prey with well-aimed throws and then harassing their prey with swift, sharp stabs.

The feathers on the shaft are taken from the ferocious, but colourful, elephant birds that roam the grasslands on the very edges of Darfar.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51855_ShortDesc", "A macabre weapon of bone fused to rock")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51855_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Cannibalism is more than a perverted appetite to the men of Darfar: it is an integral element of their cult. This cudgel is one of the ritual objects of the Yoggite religion. It is used to bludgeon human prey so that they can be carried to the sacrifice pit unblemished.

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These leather wraps, generously called greaves, are supple leather adorned with human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52105_ShortDesc", "Anklets worn by the temple dancers of Zamoria")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52105_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
It is whispered that the temple girls of Yezud wear clothing such as this when they dance before the black stone spider that is their god.

For ceremonial usage, these anklets offer very little protection against sword or fang, but offer slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_ShortDesc", "A blouse favored by Zamorian temple dancers")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
The steps of the dance are unknown, but it is clear that it eases the black madness that whispers to those who find themselves in the vicinity of the awful presence of Zath, spider-god of Yezud.

For ceremonial usage, this blouse offers very little protection against sword or fang, but offers slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52939_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots of supple leather")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52939_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These boots are designed to allow cutthroats easy access to their victims, damping their footsteps as they approach from behind. 
They're also surprisingly durable when fleeing the city watch.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52938_ShortDesc", "Leather leggings with a belt of useful pouches")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52938_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

These leggings are designed to help, not hinder, the burgeoning burglar in their trade. Accompanied by a handy belt, full of small pouches for storing the various tools of the thieving profession, these skin tight leather pants also offer excellent protection.
 Zamorian cutthroats swear by them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52936_ShortDesc", "A leather chestpiece those who work in the shadows")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52936_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

Designed with the principle that the best fight is a fight avoided, this outfit allows the wearer to blend into the shadows and remain unseen in the deep shadows of the Zamorian cities. 

It has been wrapped tightly to dampen any noise caused by loose straps and buckles. Whether it is as effective in the lands beyond Zamoria is another question.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52937_ShortDesc", "Fingerless gloves for those who need dextrous hands")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52937_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Native rogues were the dominant element - dark-skinned, dark-eyed Zamorians, with daggers at their girdles and guile in their hearts.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

Among the shadow haunted streets of Shadizar and the wild, dangerous streets of The Maul, the dark-skinned Zamorian thieves work their stealthy trade.

A thief's fingers must be free to do nimble work - manipulating lockpicks, snatching purses and slitting throats. These gloves are designed to protect the hand and forearm while freeing the fingers to do their worst.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51540_ShortDesc", "A pair of knives forged in Zhaibar")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51540_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The governor checked his motion toward the sword on the table. He was within reach of the yard-long Zhaibar knife that glittered in the intruder's fist, and he knew the desperate quickness of a hillman.</> - People of the Black Circle

It is not known whether it is some special quality to the metal forged in Zhaibar, or if it is simply the training that they give their warriors, but all know that the wielder of a Zhaibar blade is to be feared.

Swift and precise are the Zhaibar blades in the hands of their wielders, offering a bonus to agility.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91039_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91039_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather boots are practical onboard a ship - for preventing splinters and broken toes, but also for kicking unfortunate prisoners over the side.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91037_ShortDesc", "A pair of gloves worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91037_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Leather gloves are practical onboard a ship - for preventing blisters, rope-burn and the occasional knife wound as well.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91035_ShortDesc", "A headscarf popular among Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91035_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

Freebooters attire themselves in all manner of flamboyant outfits, but the headscarf is cheap, popular and practical.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91038_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91038_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather pants offer the freedom to scamper along lines, while still being stiff enough to turn the sharp edge of a dagger. They also never need to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91036_ShortDesc", "A vest worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91036_LongDesc", "The flamboyant Zingaran Freebooters are both loved and feared in their home nation. The naval rivalry between Argos and Zingara forms a platform for troubadours to spin tales of Zingaran chivalry on the high seas and romanticize the swashbuckling rogues who fight to preserve Zingaran honor.

Never mentioned are the screams of their victims, plucked from burning caravels to be sold in the slave markets of the south. Never mentioned are the sacked coastal towns and slaughtered villagers, left to rot among their broken homes.

The sturdy leather vest is designed to turn the sharp edges of a saber but will offer little protection against a well-placed thrust. Still, it is practical for those who spend their lives on ships, and never needs to be scoured for rust.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ConanSword_DLC_ItemTable_8000_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword adorned with runes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ConanSword_DLC_ItemTable_8000_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan did not shout. His eyes coals of blue fire and his lips smiling bleakly, he lashed right and left with his two-handed sword.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Men speak of Atlantis as merely a legend, a place that once existed but has passed into the ancestral memory of mankind, lost beneath the waves thousands of years ago.

This sword, discovered by Conan the Cimmerian when he stumbled into the depths of some forgotten pit, seems to resonate with the sorrow of that long-lost continent. Scholars who have glimpsed the blade agree that the runes are of no language spoken on the Thurian continent and the blade itself seems to be of a metal that none have ever seen before.

How it came to be in the Exiled Lands is also a matter of much speculation.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ConanSword_DLC_ItemTable_8001_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword adorned with runes")
column4:

How it came to be in the Exiled Lands is also a matter of much speculation.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "ConanArmor_DLC_ItemTable_8001_ShortDesc", "A well-crafted, regal circlet")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ConanArmor_DLC_ItemTable_8001_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan's armor of black plate-mail, with the vizored salade, and the dark plumes nodding over the wivern crest. Over all they put the silken surcoat with the royal lion worked in gold upon the breast, and they girt him with a broad gold-buckled belt which supported a jewel-hilted broad-sword in a cloth-of-gold scabbard.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

It is whispered that some threads of destiny are so strong that men dream of them before they come to pass. Not the vile dreams of the Black Lotus, but dreams more like memories, only rippling backwards into the past.

This set of armor was conceived in such a dream. In this dream, a man stalked prey in a pantherskin loin-clout, fought savagely on the deck of a corsair, led desert raiders to fall upon travelling caravans and, finally, sat gloomily upon a throne decked in this armor.

What the dream signifies is unclear, but the design of the armor was plucked from the last vision of the dream and made reality. It is a symbol of ambition and, perhaps a future yet to come.

This circlet offers little protection, but the simple elegant design draws the eye. ")

column4:
